professional_statement: Dr. Houtan Chaboki is a board certified facial plastic surgeon who sees patients from Washington DC, Maryland, and northern Virginia. Rhinoplasty and minimally invasive nasal surgery, eyelid surgery, face lifts, and nonsurgical facial rejuvenation (Botox® Cosmetic, facial fillers, skin care) are his specialties as a facial cosmetic surgeon. An individualized approach with each aesthetic patient, he provides various treatment options.,,Dr. Chaboki received his undergraduate degree in biomedical engineering at Northwestern University and his medical degree at the University of Illinois at Chicago. He completed his residency in head and neck surgery and a fellowship in Facial Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery at Mount Sinai Medical Center in New York City.

review_text:
Dr. Chaboki is thorough, diligent and quite professional. His staff spends adequate time processing first time patients and along with the ZocDoc appointments process, makes it quite convenient. Dr. Chaboki is well recommended for his professionalism and high standards! ,Incredibly warm and easy to talk whilst remaining highly professional.,Personable and professional.,Dr. Chaboki Is an excellent doctor.  He is very thorough, patient and takes time to answer any questions.  Unlike other doctors, I never feel like he just breezes through my visit.  I highly recommend Dr. Chaboki for any ENT needs.  His office staff (receptionist) could use some improvement.  I found it difficult to actually reach someone, maybe he has only one staff person?  When I went to check-in she was not the friendliest person.  I went from good mood to bad mood with her attitude and tone.  Ex- I asked “how many people are ahead of me.”  Her response in snappy tone “not sure.”  Hmm…  if she can’t how many people are ahead of me I really hope she does not do any billing. The rest of the staff and Dr. Chaboki are fantastic so do not let one person deter you from seeing a great doctor!     
,I have seen Dr. Chaboki for years and he is fantastic!  He is very efficient but takes time to explain what is going on and possible options.  The only negative is with his staff.  I tried to call today to ask a question and was put on hold for 15 minutes. I was then disconnected and never got to speak to a staff member.  The office definitely needs to fix their telephone system!  Even with the office issue I still highly recommend Dr. Chaboki! 
,I had a last minute problem and needed to be seen immediately.  ZocDoc and Dr. Chaboki's office made this possible.  

The service and process was excellent on both ends.  

I would not hesitate to go back in the future for other problems, procedures or routine check-ups.  ,Very thorough, competent, professional.  I would recommend him without reservation.,Dr. Chaboki immediately addresses challenges you are facing and is great about being in touch if you find yourself needing follow-up for some reason.  I am a big fan.,This is my second visit to Dr. Chaboki's office.  I had such a good experience last year visiting him, but especially communicating with him after the appointment via email while I traveled for work and was not responding to the prescription. He will continue to be my preferred ENT.,I really enjoyed my appointment with Dr. Chaboki. He was very informative, listened attentively and let me know my options for my problems as well as the risks and benefits of each option. For those looking for an ENT, I highly recommend Dr. Chaboki, he was wonderful,I give top marks to Dr. Chaboki.  He is highly knowledgable and experienced and his skills and ability will make you feel safe and at ease immediately.  He is also very patient and friendly and takes a great deal of time to answer all questions and cover all basis.  This was my first encounter with a plastic surgeon and I am delighted it was with Dr. Chaboki.  I recommend his unreservedly.   ,NO doubt this Doctor is brilliant and quite accomplished. He is also very kind and charming.
He saw me for severe ear pain and pressure in both ears, yet no infection was to be seen from looking at eardrum. I thought that the pressure of the ear can be measured with a special instrument...but it was not employed. I was relieved that there was nothing 'serious'; I felt quite perplexed as to how I could have such incredible ear and head pain. Helpfully, Dr.Chaboki explained other reasons that could cause my pain and gave me excellent referrals with which to follow up. ,This is a very brilliant and kind man who explains everything.,I was taken back within 5 min. and spoke with a doctor right away. Problem solved and out the door in less than 45 min. start to finish.,Dr. Chaboki is an absolute miracle worker. He is knowledgable, efficient, and gets right to the heart of the matter. I was especially pleased to be provided with long term solutions to my problem, which hadn't happened before with other Doctors. In short, he is outstanding. And that's sometimes hard to find in the medical profession.,Dr. Chaboki was very helpful and friendly.  He diagnosed and fully solved my problem very fast.  I was in and out of there in 30 minutes.,I have been to Doctor Chaboki before and he is always pleasant and answers all my questions.,NA,NA,NA,NA

name: Dr. Susan Grant
og:description: A neighborhood private ob/gyn practice that cares: Providing Women's Health Care for twenty years. We take the time to listen, to understand, to educate. We return your calls promptly. Wellness, obstetrics, contraception and family planning, infection, sexual issues, fertility, perimenopause and menopause, emergencies, gyn surgery. Our staff will help you with insurance/reimbursement questions. First and foremost, come prepared for a very honest experience. We want to know who you are, because we believe that your health concerns are integrally related to where you are in life, your relationships, experiences, stresses and dreams.

review_text:
Dr. Grant is so nice and patient, explaining everything clear. I feel comfortable though English is not my first language since sometimes those terminologies make me confuse. Highly recommended!,Dr. Grant is a WONDERFUL doctor, professional, SMART AND HUMAN.   She takes her time every single visit, she truly CARES about all of her patients, offers advice and/or suggestions for any/every medical condition I speak to her about. She ensures that I am paying attention to / addressing what I need to from a medical standpoint.  She is truly a Godsend, BEST doctor around in my book! ,I was seeing as associate of Dr. Grant's for over 30 years -- she left the practice, so I've been seeing Dr. Grant for the past 3 years.  Dr. Grant is a GREAT doctor, so very professional but yet has the HUMAN TOUCH.  She explains every single thing down to detail, will talk about any concerns including non-gyn issues.  She is the epitome of what all doctors should be like.  I absolutely love her! ,She is very nice and now she would be my future doctor too.,Dr Grant was very professional and lovely, too!
Seemed really interested in the the state of my health and asked me also fun questions about myself which helped diffuse the tension.
I will certainly go back! Great doctor!,She was very thorough in understanding my medical history, had clearly read materials previously submitted, and genuinely cared about me as a person - seems like that would not be something so outrageous to comment on, but in dealing with medical professionals, it's more rare than not!,She was amazing! Straightforward but gentle. I would definitely go back to her.,Bit of a wait upon arriving, but other than that I couldn't have a higher opinion of Dr. Grant.

She is very professional, very knowledgeable, and takes the time to explain things, engage you in a conversation about your health, answers any questions in a clear and simple to understand way, prompt about following up, makes your visit efficient but not rushed. ,I love that she is always very friendly, attentive to everything that is being said, and clear in all her explanations.
The staff is attentive and friendly.
The waiting room is clean and relaxing. ,The best! Dr. Grant is very professional and very compassionate.  She made a great effort to help me with managing payments for her services because I have no health insurance.  She takes the time to sit down with you to discuss results and to answer any questions.  ,I really appreciated her thoroughness.  As a first visit I left feeling confident she was the right choice of a doctor who would understand my needs.  ,.,Very comforting and very helpful. Took her time examining me and answering my millions of questions. Highly recommended. ,Dr. Grant is absolutely wonderful. I went to her for an emergency while I was visiting the city, and she was beyond comforting, professional and thorough. She listened to all of my questions and worries with understanding and patience and called me to check in on how I was doing. I am now switching from my former doctor to be her patient. ,I had an amazing experience with Dr. Grant. She is very thorough, takes her time with the patient, and she and the office staff are professional and friendly. ,She was great -- very warm and caring and professional. Very thorough in her examination and I felt very safe in her hands.,As usual, a very sweet person. Very dedicated, responsible and professional. I am very happy to be her patient. Thanks Dr. Susan!,Exceptional and thorough.  A true professional,Dr. Grant was very helpful. She was patient and took a thorough history before my physical exam. I was very nervous for the appointment, and by the end was feeling assured and confident. Despite the fact that I kept her for quite some time, I never felt rushed, which is refreshing. During the examination itself, she was sensitive and professional. 

If you do not already know, she does not deal with insurance companies, so be prepared to pay the full rate. However, you will not feel sorry or that it is a waste of money. Dr. Grant really earns the trust of her patients. NB not that it is avoidable, but be sure to mention you do not have insurance. She will prescribe generics and depending on the labs may provide a discount. ,She is awesome. She really makes my first  visit  comfortable. A very warm, nice doctor. I will surely recommend her to my friends.,Very friendly and professional,She is awesome ! Going to the gynecologist is never funny, but she makes it so much easier !
She is very sweet, explain you everything with simple words, she takes her time to get to know you. ,She was so personable and amazing I liked alot!!,Dr. Grant is one of the most caring doctors I have ever met. I only met her once (so far!) but she remembered me when I called. She also called and emailed me several times just to check up on me since I was having surgery. She is a knowledgeable and trustworthy doctor, and I will definitely be going back.,Even though the wait was a bit long(30mins), it was worth it. Dr Grant was very helpful and put me at ease straight away and tried to get me the best price for the tests available as I didn't have insurance. ,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

name: Dr. Beatrice Im
og:description: Book now with Dr. Beatrice Im of Brooklyn, NY. Read patient reviews and ratings, and make an appointment online, instantly. View insurance networks Dr. Beatrice Im participates in, and a map of the practice location.
og:title: Dr. Beatrice Im - Profile by Zocdoc
professional_statement: Dr. Beatrice Im completed her residency in Obstetrics & Gynecology at the New York Presbyterian Weill-Cornell Center in 2007. She then practiced and taught at the Bugando Medical Centre and the Weill-Bugando University College of Health Sciences as on-the-ground faculty for Weill-Cornell Medical College in Mwanza, Tanzania. While there, she focused on improving emergency obstetric care and started several different programs in women’s health including those for cervical cancer screening, emergency obstetric ultrasound, and laparoscopy. Though she continues her involvement overseas with medical education for faculty and residents, her vision for bringing compassionate quality care to patients in her hometown has brought Dr. Im back to New York City.

og:description: I have a solo practice of office gynecology so that I can offer personalized care to my patients.  I provide comprehensive office gynecology services. I trained at Harvard Medical School and Harvard teaching hospitals and opened a private practice in Boston in 1973.  I am an assistant clinical professor of gynecology and reproductive biology at Harvard Medical School and I teach gynecology residents at the Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center.  My clinic teaching focuses on technical expertise and I work hard to teach my residents to pay close attention to what their patients tell them.  I believe this is the foundation of a positive doctor-patient relationship.

professional_statement: Dr. Preys graduated from UCLA medical school and did her residency in obstetrics and gynecology at USC. While at USC, she became interested in cosmetic procedures involving the genitalia. In particular, she worked on multiple complex vaginal restorations on patients that had female circumcision.,Dr. Preys is board certified in Obstetrics and Gynecology. She is also part of the teaching faculty at both Cedars Sinai and USC Medical School.,In private practice since 2000, she practices all aspects of obstetrics and gynecology with special interest in vaginal cosmetic procedures and diagnosis/treatment of cervical dysplasia/HPV lesions

A followup consultation, visits to Dr. Ali are always pleasant. Amazing consideration, you never feel rushed by him.,My visit to Dr Ks office was a pleasant one.i was attended to promptly and his staff was nice. Dr K took his time to ask me thorough questions and asked me about my concerns. ,He is an excellent physician,Both Dr. Alireza and his staff were very courteous and helpful. I left my visit with Dr. Alireza knowing that I have found a doctor that I will continue to go to in the future. ,Marvelous doctor.
,I think Dr. Khazaeizadeh is great. I am not the kind that  just takes anybody's word for something, I need to understand and be convinced. Even though I have no medical knowledge, I think I know my body and have acceptable IQ to be able to understand if things are explained to me. I want to know what is going on and why I need to do such and such treatment. I really appreciate that Dr. Khazaeizadeh respects my intelligence enough to answer my questions and share the logic for his diagnosis or course of treatment. He answers my questions patiently without making me feel rushed or unwelcome. This is very nice and unfortunately not that common. ,Dr Ali is very competent and gives me a feeling of trust with my health care.
,Excellent. Took his time to listen to me and to discuss a course of action. ,My husband and I am happy with Dr. Alireza Khazaeizadeh and friendly and polite receptionists.  Dr. Ali has been professional, excellent manner, and knowledgeable for our past visits.  He tries to make sure we stay healthy by listening to us, running some tests when it's necessary, and reviews any results with us, and makes us feel that our health is taken care of.  The receptionists are kind and caring.  Very clean.,nice and quick, got good advice.  ,Again Dr. Ali is awesome - highly recommended!,Dr Khazeizadeh is great. He is very thorough and also very pleasant. He takes his time to hear you out and tries to explain the medical concepts in a language that is understandable to the patient.  It was my first visitv there, but he was very friendly and spent at least 30 minutes examining, listening to me talking about three different problems. I do not see foctors often and I usually have more than one thing to ask my doctor when I go. With most of my previous doctors I felt like after they had done the first thing they were ready to show me out. Dr. Khazaeizadeh is different. He does not rush you and does not try to get rid of you or have you make another time. I get the feeling thst he really likes his job and is genuinely interested in your health. ,This was my first appointment for a general consultation.  Nurse who checked me in and did my blood pressure was really friendly.  Doctor seemed genuinely concerned with my medical history and concerns.  Even mentioned that if I ever have a gynecological issue or need a women's exam, the office's other, female doctor (his wife) is available if I prefer a female doctor.   ,Professional, knowledgeable, attentive, and friendly. Staff and office setting are also very nice.,Wanted to switch my doctor from Newport Beach to somewhere a little closer.  Saw Dr. Ali had great reviews and decided to give him a try.  VERY impressed!  Took his time answering questions and really getting to know me.  The staff was great too.  I'll definitely keep him as my primary.,The staff and doctor were really great. Everyone was nice and calm. I was a new patient, they answered all my questions right away, and gave me correct information. The environment was nice. It went fast and was a stress-free visit. :),Very nice and equipped office, nice staff and a good doctor. ,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

og:description: Peter is board certified in Obstetrics & Gynecology since 1995.  He started practice at Virginia Mason Medical Center after completing medical school and residency at the University of Washington.  When he decided to move into private practice, he joined North Seattle Women's Specialists in 1996.  Ballard Women's Health was started in October 2008 when Peter and Heidi decided to shift their emphasis to women's health and gynecology.   In addition to women's health care, Dr. Brandon performs medical aesthetics, including Botox/Dysport, Fillers, Skin rejuvenation, treatment of stretch marks, and SmartLipo liposuction. Peter is married to Ellen Wilber, MD (also an Obstetrician/Gynecologist at the PolyClinic).  They have two daughters and are active with horseback riding, bicycling, travel, and surviving the teenage years.

name: Dr. Joseph Fishkin
og:description: NOTE: There are other appointments available if none of these displayed on ZocDoc work for you. Dr. Joseph Fishkin is a Board-Certified Comprehensive Ophthalmologist. He treats all ages, and specializes in all aspects of eye care, including cataract surgery, laser vision correction, contact lenses, glaucoma and eye infections. Over the past year, he has been awarded both the Patients' Choice award, and the Most Compassionate Doctor award, a distinction shared with fewer than 3% of the nation's doctors. Dr. Fishkin has served as medical technology consultant for a variety of medical internet companies and has been involved in the development of award-winning software, devices, and websites. He draws on his technological expertise to ensure that the latest developments in ophthalmology are made available for his patients. Dr. Fishkin's philosophy is that every person who visits his office deserves a comprehensive eye exam. Every patient is greeted with a smile. You will not be rushed in and out. Every question you have will be answered, and you will leave the office with a complete understanding of your ocular health.

professional_statement: Dr. Hsu moved to Washington to practice optometry in September 2001 and has been practicing in Redmond since August 2002.  Because he works so close to the Microsoft campus, Dr. Hsu has studied the effects of computer vision syndrome on the visual system and applies it to his daily practice.  In addition, Dr. Hsu is very interested in the latest technology so we have introduced the Optos Retinal Exam as part of our services.  Furthermore, to screen for diseases such as glaucoma, we have also purchased the Humphrey Matrix system to test visual fields.,,Dr. Hsu lives in Bellevue with his wife and son. professional_statement: *ANNUAL PHYSICALS CANNOT BE SCHEDULED ONLINE*,,Dr. Carol Spies was born in Los Angeles, California. She attended college at Stanford University and medical school at Tulane University. She completed her internship and residency at the University of Colorado. She started the group "Front Range Internal Medicine" in 1989 and has worked there ever since. Dr. Spies enjoys all aspects of primary care. She particularly likes the opportunity to follow her patients over time. She is happy that she has been able to follow many of her patients for over twenty years, in some cases also caring for their children and grandchildren. Dr. Spies has two teenage sons, and enjoys hiking, reading and Sudoku in her spare time.,,

name: Dr. Steven Schrager
og:description: Dr. Steven M. Schrager received his undergraduate degree from Boston University, where he also graduated from Boston University School of Medicine in 1976. He completed his general surgical and otolaryngology residency at the University of South Florida Affiliated Hospitals in Tampa, FL. Dr. Schrager has been in private practice in South Florida since 1981 and is Board Certified by the American Board of Otolaryngology. He is a fellow in the American Academy of Otolaryngology and an active member of the Florida Society of Otolaryngology  and the American Medical Association. Dr. Schrager is formerly the otolaryngology Consultant for the Broward Center for the Performing Arts and has served as the ENT physician for the Florida Marlins and the Chief of the Department of Otolaryngology – Head and Neck Surgery at North Ridge Hospital.

name: Dr. Larry Kosova
og:description: Dr. Kosova is one of the leaders of Sports Medicine and injury patients in the Western Suburbs. He is Board Certified and treats patients from referrals from some of the leading Medical Groups and Physical Therapists that treat Athletes in the area. Dr Kosova has been practicing Podiatric Medicine and Surgery for the last 2O years in the western suburb. He and his practice have been featured on CBS Channel 2, NBC Channel 5, ABC Channel 7 for treatment of patients in Illinois and new techniques used. He has been interviewed for Chicago Tribune about heel pain to Joaquin Noah of the Chicago Bulls. Dr. Kosova was also interviewed by a Los Angelos paper about Kobe Bryants new Basketball Shoe. Dr Kosova uses new technology to get your back to your activity quickly. He was one of the first in the United States trained and used shockwave treatment for heel pain but now uses an advanced technique of Topaz for some tendon and heel pain issues. He also has techniques that other doctors might not know about to help heal your pain to get you back into your sport quickly. His patients have run multiple marathons like Boston Marathon , Hawaii  and Chicago Marathon and has many Triathletes and Iron man athletes and has patients that are nationally ranked tennis and multiple dances like Irish Dance. Dr Kosova also sees many high school athletes for all sports including baseball, football, volleyball and wrestling.  Dr Kosova’s work with advanced techniques in tendon and ligament repair has gain him favorable reviews with everyone from the weekend athlete to collegiate and semi pro. He is also one of the only Master Surgeons for flatfoot correction in both children and adults in the Western Suburbs. Dr. Kosova’s experienced and friendly staff will assure you a pleasant visit. Dr. Kosova takes time to understand and correctly diagnose your individual foot and ankle condition and he looks forward to talking to you about all your families foot and ankle needs.

name: Dr. Brett Bowman
og:description: Dr. Brett Bowman is a board certified optometrist who promises to spend as much time as you need for comments or questions regarding your vision. Dr. Bowman will check your eyes annually for eye disease such as Cataract, Glaucoma, Diabetes, and Macular Degeneration. Dr. Bowman is well versed in the latest technology such as the new wavefront guided progressive lenses, crizal protective coatings, transitions, and ultralite high index plastic lenses. Their knowledge and experience will help you choose the right options to fit your needs. We provide medical eyecare as well, treating eye infections, dry eye syndrome, styes, and other external eye disease. We can also help refer you to the appropriate ophthalmologist in the case of more serious vision problems.

name: Dr. Brett Bowman
og:description: Dr. Brett Bowman is a board certified optometrist who promises to spend as much time as you need for comments or questions regarding your vision. Dr. Bowman will check your eyes annually for eye disease such as Cataract, Glaucoma, Diabetes, and Macular Degeneration. Dr. Bowman is well versed in the latest technology such as the new wavefront guided progressive lenses, crizal protective coatings, transitions, and ultralite high index plastic lenses. Their knowledge and experience will help you choose the right options to fit your needs. We provide medical eyecare as well, treating eye infections, dry eye syndrome, styes, and other external eye disease. We can also help refer you to the appropriate ophthalmologist in the case of more serious vision problems.

professional_statement: Dr. Szilvia Nagy completed her residency training at New York Downtown Hospital, after which she spent time in San Antonio, Texas, in private practice. She returned to New York and joined our team in June 2012. Dr. Nagy’s clinical interests include management of abnormal pap smears/HPV, treatment of sexually transmitted diseases and counseling on safe sex practices, contraceptive counseling, medical and surgical management of abnormal uterine bleeding and general obstetrical care. name: Dr. Jerry Floyd
og:description: Dr. Jerry Floyd is a family physician who works with Saint Francis Medical Partners. He treats patients, from age 7 and up, in Millington and Greater Tennessee. He is a diplomat of the American Board of Family Practice and a member of the American Academy of Family Physicians. Originally from Palatka, Florida, Dr. Floyd is the beneficiary of an international educational career. He received degrees from both St. John’s River Community College in Palatka, Florida and Georgia Southern College in Statesboro, Georgia.  He then attended medical school at Benito Juarez-Abraham Lincoln Escuela de Medicina in Mexico and Spartan Health Sciences University in Bieux Fort, Saint Lucia, where he completed his medical degree.  Dr. Floyd attended the University of Tennessee Healthplex Program to complete his residency in family practice. When he is not treating patients, Dr. Floyd enjoys tennis, chess, travel, and spending time with his family. He is married to Frances Floyd and has one child.

name: Dr. Joseph Kerpsack
og:description: Dr. Joseph Kerpasck is a board certified Ob/Gyn physician with over nearly two decades of private practice experience caring for women.  He recently relocated to Clermont from Ohio from a busy Ob/Gyn practice. Dr. Kerpsack's philosophy is to listen to the patient and give her the time she deserves whether it is for a yearly visit or a problem focused appointment.  Taking a through history and taking into consideration the entire body is imperative in making the correct diagnosis and then recommending options for individualized treatment.   The patient should always be involved in the decision process to fit her personal needs. He graduated from Canfield High School in 1986 in Canfield Ohio.  He received a Bachelors of Science in chemistry from the University of Miami in Coral Gables, Florida in 1990.  Dr. Kerpsack then moved back to Ohio to attend Wright State University School of Medicine where he earned his Doctor of Medicine degree in 1994.  Soon it was back to the South for specialty training in Obstetrics and Gynecology in New Orleans, LA at Ochsner Clinic.  Upon completion of residency in 1998, Dr. Kerpsack returned to his home town in Ohio to practice where he had 12 wonderful years delivering babies and meeting the healthcare needs of women.  Dr. Kerpsack and his beloved wife Christie of almost 20 years relocated to Clermont in November 2009.  They have four wonderful children the youngest being Sophia was adopted from South Korea.  Other children are Tyler, Christopher, and Sarah who are all involved in numerous activities.

name: Dr. Amit Patel
og:description: “I believe being an oncologist is not only an important responsibility but a true privilege. Every patient I meet represents an opportunity for me to make a real difference and to help turn a cancer patient into a cancer survivor. This is why I strive to provide the most attentive, effective, and advanced care possible. And I do it with heartfelt empathy, guidance, and support for my patients and their families.” Dr. Patel received his medical degree from St. George’s University School of Medicine where he was inducted into the Iota Epsilon Alpha International Medical Honor Society. He completed his internship and residency at the University of Medicine and Dentistry of New Jersey – New Jersey Medical School. He was selected to serve as Chief Medical Resident and was a Clinical Instructor at New Jersey Medical School. Dr. Patel completed a fellowship in hematology & oncology at St. Luke’s Roosevelt Hospital Center, University Hospital of Columbia University College of Physicians and Surgeons. Dr. Patel is a Diplomat of the American Board of Internal Medicine and is an active member of the American Society of Clinical Oncology, American Society of Hematology, Oncology Society of New Jersey, American Medical Association and American College of Physicians. He has also submitted numerous abstracts to national scientific meetings. Dr. Varghese sees both adult and pediatric patients for the  evaluation, treatment and management of allergic and non-allergic asthma, nasal and ocular allergies, exercise induced asthma, sinusitis, food allergies, pet allergies, allergic skin conditions such as contact dermatitis, eczema and urticaria (hives) /angioedema.  Other areas of focus include stinging insect allergy and medication/drug induced allergy for which he has authored the only paper devoted solely to this topic in the medical literature. He also has an interest in the evaluation of primary deficiencies of the immune system.

Overall the visit was good.  I felt that Dr. Varghese will help me to get the right treatment over time.  All of the other staff were also kind and willing to listen to me.  The office is on the newer side and they have all the latest technology which was very nice.  I'm thankful for Dr. Varghese!  ,It was great! Very Clean place i love it! They told me exactly what they where going to do and how the process would be. The doctor showed me a video of my nasal cavity that he took with a long camera. He explained my situation and made follow up visits. ,Dr. Varghese is extremely passionate about his specialty and it shows in his confidence and care for the patient.  You know he's committed to getting you better and couldn't recommend anyone better.,Very attentive and informative. Awesome staff. Great doctor and services. ,Dr. Varghese was very knowledgeable, professional, and friendly. It was the best doctor experience I have had so far.,Dr, Varghese listens. He asks questions to help determine the issue and is very effective in his recommendations and prescriptions. He helped me when five other doctors could not.,After a referral from my ENT to visit this office, I was very pleasantly surprised by Dr. Varghese's impressive knowledge, passion for his specialty,overall empathetic and friendly manner in explaining how to get me on the path to feeling better from persistent allergies. Just as friendly and courteous were his nurses and staff. I highly recommend.,Their service was excellent and clear explanation for everything. I personally recommend to any one to visit Dr mathew m Varghese MD,Very informative and thorough to get to the bottom of what is going on with me and my 2 year old.,Before seeing Dr. Varghese, I was constantly sneezing with an itchy nose and watery eyes. I made an appointment with him after reading positive reviews online. At my first appointment, I was there for almost 3 hours. I have never been to a doctor who was so thorough and spent so much time with me. It is clear that Dr. Varghese is very passionate about his work and his patients. He and the nurses performed a slew of tests to determine what I was allergic to (turns out just about everything), as well as various breathing tests for my asthma and nasal issues. He also has a really cool video scope connected to an iPhone, so he showed me pictures and videos of what my nasal passages looked like. 
He prescribed me various eye drops, nose spray, inhalers, and a daily allergy pill to take, and they spent time showing me the proper way to use the inhaler and the nose spray (I had been doing it wrong all along). It’s a lot to take, but I was feeling significantly better within only a few days. I have also been doing the weekly allergy shots and am close to being on maintenance shots only (once a month). I feel infinitely better than I used to and am so happy to have found such a wonderful practice. 
His staff are WONDERFUL and also take a lot of time with you to explain things and listen. The practice can get very busy so make sure you allow yourself enough time when getting weekly shots and particularly on your first visit. They are open every Saturday now, which is very convenient for those who work during the week. 
,Dr. Varghese has been treating me for almost a year for my accute allergies. He is professional, caring and he truly listens to what you have to say.  I feel much better since being in his care. His STAFF is amazing from the receptionist to the medical assistant.,Dr. Varghese is an amazing doctor. He is very diligent and follows up constantly with my daughter's care. I am very thankful to have him as my daughter's doctor. ,My visit was educational and symptom relief started immediately. ,Excellent doctor, explained clearly all procedures being done, very friendly and his employees super professional and friendly.,Wonderful visit all around, Dr. Varghese is awesome he answered all my questions without feeling rushed. Lovely staff, they made me feel comfortable and were all very tentative.
Thanks =)
,Excellent experience with Dr. Varghese, He is knowledgeable and dedicated. We would definitely recommend this doctor.,Dr Varghese was very polite and took his time listening. His staff was very nice.,Doctor was very knowledgeable, took his time explaining my son's condition, very professional.,Dr. Varghese was very thorough, friendly, and personal. His passion for his work is self-evident. The office uses modern and updated technology and all the staff are very friendly. I would highly recommend this doctor!,Dr. Varghese is amazing and so are his staff. I brought my 2 children tday one who is 4 years old and one who is 2 years old and he was amazing when checking them!!! They loved him and Stephanie was the best nurse.. I was given the answers I have been waiting for which is a big relief.  I also love that dr. Varghese explains everything. ,Very knowledgeable allergist. My son has been getting allergy shots for months now and it has helped tremendously! Will highly recommend this doctor to friends and family. ,Dr. Varghese is sent from above so to speak. Right of the bat he knows what's wrong and what's appropriate remedy. He not only love his craft but his patients as well. His very knowledgeable and have a lots of patient answering endless questions. Most of all, his not money hungry kind of Doctor. His a kind of Doctor with a very big heart. And, its hard to find now a days...,My visit with Dr. Mathew Varghese was great as usual and amazing. Over the weekend I was coughing, wheezing and I had shortness of breath and I could not get any sleep because whenever I would lie down it would get worse. I had also run out of my backup inhaler which I had purchased two weeks ago and I knew the pharmacist would not allow me another refill so soon, I then purchased a vicks vapor steam, vapor rub, mucinex expectorant/cough suppressant anything that I thought would help because it felt like if I had the flu and asthma at the same time but the things I purchased were only a temporary Band-Aid because they only helped me for a few minutes before I went back to my coughing fit and shortness of breath, I did not want go to the ER because I still was not sure if I was just coming down with the flu and I did not want to be charged 2000 + dollars at the ER just for a check up. On Monday I went to see the doctor and the nurses where doing their regular check up on me and when they finally did the test where they measure/check how much air I can blow out my lungs and how fast, that is when I went into a very bad coughing fit Dr. Varghese immediately came into the room and had the nurses give me a nebulizer a shot and oh my gosh I immediately felt better. He knew that my issue was not a flu.He also said that he was going to treat me in his office because if I went to the ER it would cost me a lot of money and since he knew I was not working he did not want me to incur that expense when he could just administer the same treatments without the expense a hospital would. I was in really bad shape and I did not even know it. He prescribed me an antibiotic and some other medication which he said I had to take immediately which I did. I was able to finally sleep and breathe that night. I have never met a doctor that knows how to take care of his patients as well he does and the nurses are just as caring and amazing as he is. 

Before I met Dr. Varghese I had gone to my primary physician and a pulmonary specialist because I had been coughing day and night 7 days a week for three months and neither doctor could diagnose or tell me what I had. The pulmonary specialist even had the nerve to ask me if I wanted an antibiotic or an inhaler. I told her both because I am not sure what was wrong with me but what I really wanted to tell her was " I don't know you are the specialist aren't you supposed to tell me what I need or have" but instead I kept that thought to myself. The only doctor that was able to finally help me and tell me what I was suffering from (Asthma due to allergies) was Dr Varghese.

I recently got laid off from my job and I was afraid that I would not be able to continue my allergy shots or keep him as my doctor but instead of letting me walk away because I didn't have insurance they said that they did not want me to stop my treatments just because of money that they would work with me and I was offered a reasonable price so I could continue my shots and my follow ups I have been with them for about two years and I am very lucky that I came upon such an amazing Dr. and staff.,He has a wonderful bedside manner. He is smart. He is through and he is a good listener. His staff is competent and efficient. ,He is an amazing doctor and I am so happy that I went for a second opinion and he gave me answers that I have been looking for ... highly recommended!!!! ,I have been at this office twice and I loved it, the waiting time was not very long.  Nurses/medical assistances were very polite and friendly.  The Doctor the best! very nice and friendly, he cares about his patients and make them feel very confortable.  I would highly recomend this doctor.,Yes an yes absolutely Dr Matthewsis a great doctor and I will recommend to everyone,Amazing,all went well,Dr. Varghese is a very thorough, caring Dr.  He took the time to listen to all my concerns, addressed each issue in detail.  He took the time to explain everything and has a wonderful bedside manner.  His office staff is very friendly and welcoming.  ,We will continue to go,It was great! Friendly staff and Dr. Varghese is super nice and knowledgable. ,Knowledgeable with good beside manner.  Great experience with him and his office staff.,He's friendly and extremely intelligent.  He sized up my issue in short order and was quick to offer solutions.   He backed up his diagnosis asking his staff to call me in two days.,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

name: Dr. Mathew M. Varghese
og:description: Dr. Varghese has been the first author on several recent peer reviewed publications appearing in the Annals of Allergy and Asthma, Allergy and Asthma Proceedings, Allergy Asthma and Clinical Immunology Canadian) and Clinical & Experimental Allergy (UK). He has also submitted numerous abstracts to national scientific meetings. Dr. Varghese sees both adult and pediatric patients for the  evaluation, treatment and management of allergic and non-allergic asthma, nasal and ocular allergies, exercise induced asthma, sinusitis, food allergies, pet allergies, allergic skin conditions such as contact dermatitis, eczema and urticaria (hives) /angioedema.  Other areas of focus include stinging insect allergy and medication/drug induced allergy for which he has authored the only paper devoted solely to this topic in the medical literature. He also has an interest in the evaluation of primary deficiencies of the immune system.

Overall the visit was good.  I felt that Dr. Varghese will help me to get the right treatment over time.  All of the other staff were also kind and willing to listen to me.  The office is on the newer side and they have all the latest technology which was very nice.  I'm thankful for Dr. Varghese!  ,It was great! Very Clean place i love it! They told me exactly what they where going to do and how the process would be. The doctor showed me a video of my nasal cavity that he took with a long camera. He explained my situation and made follow up visits. ,Dr. Varghese is extremely passionate about his specialty and it shows in his confidence and care for the patient.  You know he's committed to getting you better and couldn't recommend anyone better.,Very attentive and informative. Awesome staff. Great doctor and services. ,Dr. Varghese was very knowledgeable, professional, and friendly. It was the best doctor experience I have had so far.,Dr, Varghese listens. He asks questions to help determine the issue and is very effective in his recommendations and prescriptions. He helped me when five other doctors could not.,After a referral from my ENT to visit this office, I was very pleasantly surprised by Dr. Varghese's impressive knowledge, passion for his specialty,overall empathetic and friendly manner in explaining how to get me on the path to feeling better from persistent allergies. Just as friendly and courteous were his nurses and staff. I highly recommend.,Their service was excellent and clear explanation for everything. I personally recommend to any one to visit Dr mathew m Varghese MD,Very informative and thorough to get to the bottom of what is going on with me and my 2 year old.,Before seeing Dr. Varghese, I was constantly sneezing with an itchy nose and watery eyes. I made an appointment with him after reading positive reviews online. At my first appointment, I was there for almost 3 hours. I have never been to a doctor who was so thorough and spent so much time with me. It is clear that Dr. Varghese is very passionate about his work and his patients. He and the nurses performed a slew of tests to determine what I was allergic to (turns out just about everything), as well as various breathing tests for my asthma and nasal issues. He also has a really cool video scope connected to an iPhone, so he showed me pictures and videos of what my nasal passages looked like. 
He prescribed me various eye drops, nose spray, inhalers, and a daily allergy pill to take, and they spent time showing me the proper way to use the inhaler and the nose spray (I had been doing it wrong all along). It’s a lot to take, but I was feeling significantly better within only a few days. I have also been doing the weekly allergy shots and am close to being on maintenance shots only (once a month). I feel infinitely better than I used to and am so happy to have found such a wonderful practice. 
His staff are WONDERFUL and also take a lot of time with you to explain things and listen. The practice can get very busy so make sure you allow yourself enough time when getting weekly shots and particularly on your first visit. They are open every Saturday now, which is very convenient for those who work during the week. 
,Dr. Varghese has been treating me for almost a year for my accute allergies. He is professional, caring and he truly listens to what you have to say.  I feel much better since being in his care. Lovely staff, they made me feel comfortable and were all very tentative.

Over the weekend I was coughing, wheezing and I had shortness of breath and I could not get any sleep because whenever I would lie down it would get worse. I had also run out of my backup inhaler which I had purchased two weeks ago and I knew the pharmacist would not allow me another refill so soon, I then purchased a vicks vapor steam, vapor rub, mucinex expectorant/cough suppressant anything that I thought would help because it felt like if I had the flu and asthma at the same time but the things I purchased were only a temporary Band-Aid because they only helped me for a few minutes before I went back to my coughing fit and shortness of breath, I did not want go to the ER because I still was not sure if I was just coming down with the flu and I did not want to be charged 2000 + dollars at the ER just for a check up. On Monday I went to see the doctor and the nurses where doing their regular check up on me and when they finally did the test where they measure/check how much air I can blow out my lungs and how fast, that is when I went into a very bad coughing fit Dr. Varghese immediately came into the room and had the nurses give me a nebulizer a shot and oh my gosh I immediately felt better. He knew that my issue was not a flu.He also said that he was going to treat me in his office because if I went to the ER it would cost me a lot of money and since he knew I was not working he did not want me to incur that expense when he could just administer the same treatments without the expense a hospital would. I was in really bad shape and I did not even know it. He prescribed me an antibiotic and some other medication which he said I had to take immediately which I did. I was able to finally sleep and breathe that night. I have never met a doctor that knows how to take care of his patients as well he does and the nurses are just as caring and amazing as he is.

name: Dr. Janice Trent
og:description: Janice R. Trent, Au.D., has practiced Audiology for over 20 years in a number of clinical settings. Her diverse career has included a total of 16 years of teaching and clinical supervision at Howard University, Washington, DC and Temple University, Philadelphia, PA. Dr. Trent has also worked as a clinical audiologist in hospital settings and private ENT practices. Dr Trent received her doctorate in Audiology (Au.D.) from the University of Florida, Gainesville, FL., her master’s degree (M.Ed.) in Audiology from Northeastern University, Boston, MA, and her bachelor’s degree (B.S.) in Communication Sciences and Disorders from Hampton University, Hampton, VA. She holds Maryland State Licensure in Audiology, a Certified Clinical Audiologist (CCC-A) through the American Speech-Language-Hearing Association; and is a Fellow of the American Academy of Audiology.

name: Dr. Danica Schulte
og:description: Dr. Danica J. Schulte received her MD from Loyola University Chicago, Stritch School of Medicine, and completed fellowships at both Cedars-Sinai Medical Center and UCLA. She has dual board certifications in both Allergy & Immunology, and Pediatric Infectious Diseases.    Dr. Schulte has practiced at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center for the past 12 years, and continues to participate in the teaching program and consultative practice at Cedars-Sinai in both Pediatric Infectious Diseases and Allergy and Immunology. She has been an acclaimed researcher, securing grants from the National Institutes of Health and the American Heart Association. She has published in several peer-reviewed medical periodicals and has written chapters in the premier Pediatric Infectious Diseases textbook, on Parvovirus and Passive Immunity. She is an Assistant Professor at both Cedars-Sinai and UCLA. Dr. Schulte grew up in Los Angeles, and lives in Sherman Oaks, CA with her husband and two beautiful children.

name: Dr. George Rodriguez-Paz
og:description: George Rodriguez-Paz is a careful and compassionate cardiologist working in Tamarac, FL. He graduated from the University of Puerto Rico School of Medicine and continued his education at James A. Haley Veteran's Hospital, completing both his internal medicine internship and residency. To complete his cardiology residency, he attended the University of South Florida College of Medicine.  Dr. Rodriguez-Paz, or “Dr. G,” specializes in heart health. He sees patients for a wide range of reasons, from high blood pressure and minor murmurs to heart failure and transplants. Dr. G performs tilt table testing, echocardiograms, TEE, and PTCA/PCI in order to help him diagnose heart issues. He also performs heart catheterization and uses the latest technology and equipment in his practice. He speaks fluent English and Spanish.

name: Dr. Enrique Rodriguez-Paz
og:description: Enrique Rodriguez-Paz is an insightful and analytical cardiologist located in Tamarac, FL. He received his medical degree from the Universidad Autónoma de Guadalajara. He then completed his internal medicine internship at Fajardo District Hospital and his residency at the Muhlenberg Regional Medical Center. Dr. Rodriguez-Paz completed his fellowship in cardiovascular disease from Deborah Heart and Lung Center. Dr. Rodriguez-Paz provides consultations for general heart conditions, high blood pressure, arrhythmia, and congestive heart disease. He performs catheterization, x-rays, echocardiograms, and other non-invasive procedures, such as tissue Doppler analysis. Dr. Rodriguez-Paz’s goal is to use his skills to help his patients avoid heart failure and improve their heart conditions by understanding the many factors involved in heart health and diseases.  Outside of work, Dr. Rodriguez-Paz enjoys sports and music. He speaks fluent English and Spanish.

Dr. Sheth has been involved in numerous research studies and is a published author.

review_text:
Excellent bedside manner- put my toddler at ease. You will not find a kinder, more knowledgeable doctor. ,Couldn't ask for a nicer, kinder allergist. ,He is one of the best and kindest doctors out there.  Not only does he truly care about his patients, but he is phenomenal at what he does. My breathing issues go beyond asthma, but he was able to figure out a treatment for me that my pulmonary doctor now uses. He's just the best. ,He his such a great doctors. Great with kids. Couldn't have asked for a better Doctor!!  He has fun with the kid and with their siblings waiting. He makes going to the doctor fun. ,My son and I had a very pleasurable experience with Dr Spiegel. He is very friendly and knowledgeable. I am comfortable with his diagnosis.  I would recommend Dr Spiegel.  ,It's always nice to see Dr. Bill.  He is funny and makes the appointment more fun than any other doctor appointment I have!  Even though it's fun, he always does a good job and helps me keep my asthma under control.  ,Highly recommend - even when they are busy, I don't feel rushed. He takes the time to fully explain and answer questions - more than that, if I don't have questions, he still repeats or provides extra info to make sure I understand. Practical, gives good advice and lets you be in control of your plan. ,Dr. Spiegel was wonderful. He made both the parents and patient very comfortable.  We left feeling informed and confident in the treatment.,I would highly recommend Dr Bill Spiegel,William is one the most down-to-earth and relate-able doctors I have ever seen.  He does a great job extracting information/symptoms and making recommendations.  Great conversation about allergy history also.,Dr. Spiegel is smart, kind, focused on patient needs and a great doctor. I have seen him for over 14 years and he is amazing, he goes above and beyond to diagnose and help you. ,Dr Spiegel, besides being an excellent clinician, is very affable and, certainly, makes the patient feel at ease.,Dr. Spiegel is a skillied diagnostician and has a warm, caring, professional style. His knowledge of treatment modalities and and latest studies/findings is impressive. Our family feels really assured and informed after leaving from a visit with Dr. Spiegel.,He is awesome.  ,Awesome as always.  Addressed all my issues.  Very nice and comforting.,Awesome! No waiting, doctor nurse and staff were all knowledgeable, friendly and helpful. All helped my 8 year old to feel more comfortable.,Dr. Spiegel was excellent with my 8year old and myself. His staff were friendly and professional. Highly recommend!,Dr. Bill is THE BEST doctor for children!  ,Quick, thorough, and had wonderful bedside manner. Would highly recommend ,I loved the doctor. He is the best. Caring and knowledgeable. ,He was really great with my 6year old and extremely knowledgeable about his problem. I will definitely make any future appointments I need with him!,Dr. Spiegel came highly recommendedby my Primary Care Physician, and I can se why. The ofice is clean, the staff pleasent and Professional. Dr. Spiegel was Very professional and friendly. I felt very comfortable and confident that I was in the best of hands!,Awesome!  He totally knows what he's talking about and made me feel super comfortable.  Helped me understand what was wrong, didn't just tell me what medicine I needed to go on.   Also joked around with me at times which was super nice!,Very courteous and professional.  Love the ability to make an appointment over zocdoc.,Wonderful experience - Dr. Spiegel was thorough and kind; staff was cheerful, helpful and quick. ,He is the most amazing doctor I've ever had,The best kids doctor EVER!!!,Terrific doctor and person. Spent plenty of time with me and clearly cared about my situation. I would recommend him highly!!!,Dr. Bill is the best!  Both my children suffer from anxiety and seeing a doctor was/is never a pleasant experience.  The staff as well as Dr. Bill made my children feel comfortable.  Dr. Bill is not only smart, he is funny and sweet!,Very professional.  He explained what he was going to do and hoped to find the right combination to make me feel more comfortable.,Dr Spiegel was great. He understood my problems and acted quickly to help me with the right medication and course of treatments!,Staff were friendly and prompt.  Dr. Spiegel suggested two options for treatment and explained the reasons for his preference.,Dr Bill is a brilliant and personable doctor.  I highly recommend him for help with allergies.  ,We were sent the paperwork via email and able to complete and scan them prior to the visit.  This saved us a lot of time.  The office notified us the day before the visit that our referral was not yet in the system, allowing us to, again, have a smooth registration the following day.
Dr. Spiegel did a trick upon meeting my sons, which they enjoyed.  He was very knowledgeable about my eldest's allergies and asked very specific questions.  The entire visit was seamless, including the medication observation period.  I was in and out in under one hour, with all time focused on my son and his issue.  I'm glad that my insurance changed, allowing me to find Dr. Spiegel.,My office visit was very pleasant. Everyone was polite and kind, including the front desk staff, the nurse and Dr. Spiegel. All of my questions were answered and I left with a solid plan to manage my health concerns. ,Great with kids!,Very knowledgable, great bedside manner. ,Dr. Spiegal is such a good doctor. He is so sweet as well as good at what he does. He is fantastic with my two young children. He really goes the extra mile in your visits. All doctors should be this good. ,Phenomenal doctor. Very knowledgeable and quickly won over my nervous 15 month old. Very highly recommended. ,I've been to a lot of doctors in my life...I've never had such FUN!!  Not only that, but they're professional, knowledgeable, and they listen.  High marks all the way around!!!,Great visit. Good suggestions.,Very kind, funny doctor. Put me at ease and explained several treatment options. ,Dr. "Bill" Spiegel is a great doctor with old school attitude and an enjoyable bedside manor. Office and staff are highly automated and high up on the tech curve.  So far, this is the only medical office I use that uses zocdoc.  Impressive!,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

name: Dr. William Spiegel
og:description: **Please Be Advised: If you are a NEW patient, you MUST book as a new patient on ZocDoc. Do not choose "I've seen this doctor before" William Spiegel, M.D. is a Senior Physician and Director with Allergy & Asthma Specialists, P.C., a group practice with eight locations in Philadelphia and surrounding suburbs. He is the Director of The Aspirin Allergy Treatment Center. He has practiced as a Board Certified Allergist/Immunologist since 1988. Dr. Spiegel received his Bachelor of Science degree from Pennsylvania State University and his Medical Degree from Temple University School of Medicine. His medical training continued at the University of Maryland Hospital where he was a Resident in Pediatrics. He was an officer in the United States Air Force for four years, attaining the rank of Major. He then became a Fellow in the Division of Adult and Pediatric Allergy & Immunology at Thomas Jefferson Hospital. Dr. Spiegel trained in the aspirin desensitization program at the Scripps Clinic and Research Foundation of LaJolla, Califormia. He is an attending physician in the Pulmonary and Allergy Department at St. Christopher's Hospital for Children. Dr. Spiegel is a Fellow of the American College of Allergy, Asthma and Immunology, a Fellow of the American Academy of Allergy, Asthma and Immunology, a member of the Pennsylvania Allergy and Asthma Association and the Philadelphia Allergy Society. Dr. Spiegel is certified by the American Board of Pediatrics and the American Board of Allergy & Clinical Immunology. He has been involved in over 100 clinical research studies for numerous international pharmaceutical companies conducting many double blinded, placebo controlled trials. He has co-authored over 20 articles that have appeared in the Annals of Allergy, Asthma & Immunology, and the Journal of Allergy a

name: Dr. Terence Delaney
og:description: Dr. Delaney is a specialist in orthopedic surgery, sports medicine and joint replacement surgery. He received his M.D. from New York Medical College in 1986 and went on to do a surgical internship at St. Luke's Hospital/Columbia University in New York. He completed a four year orthopedic residency at Catholic Medical Center/Cornell University in 1992. During this time he trained in spinal reconstruction and pediatric orthopedics at NYU/Hospital for Joint Diseases as well as an advanced AO fracture and trauma course. He then completed a one year Joint Replacement Fellowship at Stanford University in PaloAlto . He has been in private practice in Los Gatos, California since 1993. Dr. Delaney is a member of the American Academy of Orthopaedic Surgeons www.aaos.org and is Board Certified by the American board of Orthopaedic Surgeons. www.abos.org. Dr. Delaney maintains current with the latest in orthopedic techniques by attending lectures and seminars on a regular basis. He is one of the first physicians in the area to treat patients with Platelet Rich Plasma (PRP) therapy and the only Orthopedic Surgeon in the area who regularly implants the Biomet Signature Custom Knee Prosthesis. In addition Dr Delaney has been trained in and performs the Oxford Unicompartmental Knee, The Birmingham Hip Resurfacing and routinely utilizes Minimally Invasive Surgery (MIS) techniques. Dr. Delaney has training in as well as extensive experience performing advanced arthroscopic surgical techniques including Anterior Cruciate Ligament (ACL) repair, meniscus transplant, arthroscopic rotator cuff repair and cartilage replacement procedures. He serves as team physician and orthopedic consultant to several area high schools, semi pro and club sports teams.

Patients visiting Dr. Messinger can receive a full range of medical services. Her areas of professional interest include breastfeeding, child development, international adoption, and common behavioral problems. In addition to her practice, Dr. Messinger founded the Long Island College Hospital chapter of the Reach Out and Read national advocacy program.

name: Dr. John Kim
og:description: Dr. John Kim is an allergist and immunologist treating patients in Medford, New Jersey, and the surrounding communities. He holds dual board certifications from the American Board of Allergy and Immunology and Internal Medicine. Dr. Kim is also a member of professional organizations including the American College of Allergy, Asthma, and Immunology and the American Academy of Allergy, Asthma, and Immunology. He is the recipient of numerous civilian and military awards to include South Jersey Top Doc, US Army Meritorious Service Medal, and numerous Patients' Choice Award. He pursued his medical degree at the Chicago Medical School and then continued his medical education at Tripler Army Medical Center in Hawaii. After serving as a physician in the US Medical Corps, he then went on to complete fellowship training in allergy and immunology at the North Shore-Long Island Jewish Medical Center and Cohen Children's Medical Center of New York.  Patients visiting Dr. Kim can receive comprehensive treatment for a full range of allergy and immune issues. He provides allergy skin testing, rhinoscopy, and lung function testing, as well as diagnostic testing for eczema and skin rashes, chronic cough, wheezing, nasal congestion and food allergies.

Dr Trimberger is great.  He takes time to listen, diagnose and discuss options. He explains things well and answers my questions thoughtfully. After my visits, I feel well tended to and like I am a whole person and not just a list of symptoms or a body part that needs repair. ,Dr Trimberger is very knowledgeable and professional.  He explained my options for my shoulder injury and the potential outcomes for each choice.,He's very easy to talk to and ask questions of.  I don't feel like he's rushing me.  He is very good about answering questions and offering options.  I saw him several years ago for my shoulder and was happy to be able to see him regarding my hip.,Dr Trimberger was friendly, efficient, and thorough. I left feeling confident about the scope of my diagnosis and the plan towards recovery. The scheduling and payment process is really convenient, much of it online. The entire staff was helpful and friendly.,Dr. Trimberger listened thoughtfully, and performed a thorough exam.  He explained his diagnosis and the next steps clearly.  ,Friendly, well-informed, good listener and great at giving options!,perfect,I really enjoy Dr. Trimberger's casual and easily understood explanations. He's straight forward, helpful, and efficient. His assistant is easy going and calm and makes for a very comfortable appointment, no stress! I know with his help my injury is going to get better!,Overall, a very good experience!  I really liked the staff as well as the Dr.  Everyone was friendly and helpful.  Dr Trimberger took the time to listen to my concerns and addressed them in a thoughtful manner.,It was well worth the visit.  He provided an overall view of what I had.  Used sound and the screen to show me the injury.  Did an x-ray to eliminate fracture possibility.  He did'nt go into deep detail about muscle fiber tears and micro tears and what happens down in the deep part of this injury.  But it was a very good ballpark analysis of the injury.  I don't think it does that much good to go that specific in detail   about any injury, just the basics of what it is and he did that.  He suggested more land resistance and that was a good thought and I'll follow through.  He did a thorough job and it was worth every minute.,Dan was great -  very informative and open .  Made great suggestions and rescheduled with another doctor when different, more achieving solution was possible.  Felt very ccomfortable with Dan
,very good,It was great, He asked and answered questions. I've never been to a better doctor!,Very good at analyzing situation with daughters knee and offering good options.,He is very thorough and knows his stuff.,thorough, friendly,He is extremely knowledgeable and is very easy to speak with. I am planning on going back to this clinic in the future.,I thought he was great and very professional.  He was very thorough and I left feeling like I had a solid plan to improve and fix my injury.  I would definitely go back to see him again.,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

name: Dr. Diana Gill
og:description: Please do not schedule appointments more than 6 months ahead of time with this practice.  Dr. Gill was born and raised in Germany. She received her medical degree from Hannover Medical School in Hannover, Germany. Afterwards, she completed her USMLE and ECFMG certifications and moved to the United States to marry her husband Mike. She completed her OB/GYN residency at Illinois Masonic Medical Center in Chicago before she moved to Oregon to join Gresham Women’s Healthcare in April 2009. Dr. Diana Gill is a Board Certified, General OB/ GYN with a special interest in minimally invasive gynecological surgery and basic workup and treatment for patients with infertility. She is dedicated to provide personal and individualized care to her patients. Dr. Gill speaks fluent German and English. Outside of work, she enjoys running, hiking, skiing, and exploring the Pacific North West with her family.

name: Dr. Brian Gottesman
og:description: Dr. Brian Gottesman is an OB-GYN treating patients in Manahawkin, New Jersey, and the surrounding communities. His primary goal as a practitioner is to ensure that each of his patients receives the highest standard of medical care. He holds certification from the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology. Dr. Gottesman is also a member of the American Congress of Obstetricians and Gynecologists. For his undergraduate degree, Dr. Gottesman attended the State University of New York at Stony Brook. He pursued his medical degree at the State University of New York Health Science Center at Brooklyn. Dr. Gottesman continued his medical education at the North Shore University Hospital. Here, he completed an internship program and received his residency training in obstetrics and gynecology. Patients visiting Dr. Gottesman can receive a full range of obstetric and gynecological services. He provides Pap smear procedures, annual gynecological examinations, and general consultations. In addition to his practice Dr. Gottesman has presented research on triplet pregnancies.

name: Dr. Michael J. Levine
og:description: Dr. Michael Levine is a cardiologist who treats patients in Lake Success, New York, and its neighboring areas. He is certified by the American Board of Internal Medicine in both Internal Medicine and Cardiovascular Diseases, National Board of Echocardiography, Certification Board of Nuclear Cardiology, and he is a Registered Physician in Vascular Interpretation. Upon receiving his medical education at Northwestern University – Feinberg School of Medicine, Dr. Levine completed an internal medicine residency at New York Presbyterian Hospital/Weill Cornell Medical Center. He also completed fellowship programs at Beth Israel Medical Center in clinical cardiac electrophysiology and cardiovascular diseases.  Professional experience for Dr. Levine includes his current position as attending physician at NYU Langone Long Island Cardiac Care. He has also been published in several journals and was awarded the 2008 David B. Skinner Award at NYPH/Cornell in Internal Medicine.

name: Dr. Jennifer Claves
og:description: If you need an annual physical, please call the office directly at (610) 325-0309. We want to be sure the doctor has enough time meet your wellness needs! Jennifer Claves is a vibrant, friendly internist providing care to her patients from the Main Line Health Center in Broomall, PA. Dr. Claves is Board certified in internal medicine. She began her medical education at the Pennsylvania State University College of Medicine, and then completed her residency at Thomas Jefferson University Hospital. Her areas of clinical interest are in geriatrics and women’s health. Dr. Claves is affiliated at the Lankenau Medical Center, Bryn Mawr Hospital, Paoli Hospital, and Riddle Hospital. She is a member of the American College of Physicians and the Pennsylvania Medical Society.  Dr. Claves provides swift, effective care to her patients. She provides illness consultations in less than an hour. She is continuously inputting effort into her medical education, working to expand her knowledge and the knowledge of others through publishing her research. In 2002, Dr. Claves collaborated on a research endeavor that examined the barriers to confronting medical errors. Additionally, Dr. Claves presented research evaluating carotid stenosis through CT angiography.  Dr. Claves was named 2011’s Top Doctor by Internal Medicine Main Line Today magazine.

name: Dr. Rye Estepp
og:description: Rye Estepp is a diligent and detail-oriented OB-GYN providing excellent medical care to her patients in Bartlett, TN. Born in Massachusetts, Dr. Estepp received her medical education in West Virginia at the Marshall University School of Medicine before completing her residency in obstetrics and gynecology at the University of Tennessee. Dr. Estepp has been practicing at the Mid-South OB-GYN Women’s Care Center of Memphis since 2010.  Dr. Estepp serves as clinical faculty at the University of Tennessee with the department of obstetrics and gynecology. She is affiliated with the Methodist Germantown Hospital and the Baptist Memorial and Baptist Women’s hospitals. Dr. Estepp is a member of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists, and the American Medical Association. In 2009, Dr. Estepp completed research examining neoadjuvant chemotherapy for the treatment of advanced stage ovarian cancer.

name: Dr. Mena Luangjamekorn
og:description: Dr. Mena M. Luangjamekorn, M.D. is a qualified primary care physician. She is affiliated with BJC Medical Group and Alton Memorial Hospital in Alton, IL. Dr. Luangjamekorn earned her B.A. in Biology from the University of Missouri, Kansas City in 1996. She finished her M.D. at the same institution in 2000. In 2003, Dr. Luangjamekorn finished her Family Practice Residency at Michigan State University in Flint, MI. Dr. Luangjamekorn spent significant time providing gynecological, pediatric, adult, and geriatric outpatient primary care at McLaren Medical Management. She was active in her community providing preventative education to children and mothers. She speaks English as a first language, as well as Thai, Spanish, and Mandarin. Dr. Luangjamekorn is dedicated to providing consistently exceptional healthcare and education. She finds incredible satisfaction in serving her patients.

professional_statement: Dr. Tseday Sirak is board certified in internal medicine, cardiovascular disease, nuclear cardiology, and echocardiography. Her areas of interest include treatment of heart failure, valvular heart disease, cardiac imaging, and congenital heart diseases. She completed her internal medicine residency at Albert Einstein College of Medicine, as well as a fellowship in Cardiovascular Medicine at St. Luke’s-Roosevelt Hospital Center. Dr. Sirak also holds a Master of Public Health degree in Epidemiology. She is an active volunteer in her community, and provides pro bono medical services at a local free clinic on a weekly basis. In 2013, Dr. Sirak was named a Rising Star Doctor by the Washington Post’s Super Doctors feature. In 2016, she was awarded Northern Virginia's Top Doctor award.

review_text:
My husband just saw Dr. Shock and I am so thrilled! My husband was told by another Doctor "Oh this is genetic, you'll just have to deal with the pain." Needless to say we were less than impressed with that diagnosis. However, Dr. Shock was the exact opposite. He took the time to explain my husband's diagnosis, discuss options, and he even took time to look through our insurance and let us know our options along with pricing. We were happy to do whatever we needed to get my husband better, but I am glad that he was considerate enough to take a financial situation into account. Overall I would highly recommend Dr. Shock to anyone in need of a foot checkup.  ,I took my active 12 yr old son to see Dr. Shock for chronic heel pain.  Dr Shock provided two avenues for treatment and even addressed potential financial burdens due to insurance limitations/coverage.  I appreciated that awareness, which was a compliment to his educational presentation of the problem and prognosis based on his extensive experience in treating athletes.,I liked his approach to the problem. He got to the point and gave me options. ,Great Doctor!  ,Very good. ,Dr. Shock was very professional and also very thorough.  I went to him for a 2nd opinion and was very pleased to have found a great doctor. ,Dr Shock saw us immediately and took care of our ingrown toenail problem within minutes.  He has a great, funny bedside manner and made the numbing shot practically painless.  We are so glad we drove to see Dr Shock.,Dr. Shock had already read my note I submitted online when I made the appointment, and was ready to discuss the issue when I showed up. He clearly communicated the options for treatment with me, and explained his recommendation.  I've seen him a couple of times now, and greatly appreciate his preparation and his treatment of my injury (which is now all better)!,Motivated to find a way to eliminate the problem.
Willing to do what it takes to make sure all possible treatments are understood and risk/benifits of all.,Dr. Ryan Shock gave me a good experience. Went in because of an old sports injury. He was very knowledgeable and gentle with checking to find the bad area. It was a pleasure to listen to him explain the details so I could understand. Being that he is down to earth with a good sense of humor. I will definitely recommend him to anyone that needs their feet looked over and evaluated.,Very friendly and was very informative. My feet felt better before I left!,very good,professional,caring and sincere !,Dr. Shock is the best foot doctor in Austin. ,He knows his stuff. I like him- he gets straight down to business!,He listened thoughtfully to my description of my running injury. Then, his comments about treatment were tailored precisely to my condition. He began treatment immediately. Gave me specific instruction on things to do at home, and left me some awesome shoe inserts that I wore the rest of the day without any pain at all. Yay!,Dr. Shock was quick to find the problem and helped me get back to running that day.,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

og:description: We want to be sure the doctor has enough time meet your wellness needs! Carol Henwood-Dahda is a family physician offering excellent care in Limerick. PA. Dr. Henwood is certified by the American Osteopathic Board of Family Physicians and is affiliated with Paoli Hospital.  Dr. Henwood received her medical degree from the Philadelphia College of Osteopathic Medicine. She furthered her postdoctoral education by completing a residency in Family Practice at Philadelphia College of Osteopathic Medicine as well. She is active in several professional memberships including the Pennsylvania Osteopathic Family Physicians Society, the Pennsylvania Osteopathic Medical Association, the American Osteopathic Association, and the American College of Osteopathic Family Physicians, where she received a Distinguished Fellowship Award in 2011, and an Inaugural Outstanding Female Leader Award in 2012.  Dr. Henwood may be visited for a plethora of reasons; her consultations last approximately 45 minutes.
