I think she's an awesome doctor who cares greatly for her patients ,I am very encouraged by Dr Henwood...she was very reassuring and I was extremely comfortable with her.,I love going to this office. My appt. was 12:40 and I was out by 1:05. I did not feel that I was rushed through, Dr Henwood is very knowledgeable and cares about your problems and wants to help you She is a wonderful doctor and I strongly recommend her. ,Open and thorough, easy to talk to about concerns. A doctor that actually cares about the patient. Very rare find!!!! ,Got right in...
everyone pleasant and I have seen the Dr and the PA. I would recommend both. Getting in on a Friday afternoon was perfect for me as well,Dr. Henwood is the best! She truly cares about my health and takes the time to answer my questions. ,Dr Henwood is thorough.She addressed all my questions and concerns. Professional yet personal. Great staff.


 ,It was so nice to have a doctor listen to me and address all my concerns,Very pleasurable experience. The entire office staff and doctors were exceptional.,I would not want to go to any other doctor. The office staff is always friendly and courteous. Dr. Henwood is truly caring and has been our family's doctor for many years.,I was please with the attention and concern for my health needs, given from the provider,Caring, professional, and very competent.,Dr. Henwood and her office staff are fantastic!  Not only are they friendly and knowledgable, but they are efficient and on top of things.  My refills are processed immediately, phone calls are returned on a timely basis and I never have to wait long in the waiting room or examining room.  Their insurance person does as much of the legwork as possible for you.  Dr. Henwood and her staff are a breath of fresh air!,Dr. Henwood really listened and spent time going over all of my concerns. I would definitely recommend her to others. ,Great visit. I don't leave a lot of reviews, but this one was earned. I almost hate recommending them in case they get too popular and busy!

I've recently had a few poor experiences with doctors, when I saw the reviews left for Dr. Henwood I decided to give her a try despite being an hour drive from the practice. Totally worth it. She (and the whole staff) was easy to talk to, listened, and tried to explain things much better than my previous doctors. They were not rushing around, treating you like another appointment to get through. I have a LOT of anxiety about new places and new people, especially doctors where you have to talk about more personal matters, but they did a really great job from the beginning to the end of the whole appointment. I will continue to make the hour long hike to see them over the seeing the doctors again near me.,I like how nice Dr. Henwood is, but still at the same time very much on point, very straightforward and to the point.  She gave a brief explanation of what she was doing and why or how it correlated to something else and then did it.  She got her point across on an even keeled manner.  I like that she is not too high energy and not too much of a warm drink of water; she is perfect balance.  Things seem to get done immediately.,This is my 1st visit with Dr Henwood. She listens well and is thorough. Happy to find her. ,Wonderful visit!!!,Thorough, listens well, informative, enthused, and caring, as always.  Dr. Henwood-Dahdah is the best.  ,Excellent service. I found the staff very helpful, professional and friendly.  Dr.Henwood-Dahdah was informative, professional AND intrested in hearing what I had to say (she looks at you when I spoke!). She takes great care of my entire family.  Her staff is always helpful and extremely  professional.  I would highly recommend Dr. Henwood to anyone looking for a family doctor.,Very professional & very thorough.   Staff friendly and professional. She is just awesome!,Great experience....wonderful professional doctor and staff!,Dr. Henwood changed my life. She is so compassionate, and truly listens. review_text:
He is the best!!!!!,Excellent service was my first visit will continue to visit on a future basis 
,Everyone was super friendly and courteous. The office was impeccably clean. The wait time was not long at all. By far, the best doctor's office I've ever been to! And very convenient to my workplace so that's definitely another huge plus,Dr. Gohar was very friendly and made me feel very comfortable. His entire team was quick and efficient - highly recommend! ,Truly and honestly one of the greatest decisions I have ever made was to give this place a shot. I was in a dire search to find a gynecologist due to some personal issues (mind you, it's my first time ever going to an OB-GYN, so I had no prior experience.) I found this place through a co-worker who raved about her FABULOUS experience and how much she loved this place, and so I then gave it a shot. Why not!

I was a few minutes late because you have to take the Q23 bus towards Elmhurst, but I walked in and the ambiance was breath taking. SO NOT your typical mediocre/ehh clinics that are usually within Queens. Walking into this place was like walking into a spa-like entrance, very calm, very high tech, very NYC vibe. The receptionists was nice and situated me in right away. The bathroom, omg, it was so high tech with their Japanese toilet with heated seat lol. (can you tell I was just in complete awe? lol) Anyway, the ambiance, the amazing assistance, and the high tech machines are just a bonus added to THE amazing doctor Gohar. He was calm, straightforward, very detailed, and NON-judgmental! Everything that I was looking for in a gynecologist. He is a total opposite of what I had experienced with previous ob-gyns. Dr. Gohar does not push anything to you that you don't need or don't want to do, like I said, he is not judgmental at all. He lets YOU be in control and just guides you, that's what I prefer with my doctors. The wait took quite a long time due to the fact that the ultra sound technician was sick and so the doctor had to do it himself but I didn't mind because they check in on you and let's you be aware of the progress. Also the assistance were funny, they had me laughing! Give this place a shot, you won't regret it! 

,Dr. Gohar is very professional and makes you feel extremely comfortable. He explains everything thoroughly, so you can be sure to understand all of your options. The office is also one of the nicest offices I've ever been to--very clean and modern.,Dr. Gohar is very empathetic, caring and nurturing - things that are incredibly necessary in a doctor, specially in this area of expertise. ,Very informative and caring. Definitely concerned about patient's care above anything else.,At first I was a bit nervous about having a male doctor checking me but Dr. Gohar made me feel comfortable. He is a very thorough doctor and takes the time to learn about his patients. The staff there are pretty awesome. All very nice and respectable and make you feel more than comfortable while you are there! Also the office is very nice. Overall I had a good experience and I will be going back. ,The entire staff was very welcoming and friendly. They really take their time with you. Dr. Gohar was extremely comforting and really listened to me. I was not sure if switching from my doctor after 6 years was the right thing to do but after my visit I am 100% sure that I am making the right decision. I am very happy with Dr. Gohar and the the entire staff!,He's an amazing doctor ! He makes me feel
Comfortable!,The doctor and staff were extremely kind, professional, and thorough! I've been looking for a great GYN for a while now and I think I finally found one. ,the office is very comfortable and pleasing. The administrative assistant, medical assistants and Doctor were all so welcoming and attentive. The hours are great. Had such a pleasant experience! The doctor did not rush and answered all my questions, really showed he cared. Can't say enough nice things. I found my new gynecologist ,I thought the visit to Mr. Gohar office was a very nice experience,  the staff is amazingly wonderful all great things to say about them , all of them .. The doctor was very professional , explained everything thoroughly,  I left the office glad that I found my new gynecologist .  ,I have to say that this is by far the best experience I have had to date. The staff was extremely professional and kind, I was attended to within minutes, the office was airy and clean, the equipment is clean and up to par with the latest technology, and most importantly I felt so comfortable with the entire visit. I look forward to many visits with Dr. Gohar. He is so nice and is very informative throughout the entire checkup. I honestly don't have one complaint which is really rare these days.,I was so impressed by my experience. Dr Gohar is now officially my ob/gyn,Very professional.,I have nothing but amazing things to say about Dr Gohar and his office staff. From the front desk receptionist whom was so nice and sweet, to the nurses and ultra sound techs, they were ALL sweet and made me feel very comfortable. I am not a fan of male ob-gyn but that have changed upon meeting Dr Gohar, his bedside manner is amazing, he spoke to me and my partner very warmly and made us feel very comfortable. he went over my full medical history in great detail, never did I feel rushed. He was even nice enough to translate to my partner when he didn't fully understand everything. A+ for that. This is an amazing Dr and am so glad that I found him. An office is nothing without the front desk, and the medical assistants etc, and they all went above and beyond. Amazing staff. Thank you everyone for making me feel comfortable. Bejos,first time visit for pregnancy check up.. He made us feel so comfortable. Everything was smooth, the office is super clean, everyone so far i met is very pleasant. I will definitely be coming here throughout the whole process! ,Amazing attentive Doctor ,Every employee was friendly and respectful! I choose the correct practice!!!,Dr. Gohar and his staff are amazing!!! He listened and did not rush. I'm so happy that he's my new gynecologist. ,Dr. Gohar is a true professional. This is my first pregnancy and from the moment he walked into the examination room I felt very comfortable with him. He is friendly, has excellent bedside manner, is very thorough in his examination, and takes the time to sit with you and  go over everything you need to know and answer questions.   He does not rush. The office is very clean and it is also very sleek and modern.  The nurses were all very friendly and helpful. The office manager actually took the time to review my insurance plan the day that I booked my first appointment and called to follow up with me to confirm that they accepted my insurance and laid out all the details with my deductible and what each visit would cost me until my deductible was met. I've actually never had any doctor experience that was this transparent, and it was a breath of fresh air. I'm going to be spending a lot of time with Dr. Gohar and his staff in the next few months, and I know I made the right decision. I would highly recommend them. ,Dr. Gohar is a one of a kind!  He is extremely caring and attentive!  The office staff is also superb.  I delivered my son with him and I am extremely grateful for his support and expertise.  Dr. Gohar is one of those doctors that you rarely find nowadays!  Highly recommended!,Staff was very nice, everyone explained everything thoroughly and made me feel comfortable, place was very clean, didn't have to wait at all, and the doctor was great! He was extremely thorough, asked questions to find out specific things, and went over everything with me! Great place! Would recommend to anyone. ,My first visit to Dr. G- awesome experience- friendly n warm staff . Minimal wait time n Dr. G was great,Great patient care. Immaculate office. 
No wait. Loved it. ,It was my first appointment and so far I am satisfied with the Doctor's opinion.,Best facility I've been to, staff was absolutely amazing and knowledgeable . Dr. Gohar was great took his time to answer all my questions very professional.  You know when someone is good at what they do it shows,  everyone at this office is the BEST ., ,I was extremely inpressed by the quality if care i received. Dr Gohar has convient hours, and everything you need is already on hand at his office. His staff is polite and kind. I am the type to do background research before going to the doctor. He is the only doctor i have ever had that respected my intelligence and listened to what i thought and wanted. He gave good information without condescending or dumbing things down. His approach made what could have been an uncomfortable appointment very easy. Highly, highly recommend.,Absolutely amazing!!!! I usually don't comment on these rating reviews. But, anyone that needs a GYN doctor Here in queens well I'll say NYC area definitely has to experience what I experienced today.. Let me start by saying as u walk in, the office is totally clean and beautifully decor. As well as a pleasant place, while waiting and filling out all your paper work u can serve yourself some fresh cut strawberry & lime water (delish) nice and chilled... Oh wait and can I tell you ladies the bathroom has a heated toilet :D yes I said HEATed TOILET SEAT!!! I got there half hour prior to my appointment time and I was seen right after I finished all my paperwork... The staff starting from the receptionist to the nurse was just PERFECT. Professional to the T. And, last but not least Dr. GOHAR makes u feel so comfortable like if you knew him for years. I can't not complain of my first visit.. Definitely looking forward to my new GYN doctor experience... ,Great first visit. Beautiful, clean office, and very professional, kind doctor. Explained everything I wanted to know. ,I found Dr Gohar through a reference and he turned out not only an excellent doctor but a good care giver. He is very through in his treatment and dont want to leave anything for a chance. my wifes delivery was smooth and without any hiccups. ,I was skeptical at first about having a male gynecologist, but Dr. Gohar is probably the most amazing gynecologist in the queens area. He was very easy to talk to and very understanding about my concerns. My visit went so well that I can definitely say I will be going back to him. Not to mention, he is very personable and is very easy on the eyes surprisingly a plus! ,The entire staff was friendly and courteous. Very modern office and equipment. Dr has great bedside manner and is very knowledgeable. Did not feel rushed at all, all of our questions were answered willingly. Parking is not so great in the area, that's the only downside, but we managed to find parking close by.,This is by far the best OBGYN office I have ever used.  The staff is polite and efficient.  I've been coming for a long time and Dr. Soukkary used to be my doctor.  Dr. Gohar is just as phenomenal - he always takes time to listen to my concerns, and takes strides to really involve me in my care.  I had been trying to concieve for a while, and just got pregnant with his help!!  If you also have fertility issues, please consider Dr. Gohar.  He is very knowledgeable, very organized and very thorough. ,By far the best Doctor that i have seen in a long time. We need more doctors like that, very understanding takes his time with you, doesn't make you feel just like another number. ,Dr. Gohar made me feel very comfortable. His bedside manner was excellent, very professional. I'm so happy I found such a great gynecologist. The staff was great and very friendly as well. From start to finish my appointment was very pleasant. I would definitely recommend Dr. Gohar. ,I came across Dr. Gohar after a friend of mine delivered with him and couldn't stop raving about him.   She would always say how lucky she felt with him.  After having a pretty brash and abrasive doc with my last pregnancy, I now see the difference.  My hubby and I are still trying to get pregnant again but after doing my annual with Dr. Gohar, I have no doubt who I'm doing it with.  He is sooo calm and knowledgeable.  There is the generic "customer service" you get at the big hospitals and clinics and then there is the truly truly personalized care that you get with Dr. Gohar! He not only calls you with any abnormal results but also makes it a point to email you normal labs so you don't have to worry!  That he delivers at one of the best rated hospitals in NY (Mt. Sinai Roosevelt) for delivering babies is like the final cherry on top!,Great doctor, easy to talk to, really cared and listened. Would recommend to anyone who is looking for a doctor one the upper east side or in forest hills! ,Dr Gohar was very easy to talk to about a difficult situation and he made me feel at ease the whole time. He discussed a range of options with me and allowed me to choose the next step. I would highly recommend Dr Gohar.,One of the kindest and most thoughtful doctors I've ever seen in my life!,Very profession and very thorough. Listened to all of my concerns. Explained every step of the exam in detail and was very open for questions. ,What a find! I booked with Dr. Gohar after a friend told me what a great surgeon he was known to be.  I found his bedside manner to be incredible as well! I also found him to be very warm, patient and genuine, I was sold immediately and he didn’t disappoint.  His office seems to really make it a point to book things in a way so that patients don’t have to wait long.  I think I found the best ob/gyn in the city!  ,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

review_text:
He is the best!!!!!,Excellent service was my first visit will continue to visit on a future basis 
,Everyone was super friendly and courteous. The office was impeccably clean. The wait time was not long at all. By far, the best doctor's office I've ever been to! And very convenient to my workplace so that's definitely another huge plus,Dr. Gohar was very friendly and made me feel very comfortable. His entire team was quick and efficient - highly recommend! ,Truly and honestly one of the greatest decisions I have ever made was to give this place a shot. I was in a dire search to find a gynecologist due to some personal issues (mind you, it's my first time ever going to an OB-GYN, so I had no prior experience.) I found this place through a co-worker who raved about her FABULOUS experience and how much she loved this place, and so I then gave it a shot. Why not!

I was a few minutes late because you have to take the Q23 bus towards Elmhurst, but I walked in and the ambiance was breath taking. SO NOT your typical mediocre/ehh clinics that are usually within Queens. Walking into this place was like walking into a spa-like entrance, very calm, very high tech, very NYC vibe. The receptionists was nice and situated me in right away. The bathroom, omg, it was so high tech with their Japanese toilet with heated seat lol. (can you tell I was just in complete awe? lol) Anyway, the ambiance, the amazing assistance, and the high tech machines are just a bonus added to THE amazing doctor Gohar. He was calm, straightforward, very detailed, and NON-judgmental! Everything that I was looking for in a gynecologist. He is a total opposite of what I had experienced with previous ob-gyns. Dr. Gohar does not push anything to you that you don't need or don't want to do, like I said, he is not judgmental at all. He lets YOU be in control and just guides you, that's what I prefer with my doctors. The wait took quite a long time due to the fact that the ultra sound technician was sick and so the doctor had to do it himself but I didn't mind because they check in on you and let's you be aware of the progress. Also the assistance were funny, they had me laughing! Give this place a shot, you won't regret it! 

,Dr. Gohar is very professional and makes you feel extremely comfortable. He explains everything thoroughly, so you can be sure to understand all of your options. The office is also one of the nicest offices I've ever been to--very clean and modern.,Dr. Gohar is very empathetic, caring and nurturing - things that are incredibly necessary in a doctor, specially in this area of expertise. ,Very informative and caring. Definitely concerned about patient's care above anything else.,At first I was a bit nervous about having a male doctor checking me but Dr. Gohar made me feel comfortable. He is a very thorough doctor and takes the time to learn about his patients. The staff there are pretty awesome. All very nice and respectable and make you feel more than comfortable while you are there! Also the office is very nice. Overall I had a good experience and I will be going back. ,The entire staff was very welcoming and friendly. They really take their time with you. Dr. Gohar was extremely comforting and really listened to me. I was not sure if switching from my doctor after 6 years was the right thing to do but after my visit I am 100% sure that I am making the right decision. I am very happy with Dr. Gohar and the the entire staff!,He's an amazing doctor ! He makes me feel
Comfortable!,The doctor and staff were extremely kind, professional, and thorough! I've been looking for a great GYN for a while now and I think I finally found one. ,the office is very comfortable and pleasing. The administrative assistant, medical assistants and Doctor were all so welcoming and attentive. The hours are great. Had such a pleasant experience! The doctor did not rush and answered all my questions, really showed he cared. Can't say enough nice things. I found my new gynecologist ,I thought the visit to Mr. Gohar office was a very nice experience,  the staff is amazingly wonderful all great things to say about them , all of them .. The doctor was very professional , explained everything thoroughly,  I left the office glad that I found my new gynecologist .  ,I have to say that this is by far the best experience I have had to date. The staff was extremely professional and kind, I was attended to within minutes, the office was airy and clean, the equipment is clean and up to par with the latest technology, and most importantly I felt so comfortable with the entire visit. I look forward to many visits with Dr. Gohar. He is so nice and is very informative throughout the entire checkup. I honestly don't have one complaint which is really rare these days.,I was so impressed by my experience. Dr Gohar is now officially my ob/gyn,Very professional.,I have nothing but amazing things to say about Dr Gohar and his office staff. From the front desk receptionist whom was so nice and sweet, to the nurses and ultra sound techs, they were ALL sweet and made me feel very comfortable. I am not a fan of male ob-gyn but that have changed upon meeting Dr Gohar, his bedside manner is amazing, he spoke to me and my partner very warmly and made us feel very comfortable. he went over my full medical history in great detail, never did I feel rushed. He was even nice enough to translate to my partner when he didn't fully understand everything. A+ for that. This is an amazing Dr and am so glad that I found him. An office is nothing without the front desk, and the medical assistants etc, and they all went above and beyond. Amazing staff. Thank you everyone for making me feel comfortable. Bejos,first time visit for pregnancy check up.. He made us feel so comfortable. Everything was smooth, the office is super clean, everyone so far i met is very pleasant. I will definitely be coming here throughout the whole process! ,Amazing attentive Doctor ,Every employee was friendly and respectful! I choose the correct practice!!!,Dr. Gohar and his staff are amazing!!! He listened and did not rush. I'm so happy that he's my new gynecologist. ,Dr. Gohar is a true professional. This is my first pregnancy and from the moment he walked into the examination room I felt very comfortable with him. He is friendly, has excellent bedside manner, is very thorough in his examination, and takes the time to sit with you and  go over everything you need to know and answer questions.   He does not rush. The office is very clean and it is also very sleek and modern.  The nurses were all very friendly and helpful. The office manager actually took the time to review my insurance plan the day that I booked my first appointment and called to follow up with me to confirm that they accepted my insurance and laid out all the details with my deductible and what each visit would cost me until my deductible was met. I've actually never had any doctor experience that was this transparent, and it was a breath of fresh air. I'm going to be spending a lot of time with Dr. Gohar and his staff in the next few months, and I know I made the right decision. I would highly recommend them. ,Dr. Gohar is a one of a kind!  He is extremely caring and attentive!  The office staff is also superb.  I delivered my son with him and I am extremely grateful for his support and expertise.  Dr. Gohar is one of those doctors that you rarely find nowadays!  Highly recommended!,Staff was very nice, everyone explained everything thoroughly and made me feel comfortable, place was very clean, didn't have to wait at all, and the doctor was great! He was extremely thorough, asked questions to find out specific things, and went over everything with me! Great place! Would recommend to anyone. ,My first visit to Dr. G- awesome experience- friendly n warm staff . Minimal wait time n Dr. G was great,Great patient care. Immaculate office. 
No wait. Loved it. ,It was my first appointment and so far I am satisfied with the Doctor's opinion.,Best facility I've been to, staff was absolutely amazing and knowledgeable . Dr. Gohar was great took his time to answer all my questions very professional.  You know when someone is good at what they do it shows,  everyone at this office is the BEST ., ,I was extremely inpressed by the quality if care i received. Dr Gohar has convient hours, and everything you need is already on hand at his office. His staff is polite and kind. I am the type to do background research before going to the doctor. He is the only doctor i have ever had that respected my intelligence and listened to what i thought and wanted. He gave good information without condescending or dumbing things down. His approach made what could have been an uncomfortable appointment very easy. Highly, highly recommend.,Absolutely amazing!!!! I usually don't comment on these rating reviews. But, anyone that needs a GYN doctor Here in queens well I'll say NYC area definitely has to experience what I experienced today.. Let me start by saying as u walk in, the office is totally clean and beautifully decor. As well as a pleasant place, while waiting and filling out all your paper work u can serve yourself some fresh cut strawberry & lime water (delish) nice and chilled... Oh wait and can I tell you ladies the bathroom has a heated toilet :D yes I said HEATed TOILET SEAT!!! I got there half hour prior to my appointment time and I was seen right after I finished all my paperwork... The staff starting from the receptionist to the nurse was just PERFECT. Professional to the T. And, last but not least Dr. GOHAR makes u feel so comfortable like if you knew him for years. I can't not complain of my first visit.. Definitely looking forward to my new GYN doctor experience... ,Great first visit. Beautiful, clean office, and very professional, kind doctor. Explained everything I wanted to know. ,I found Dr Gohar through a reference and he turned out not only an excellent doctor but a good care giver. He is very through in his treatment and dont want to leave anything for a chance. my wifes delivery was smooth and without any hiccups. ,I was skeptical at first about having a male gynecologist, but Dr. Gohar is probably the most amazing gynecologist in the queens area. He was very easy to talk to and very understanding about my concerns. My visit went so well that I can definitely say I will be going back to him. Not to mention, he is very personable and is very easy on the eyes surprisingly a plus! ,The entire staff was friendly and courteous. Very modern office and equipment. Dr has great bedside manner and is very knowledgeable. Did not feel rushed at all, all of our questions were answered willingly. Parking is not so great in the area, that's the only downside, but we managed to find parking close by.,This is by far the best OBGYN office I have ever used.  The staff is polite and efficient.  I've been coming for a long time and Dr. Soukkary used to be my doctor.  Dr. Gohar is just as phenomenal - he always takes time to listen to my concerns, and takes strides to really involve me in my care.  I had been trying to concieve for a while, and just got pregnant with his help!!  If you also have fertility issues, please consider Dr. Gohar.  He is very knowledgeable, very organized and very thorough. ,By far the best Doctor that i have seen in a long time. We need more doctors like that, very understanding takes his time with you, doesn't make you feel just like another number. ,Dr. Gohar made me feel very comfortable. His bedside manner was excellent, very professional. I'm so happy I found such a great gynecologist. The staff was great and very friendly as well. From start to finish my appointment was very pleasant. I would definitely recommend Dr. Gohar. ,I came across Dr. Gohar after a friend of mine delivered with him and couldn't stop raving about him.   She would always say how lucky she felt with him.  After having a pretty brash and abrasive doc with my last pregnancy, I now see the difference.  My hubby and I are still trying to get pregnant again but after doing my annual with Dr. Gohar, I have no doubt who I'm doing it with.  He is sooo calm and knowledgeable.  There is the generic "customer service" you get at the big hospitals and clinics and then there is the truly truly personalized care that you get with Dr. Gohar! He not only calls you with any abnormal results but also makes it a point to email you normal labs so you don't have to worry!  That he delivers at one of the best rated hospitals in NY (Mt. Sinai Roosevelt) for delivering babies is like the final cherry on top!,Great doctor, easy to talk to, really cared and listened. Would recommend to anyone who is looking for a doctor one the upper east side or in forest hills! ,Dr Gohar was very easy to talk to about a difficult situation and he made me feel at ease the whole time. He discussed a range of options with me and allowed me to choose the next step. I would highly recommend Dr Gohar.,One of the kindest and most thoughtful doctors I've ever seen in my life!,Very profession and very thorough. Listened to all of my concerns. Explained every step of the exam in detail and was very open for questions. ,What a find! I booked with Dr. Gohar after a friend told me what a great surgeon he was known to be.  I found his bedside manner to be incredible as well! I also found him to be very warm, patient and genuine, I was sold immediately and he didn’t disappoint.  His office seems to really make it a point to book things in a way so that patients don’t have to wait long.  I think I found the best ob/gyn in the city!  ,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

name: Dr. Daren Kest
og:description: Daren Kest is a friendly and insightful Ear, Nose, and Throat doctor and Head and Neck Surgeon assisting his patients in Florissant, MO. Dr. Kest is certified by the American Osteopathic Board of Otolaryngology – Head and Neck Surgery. He is a member of the American Osteopathic Association and the American Academy of Otolaryngology – Head and Neck Surgery. He is currently affiliated with the Christian Hospital in St. Louis. Dr. Kest attended the Oakland University to earn his bachelor’s degree, and then Michigan State University College of Osteopathic Medicine for his medical degree. He then completed an internship at St. Johns Oakland General Hospital in Madison Heights, MI, followed by two residencies in General Surgery and then Otolaryngology - Facial Plastic Surgery at POH Medical Center on Michigan State University Wide Campus. Finally, Dr. Kest completed a fellowship at Head & Neck Surgery Associates, P.C. at Indiana University. Dr. Kest is consistently augmenting his knowledge and work through published research as well as participation in classes and conferences nationwide.

name: Dr. Ralph Vetters
og:description: Dr. Vetters Focuses on seeing patients from 12-29 years old.  Dr. Vetters is the Medical Director of the Sidney Borum Jr. Health Center, a program of Fenway Health. He is from Texas and Missouri and graduated from Harvard College in 1985. His first career was as a union organizer in New England for workers in higher education and the public sector. In 1998 he went back to school and graduated from the Harvard Medical School in 2003 after also getting his masters in public health at the Harvard School of Public Health in maternal and child health. He graduated from the Boston Combined Residency Program in Pediatrics at Boston Children’s Hospital and Boston Medical Center in 2006 and has been working as a pediatrician at the Sidney Borum Health Center since that time. Dr. Vetters focuses on providing care to high risk adolescents and young adults, specifically developing programs that support the needs of homeless youth and inner city LGBT youth.

name: Dr. Maryellen Brucato
og:description: Dr. Brucato joined New Jersey Foot & Ankle Centers in Oradell, New Jersey in April 2013 as an associate podiatrist. She began her education at St. Joseph's University in Philadelphia, PA where she obtained her Bachelor's of Science in biology and a minor certificate in Spanish. While there, she was inducted into Sigma Delta Pi (the Spanish honors society) as well as Alpha Epsilon Delta (the pre-medical honors society). Immediately after college, Dr. Brucato attended Temple University School of Podiatric Medicine in Philadelphia, PA. While there, she volunteered for many races in the medical tent with the sports medicine club. She also became the President of the American Association for Women Podiatrists Student Chapter. Additionally, she served as the TUSPM student representative to the New Jersey Podiatric Medical Society.   From 2010 to 2013, Dr. Brucato completed her Podiatric Surgery Residency at Morristown Medical  Center. This included extensive surgical training in all major areas of the foot and ankle including elective forefoot, rearfoot reconstruction, diabetic foot infections/amputations, trauma, and plastic surgery techniques. She completed rotations in virtually all aspects of medicine including rotations in the emergency department, internal medicine, and vascular medicine. During residency, Dr. Brucato completed multiple research projects and publications including being honored to present her research at the national meeting of the American College of Foot & Ankle Surgeons. In 2011, one of her research posters achieved a Finalist Award at the Atlantic Health Research Day out of hundreds of posters.   Since joining New Jersey Foot & Ankle Centers, Dr. Brucato remains active academically and also holds an attending position at Morristown Medical Center where she is able to teach the residents clinically as well as academically. She also serves as the Clinical Research Coordinator for the Podiatric Surgery Residency Program there.  Dr. Brucato has experience in treating a variety of different types of patients including athletes, pediatric patients, and diabetics. She is extremely knowledgeable in many new technological advances and procedures in the foot and ankle field and is certified in foot and ankle arthroscopy. She also volunteers at the Spasticity and Gait Disorder Center in Morristown, NJ. Although Dr.Brucato is surgically trained, she is conservatively minded, and only recommends surgery as a last resort. Outside of the office, she enjoys running, visiting the Jersey Shore where she grew up, traveling, and relaxing in her home in Pompton Lakes with her fiancée and Yorkie named Fergie

He hopes to establish a continuity of care with his patients, which is vital to one’s health.

name: Dr. Robert Carracino
og:description: Dr. Robert Carracino has been recognized by the National Committee for Quality Assurance (NCQA) as a Triple Crown physician.  This means that his practice has been recognized as a Patient-Centered Medical Home (level 3) and individually, he achieved recognition for the quality care provided to both Diabetic Patients and Heart/Stroke patients.   Dr. Robert Carracino is a capable and attentive internist based in Tinton Falls, NJ. Dr. Carracino attended Universidad de Navarra Facultad de Medicina, where he earned his degree in medicine. He completed a residency in internal medicine at Seton Hall University, Trinitas Hospital. Dr. Carracino also completed a residency at St. Elizabeth Hospital. Dr. Carracino is certified by the American Board of Internal Medicine. He is affiliated with the Riverview Medical Center in Red Bank, NJ. Patients see Dr. Carracino for a variety of reasons, including arthritis, asthma, cystic fibrosis, melena and diabetic consultations. He speaks English and Spanish fluently. Dr. Carracino is committed to helping his patients enjoy a healthier lifestyle. He works with each one to discuss ways they can make better choices for their health.

professional_statement: Dr. Jillian Boroniec is a dedicated and compassionate family physician based in Chicago, IL. She then completed both her internship and residency in family medicine at the University of Michigan.,,Dr. Boroniec is affiliated with Rush University Medical Center in Chicago. She is board certified by the American Board of Family Medicine.,,She sees patients of all ages from infants to geriatrics. Her areas of interest include women's health, depression/anxiety, preventive medicine, and the management of chronic diseases including type II diabetes, hypertension, hyperlipidemia, obesity, and asthma. She places special emphasis on disease prevention and developing a partnership with her patients to work towards their health and wellness.

Wonderful pleasant experience!,Dr. Jillian was great - incredibly kind and easy to relate to. Also very thorough. ,I have never had such a caring, informed, thoughtful, sensitive, intelligent doctor consultation in 47 years. ,Dr. Boroniec was super friendly and a great listener. She provided me with excellent care and I felt very comfortable with her.,I really like Dr. Boroniec and her staff and would recommend her to anyone.  Very friendly and willing to listen.  Unfortunately, I had to move to Denver, CO and have to try to find another doctor :(,She talks to you like a friend would. Very good advice too. I'm a habitual mistruster of doctors so know that it means a lot when I say I trust her completely.,Dr. Boroniec was friendly and helpful.  I would definitely visit her again.,Dr. Boroniec was wonderful. Sympathetic, patient, optimistic, a great listener and communicator. I was very pleased with my appointment.

However, the intake process was quite painful. I was told to stand next to a phone to wait for a phone call from a pre-registration staff member, and ended up waiting for 15 minutes. When I finally got the call, the staffer was confused about why I was supposed to speak with her (how was I supposed to know?). The wait was also too long.,Jillian was very attentive and thorough. She took the time to listen to my concerns and made me feel comfortable.,Dr. Jillian Boroniec was very friendly, patient and genuine. She listened carefully to my concerns and answered all my questions. I feel like I can trust her even though today was only my first visit. ,My visit with Dr. Boroniec was great, she made me feel comfortable.  ,I've been looking for a new primary care physician for a while, and I'm so glad I found Dr. Boroniec.  Her bedside manner is impeccable, she's funny, kind, and personable, and most important, she's extremely compassionate and competent.  Some doctors can make you feel rushed during an appointment, but she takes the time to make you really feel cared for.  I've already recommended her to several of my friends!,It was a good visit. She had a nice medical student shadowing her and I believe it is positive to want to mentor others. I did not feel rushed by the doctors, but I did cut our time short because I had to wait so long to be seen.,Compassionate, knowledgeable, accommodating and overall wonderful!  ,All of the office staff, from the receptionist, to nurse, to the doctor, were all extremely welcoming and calming. They took their time during my appointment, answered all my questions and asked relevant ones without judgement. She was then very thorough in her follow through and was clear with what I had to do next. I am very happy I've found her and will definitely continue seeing her as my primary care physician.,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

og:description: Dr. Charles Adamczyk is a caring and experienced obstetrician and gynecologist serving the River Forest, IL community. Dr. Adamczyk earned his medical degree from Loyola University Chicago. He was chief resident during his residency in obstetrics and gynecology at the University of Chicago. Dr. Adamczyk is certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and is affiliated with MacNeal Hospital in Berwyn, IL. He is a member of the American Congress of Obstetricians and Gynecologists. Dr. Adamczyk is bilingual in English and Spanish. Dr. Adamczyk believes in a holistic approach with emphasis on patient education and an understanding of their health and body. He also believes that primary prevention is the key to optimal health outcomes and encourages his patients to practice preventive health measures.

She graduated from the School for Advanced Studies, a dual enrollment high school program, where she obtained 50 college credits prior to entering undergraduate study. She was a Golden Drum Scholar, which awarded her a full tuition scholarship to University of Miami. There, she obtained a Bachelor of Science in pre-medical studies in only three years. She earned a Howard Hughes Scholarship Award, while at UM, for her achievements in medical research at University of Miami School of Medicine (now Miller School of Medicine). og:description: When scheduling an annual exam, please be sure you are complying with your insurance company’s policy. Dr. Misha Dad is a kind and trusted primary care doctor based in Boston, MA. She is an alumna of the University of Massachusetts, where she earned her medical degree. She completed both her internship and residency in internal medicine at Tufts Medical Center. Dr. Dad is a part of General Medical Associates and is affiliated with Tufts Medical Center in Boston, MA. She is certified by the American Board of Internal Medicine. In addition to diagnosing and treating illness, Dr. Dad offers a range of acute, chronic, and preventative medical care services. Dr. Dad is devoted to ensuring the longevity of her patients’ health and developing long-lasting relationships with them. She takes her time to understand symptoms and give correct diagnosis to ensure the continued health of all her patients.

name: Dr. Pamela Edwards
og:description: Dr. Pam Edwards is a qualified and skilled family physician based in Beaufort, SC. Dr. Edwards earned her medical degree from Mercer University in Macon. She completed her residency in family medicine at Floyd Medical Center. She also holds a bachelor’s degree from Shorter University in Rome. Dr. Edwards is board certified in family medicine by the American Board of Family Medicine and is a member of the American Academy of Family Physicians. She is affiliated with Hilton Head Regional Medical Center in Hilton Head, SC. She is a part of Lady's Island Medical Center. Dr. Edwards provides a full range of family medicine services for males and females of all age groups with a special interest in women’s health, pediatrics, and preventive medicine. Her experience includes working in both military and civilian clinics. She has served in the U.S. Navy Medical Corps and was a family physician for the U.S. Naval Hospital in Beaufort, SC for 4 years. Her work with the Naval Hospital earned her several “Excellence in Action” awards.

name: Dr. David Anmuth
og:description: **PLEASE NOTE: you will need to fill out additional paperwork upon arrival of your appointment.  Dr. Anmuth joined Allergy & ENT Associates in July, 2007. He is a Diplomate of the American Board of Pediatrics and the American Board of Allergy and Immunology. In addition, he is a member of both the American Academy and the American College of Allergy, Asthma and Immunology.   In 1998, Dr. Anmuth graduated with highest honors from Lehigh University located in Bethlehem, PA and received his medical degree in 2002 from Temple University School of Medicine in Philadelphia, PA. He completed a three year pediatric training at Thomas Jefferson University/AI Dupont Hospital for Children (Philadelphia, PA/Wilmington, DE) and then went to Baylor College of Medicine/Texas Children’s Hospital where he performed a two year fellowship in adult and pediatric allergy/immunology.   During his training, Dr. Anmuth participated in several projects and lead presentations which focused on public health topics such as the effects of environmental tobacco smoke on childhood asthma and the relationship of obesity (body mass index) and asthma. In daily practice, Dr. Anmuth’s main goal is patient and family education. He strongly believes that proper awareness, guidance, and treatment will enable those with allergic disease to live fuller and more active lives.   Dr. Anmuth enjoys being active in the community and has been a Big Brother, a volunteer baseball coach, and an asthma camp counselor. He is married with one child and enjoys living in Houston.

name: Dr. David Anmuth
og:description: **PLEASE NOTE: you will need to fill out additional paperwork upon arrival of your appointment.  Dr. Anmuth joined Allergy & ENT Associates in July, 2007. He is a Diplomate of the American Board of Pediatrics and the American Board of Allergy and Immunology. In addition, he is a member of both the American Academy and the American College of Allergy, Asthma and Immunology.   In 1998, Dr. Anmuth graduated with highest honors from Lehigh University located in Bethlehem, PA and received his medical degree in 2002 from Temple University School of Medicine in Philadelphia, PA. He completed a three year pediatric training at Thomas Jefferson University/AI Dupont Hospital for Children (Philadelphia, PA/Wilmington, DE) and then went to Baylor College of Medicine/Texas Children’s Hospital where he performed a two year fellowship in adult and pediatric allergy/immunology.   During his training, Dr. Anmuth participated in several projects and lead presentations which focused on public health topics such as the effects of environmental tobacco smoke on childhood asthma and the relationship of obesity (body mass index) and asthma. In daily practice, Dr. Anmuth’s main goal is patient and family education. He strongly believes that proper awareness, guidance, and treatment will enable those with allergic disease to live fuller and more active lives.   Dr. Anmuth enjoys being active in the community and has been a Big Brother, a volunteer baseball coach, and an asthma camp counselor. He is married with one child and enjoys living in Houston.

review_text:
I actually have no injuries or chronic pain but i do love going to the chiropractor for maintenance. Dr. Arash really evaluated me and gave me some exercises to work on strengthening my mid-back and bettering my posture. Really nice guy and knows what he's doing - took his time making sure i was even and aligned. Will definitely be back!,Dr. Noor was excellent, I could barely walk when I came in and when I left, I was feeling great.  He diagnosed the problem, explained what could be causing the problem, did some corrections and showed me so exercises that could help.  I would recommend him to anybody.,Dr. Arash is by far the best chiropractor I have been to.,My first visit with Dr. Noor couldn't have been better! His office was nice and his staff was super friendly. Dr. Noor was very informative and I felt he cared about my health. He is most definitely someone I will continue to work with and someone I highly recommend! When I left his office, I felt like a million bucks. ,I am typically not a huge fan of Chiropractors but Dr Noor completely changed my perspective on them today.  The visit was easy and I didn't feel like he gave me the generic mumbo jumbo script most doctors without personalities give because they do not know how to socialize with humans. 

It was also not a turn and burn, he took his time and fully explained to me everything that I wasn't too sure about.  

Overall great experience and I highly recommend him.   ,Very knowledgeable and wasted no time in getting straight to the point. Even the after treatment treatment was over and above. Love that massage chair. 
,Excellent experience with Dr. Noor.  He is welcoming, attentive and professional.  The office is efficient and courteous.  While waiting for your appointment you can use two massage chairs which are terrific.  ,I have been treated by several Chiropractors before and this was my first visit with Dr. Noor. After a thorough consultation and the recommended treatments for my ailing concern Dr. Noor proceeded to work on my body. He used his hands on me to administer full body adjustments as well as applying his contemporary accessories. Soon afterward,  I did find satisfying relief and felt much better. I realize it's going to take several treatments to improve and to help manage my problems.  I found Dr.Noor to be extremely good with his practice and highly recommend him to anyone whom is seeking to find an excellent, knowledgeable and talented Chiropractor.   Needless to say without hesitation, I scheduled my next appointment. ,I've been coming to Dr. Noor for a little over a year. I've gone to many other doctors, and Dr. Noor was the only one to figure out what was wrong with my hips. 

Not only does he provide chiropractic treatment, he also does physical therapy to make my hips stronger and prevent my hip injury from happening again. I don’t usually write reviews because I’m a professional athlete, but Dr. Noor deserves one! 

The doctor also has amazing massage chairs that he puts me in to make sure I'm comfortable while I'm waiting and is always making sure I am okay. 

Sometimes Saturday's are busy, but what other doctor is open on Saturday's? I HIGHLY recommend Dr. Noor because he took his time with me and will do whatever it takes to get my back to how it used to be. 
,Very impressed! ,Best doctor ever. Super knowlegable, understanding, listens, and addresses the issue at hand. 

He also has amazing massage chairs to sit in while you wait to be seen. The office is really cool.,Dr. Noor is awesome!,Arash is great!  I showed up a little early and was seen straight away, and I left feeling better... Both physically because of the adjustment and also mentally because of the exercises he taught me.  I'll be coming back after completing the exercises to continue progressing towards a straight back!,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

name: Dr. James Wong
og:description: Dr. James Wong is a licensed Chiropractor serving the New York City community. Dr. Wong has been freeing people from pain in the clinic in New York, NY. As a Chiropractor with experience, he is committed to promoting optimal health and well being of  patients. We at JW Chiropractic use a "whole person approach". This approach to wellness means looking for underlying causes of any disturbance or disruption (which may or may not be causing symptoms at the time) and make whatever interventions and lifestyle adjustments that would optimize the conditions for normal function. Using this unique approach, Dr. Wong and his staff are able to help you to accelerate and/or maintain your journey to good health. Dr. Wong accepts most major insurances. If you do not see your insurance listed, please give our office a call.

I feel really confident in his treatment plan and look forward to returning. ,Dr. Wong is bright, both in intellect and personality. I had suffered severe back and neck pain for years before deciding to try going to a chiropractor. Upon my first visit he quickly diagnosed exactly what was wrong with my back, and took the time to explain it to me using books and graphs in the office. Throughout the last 3 months of me attending his office he has always been prompt, efficient and thorough. Additionally, he is a warm, genuine person who puts me at ease as he goes through my adjustments. My pain level has decreased ENORMOUSLY. I went from being in tears because of the constant and intense neck pain down to nearly zero.

The office staff are all incredibly nice and efficient in scheduling. The office itself is bright, clean and spacious. A few days of the week Dr. Wong brings in a massage therapist as an added extra bonus for his patients. 

I HIGHLY recommend Dr. Wong to anyone suffering any kind of pain!,It was excellent! og:description: **Please type your NAME exactly as it appears on your insurance card when booking your appointment. Dr. Linda Karadsheh is a caring and considerate OB-GYN based in Clinton Township, MI. Dr. Karadsheh earned her medical degree from Michigan State University. She completed her residency in obstetrics and gynecology at Mount Clemens General Hospital. She also received a bachelor’s degree from the University of Michigan. Dr. Karadsheh is board certified in obstetrics and gynecology and is an active member of the American College of Osteopathic Obstetricians and Gynecologists, Student Osteopathic Medical Association, American Osteopathic Association, and the Michigan Osteopathic Association. A strong believer in medical guidelines, Dr. Karadsheh provides care and encouragement to her patients. Her skill set has given her the opportunity to treat patients for a host of diverse issues, with special focus on issues pertaining to women’s health. Dr. Karadsheh understands the fears and sensitivities her patients face, and she works hard to help her patients overcome their health challenges.

og:description: **Please type your NAME exactly as it appears on your insurance card when booking your appointment. If you are an established patient at this office and need to book an annual physical, please call the office directly to ensure the provider allows proper time to meet your wellness needs. Dr. Gail MacIntyre is a diligent and detail-oriented family physician in Clinton Township, MI. She obtained her medical degree from the University of New England. She completed her internship at Mount Clemens General Hospital. She then completed her residency in general surgery at Bi-County Community Hospital. Dr. MacIntyre is a part of McLaren Macomb-Clinton Township Family Medicine. She is board certified by the American Osteopathic Board of Family Physicians. She is a member of the American Osteopathic Association, the American College of Osteopathic Family Physicians, and the American Society of Colposcopy and Cervical Pathology. Patients see Dr. MacIntyre for a variety of reasons, including general follow ups, annual physicals, and thyroid consultations. During her consultations, Dr. MacIntyre fully explains patients’ conditions and helps them choose an appropriate treatment plan.

professional_statement: Dr. Carrie Judy received her bachelor of science in biology and chemistry from Geneva College in Beaver Falls, Pennsylvania. She earned her medical degree from Penn State College of Medicine in Hershey, Pennsylvania. Dr. Judy performed her residency at Eglin Air Force Base in Florida, where she was chief resident. She is board certified in family medicine.,,Dr. Judy is a member of Alpha Omega Alpha medical honor society. She appeared on “Mystery Diagnosis” on Discovery Health. She is the recipient of a Meritorious Service Medal and served in Iraq.,She enjoys caring for the whole person at Colonial Family Practice. Dr. Judy likes the small-town feel of the Sumter area. When she is not at work, Dr. Judy loves to spend time with her husband, daughter, three cats, and two dogs.

name: Dr. David D'Agate
og:description: *PLEASE NOTE: We only see patients ages 15 and older!*  After completing an advanced degree in biophysics and physiology at Georgetown University, Washington, D.C., Dr. D'Agate completed his residency at Winthrop University Hospital in 2002 and a fellowship in adult cardiovascular disease at Saint Vincent's Hospital and Medical Center in New York City in 2005. Dr. D'Agate recently co-authored a book chapter and numerous publications in various areas of cardiovascular disease. His interests include: atherosclerosis and diabetes/obesity, non-invasive imaging of the coronary arteries, primary/secondary prevention of atherosclerotic heart disease, and the diagnosis/treatment of peripheral vascular disease. Dr. D'Agate is only one of a few cardiologists in the United States with advanced training in vascular imaging technology (R.V.T.). Dr. D'Agate is board-certified in internal medicine, cardiovascular disease, and nuclear cardiology. He currently practices as a member of Suffolk Heart Group with privileges at Southside Hospital of Bay Shore, Good Samaritan Hospital of West Islip, and St. Catherine of Siena of Smithtown, New York. *Dr. D'Agate is accepting new patients as young as 15 years old. All patients under the age of 18 must be accompanied with a parent or gardian.

name: Dr. Sergey Terushkin
og:description: Sergey Terushkin is a board certified general and bariatric surgeon practicing in New York, NY. He earned his medical degree from Ross University School of Medicine, interned at North Shore-LIJ Health System, and completed his residency at Maimonides Medical Center.  Dr. Terushkin specializes in minimally invasive and bariatric surgery having graduated a fellowship at Cleveland Clinic. He uses cutting edge technology and individualized patient care. A few of his most commonly performed procedures include laparoscopic gastric banding, laparoscopic sleeve gastrectomy, laparoscopic gallbladder surgery, laparoscopic and open hernia repair, and removal of lipomas and cysts. He is a member of the American College of Surgeons and the Society of Metabolic and Bariatric Surgeons. Dr. Terushkin regularly attends meetings for various professional societies in order to stay current.  Outside of work, Dr. Terushkin is passionate about fishing, skiing, and running. He often participates in community educational seminars and diabetes and obesity walks. He is fluent in Russian and English.

name: Dr. Moo Lee
og:description: Moo Lee is a dedicated and experienced pediatrician specializing in pediatric cardiology. Dr. Lee is available to his patients in Duluth, GA.  Originally from South Korea, Dr. Lee earned his medical degree from the Yonsei University’s Medical College. He then completed his pediatric residency at the Children’s Hospital at the University of Manitoba. Dr. Lee was a pediatric cardiology fellow at the Babies and Children’s Hospital and University Hospitals of Cleveland. He then served as a research fellow in pediatric cardiology at the Case Western Reserve University before he completed his postdoctoral research fellowship at the Mount Sinai Hospital of Cleveland.  Dr. Lee provides his patients with comprehensive pediatric care, hearing and vision tests, ADHD evaluations, and pediatric counseling. He prides himself on his easy going bedside manner and utmost compassion for his smaller patients, putting both the children and their parents at ease in his care.  Dr. Lee is a loving father to his three children and caring husband to his wife.

review_text: He was awesome. He threw in a little chiropractor like things and massage too! walked out feeling like I was floating!,So so wonderful. I left feeling so much better, I didn't even realize where I needed attention in my body and he knew just from looking at me. He really knows what he is doing and the whole staff and atmosphere is welcoming. ,By far the most amazing experience I've had finding a doctor through ZocDoc. I can't say enough wonderful things about Dr. Phil and his entire team. It was such a pleasant experience and I look forward to going back again and again. ,Dr. Trigiani treated me for dance related pain in legs and feet and it feels much better.  I will definitely be back.,Dr. Phil is AMAZING! Very easy going, warm demeanor, and he explains what he is doing, so you feel comfortable. This was my first time ever going to acupuncture, and I actually felt euphoric when I left. I wonder if this usually happens to everyone? The office is very serene and the receptionists are very welcoming! I can tell Dr. Phil loves his job, and is passionate about health and well being. I had a great experience and would definitely go back! ,I was nervous about getting stabbed with needles... This was the best experience I have ever had with a doctor.  I was immediately relaxed upon walking into the office.  The staff is bubbly and friendly and the doctor was very thorough in his assessment.  This is truly a unique approach to wellness and the team here is a very interesting group of characters.  I usually don't rant and rave about this type of stuff, but this is HIGHLY recommended.,Amazing! He's so personable and knowledgable. Very gentle and very kind. Looking forward to going back.,The team welcome you so awesomely. Then you meet Philip and he is great. He's very honest, warm, and  genuine. Highly recommend him!,Very informative and helpful in explaining everything they were doing - a professional and beneficial experience,Dr. Philip is fantastic. He is knowledgeable and intuitive, and is incredibly warm and approachable. He knows exactly what to work on, and I've already seen a big difference in my body and well being. He answers questions and makes you feel like you really matter. I've only seen him a few times but my back and neck are finally releasing the stress they've been holding for years, and those areas feel freer and looser. His colleague, Dr. John, and the rest of the care team are also amazing. I plan on seeing them regularly to properly maintain everything in good health!,A friend referred me to Dr. T because of his distinct ability to help people improve using unique and natural techniques. His office is very welcoming, as are his staff--Unisha (sp?), the receptionist is just delightful. My sessions never lasted more than 30 minutes, which is perfect for a lunch time appointment, but I got so much out of them. Unfortunately, I could only afford to see him about four or five times, but my body improved from day one and is still benefiting from those sessions weeks later. His chiropractor, Dr. John, is magical as well. All aspects of my experience were exceptional. Thanks to Dr. Trigiani and Dr. John for helping me.,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

When I arrived, he saw me within 10 of my appointment time and asked me specific questions regarding my low back pain. He assessed my back and began to explain to me what my issues were. I was able to immediately schedule my physical therapy sessions and had my first session the next day. Again, he saw me within 10 minutes (probably less) of my appointment time. The physical therapy session was about 30 minutes and I felt improvement in my back when my session was done. Given that I was apprehensive about seeing a chiropractor about my issue, I'm glad that I did and I am glad it was Dr. McClenny!,My first visit was informative and reassuring.,It was my first time seeing a chiropractor so I was s little nervous but his bedside manner was great so it eased the fear.,This was my first appointment with a chiropractor. I was nervous because I have heard the horror stories. Mr. McClenny was very warm, welcoming and professional. He took time to explain my situation and course of treatment. He is also quite funny which helped calmed my nerves. I left the appointment feeling much butter than when I went in!! I will be scheduling future appointments with Mr. McClenny! Thank you!!,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

name: Dr. Gregory Zapantis
og:description: Gregory Zapantis is a trusted obstetrician and gynecologist (OB-GYN) and reproductive endocrinologist treating patients in the Jericho area of Long Island in New York. He is certified in reproductive endocrinology and infertility by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology. Dr. Zapantis is a member of the American Congress of Obstetricians and Gynecologists. He speaks English and Greek. Dr. Zapantis completed his Bachelor’s degree at the University of Toronto. He also studied medicine at the Albert Einstein College of Medicine of Yeshiva University in Bronx, NY. Dr. Zapantis later finished a fellowship in reproductive endocrinology and infertility at the some institution. Patients trust Dr. Zapantis to provide a number of services. A few of these include ovulation induction, donor egg and sperm management, gestational carrier (surrogate) consultations, intrauterine embryo transfer, egg freezing and fertility preservation, and many others.

name: Dr. Dip Jadav
og:description: Dr. Jadav is a brilliant and engaging ophthalmologist based in Sugar Land, TX. He has a true passion for ophthalmology and genuinely cares for the well-being of his patients. Dr. Jadav was one of ten students chosen for the Medical Science Scholars Program, a 6-year joint undergraduate-medical degree program. He completed his internship at Houston Methodist Hospital and residency in Ophthalmology at the University of Texas Health Science Center. Dr. Jadav also completed a prestigious fellowship in Cornea, External Disease, and Refractive Surgery at Tulane University.  During his medical education, Dr. Jadav authored and edited several articles and books.  He is also currently contributing to medical research in affiliation with Houston Methodist Hospital. Dr. Jadav is a member of the Texas Medical Association, Fort Bend County Medical Association, American Academy of Ophthalmology, and Alpha Omega Alpha Honor Medical Society.  Dr. Jadav is fluent in English, Spanish, and Gujarati, and his practice also accommodates Hindi-, Bengali-, and Urdu-speaking patients.  Dr. Jadav enjoys spending time with his family, reading, and playing sports.

og:description: Robert S. Graebe, MD, is a physician at Valley Medical Group, affiliated with The Valley Hospital in Ridgewood, NJ. name: Dr. Ella Ostrovskaya
og:description: Dr. Ella Ostrovskaya is a foot and ankle specialist & surgeon. After graduating from DePaul University with high honors, she went on to attend Dr. William Scholl College of Podiatric Medicine. She then completed a 3-year surgical residency at Swedish Covenant Hospital in Chicago, IL. Her specialization includes pain relief, deformity correction, diabetic foot care, wound-care and the restoration of function in the foot and ankle. Dr. Ostrovskaya is a compassionate physician who believes that all patients deserve the highest quality of medical care. Her journey to become a podiatric physician began when she had a foot problem at an early age and was inspired by the care she received from the doctor who treated her. She is passionate to help those who suffer from the foot and ankle ailments. Please visit our website to learn more about our practice: www.olivomedicalwellnesscenter.com *All patients must bring a valid picture ID to the appointment. ***PLEASE FILL IN ONLINE CHECK IN FORMS**

name: Dr. Khuram Khan
og:description: Dr. Khuram Khan is a board certified Ophthalmologist.  He is fellowship trained in retina and vitreo-retinal surgery.  Dr. Khan graduated cum laude with a Bachelor of Arts from the University of Pennsylvania.  He went on to earn his medical degree at Pennsylvania State University, where he served as Class President.  Dr. Khan completed his internship in internal medicine at Lankenau Hospital in Philadelphia, PA.  He then completed an ophthalmology residency at the State University of New York, Downstate in Brooklyn.   Dr. Khan completed a fellowship in vitreo-retinal surgery at Tulane University under the tutelage of world-renowned retinal surgeon, Dr. Gholam Peyman.  He completed additional retina fellowship training at Henry Ford Hospital in Detroit, Michigan.  Before moving to Maryland, Dr. Khan worked for several years in Las Vegas, NV where he ran a successful solo practice.  Dr. Khan has served as an investigator in a phase 3 clinical trail and has published articles in peer reviewed journals.  In his spare time Dr. Khan enjoys golfing, snowboarding and spending time with his wife and four children.

og:description: Keith M. Blechman, M.D. is a plastic, cosmetic, and reconstructive surgeon who is board certified by the American Board of Plastic Surgery. His practice offers excellence and compassion in cosmetic surgery of the face, breast and body, as well as state-of-the-art reconstructive procedures for breast cancer, skin cancer, and traumatic injuries. Dr. Blechman provides the highest quality care and offers the most cutting-edge techniques.  He prides himself on maintaining a personalized boutique plastic surgery practice where all his patients are treated as VIPs.  Dr. Blechman is includeed as a Rising Star in both the 2016 and 2015 New York Super Doctors lists, an honor extended to only 2.5% of physicians in the region. Dr. Blechman completed his plastic surgery residency at New York University Medical Center and his reconstructive microsurgery fellowship at MD Anderson Cancer Center.  He is affiliated with Lenox Hill Hospital, Manhattan Eye, Ear, and Throat Hospital, New York Eye and Ear Infirmary of Mount Sinai, as well as New York Methodist Hospital in Brooklyn. Dr. Blechman presents research at numerous national and international conferences, and is an author on multiple publications in peer-reviewed journals including Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery, The Breast Journal, and the Journal of Reconstructive Microsurgery. Textbook chapters written by him appear in the most recent edition of Grabb and Smith’s Plastic Surgery as well as in Problems in Breast Surgery: A Repair Manual.

Dr. Blechman.,Dr. Blechman was very kind and sensitive to my issue.  He answered all my questions and put me at ease during the procedure I needed. I was very lucky to pick Dr. Blechman for my care.  All my questions were always completely answered. While I never want to go to the doctor, I would gladly go back to Dr. B if I had a reason to.  Wish more doctors were like him. ,Very personable . of the day if you need him. I would recommend him. ,Amazing bed side manner and he was very detailed and every explanation, looking forward to having surgery with him.,Pleasant, attentive, great bedside manner. I never felt rushed, all my questions and concerns were responded to, and I feel that my surgery will be in very capable hands. Absolutely would recommend!!,Dr. Blechman was very gentle. He's very knowledgable on all medical questions. I would highly recommend. ,He took his time and did amazing and thorough job!!!,Our daughter took a fall at the playground and cut her chin pretty badly. Dr. Blechman made time to see her immediately and did a beautiful job "putting her back together."   He  followed up to check on her healing progress, and was readily available when we had questions.  Not only did he do excellent work, but he was very kind when dealing with my daughter and patient with my many questions.   We couldn't recommend him more highly. ,He is highly attentive, and goes above and beyond to make sure all needs are met. Genuinely nice too. Highly recommended.,It is always a pleasure to see Dr. Blechman. I'm pleased with my results and have healed beautifully!! I am so happy and much more confident. ,Great therapeutic communication during a procedure. His questions about my medical history were extensive and he provided guidance with several options. 
He is a most impressive physician.,Dr.Blechman made me feel comfortable, he was kind and very professional.,Extremely nice, competent and attentive. A gem of a doctor. Great work - and no wait time!,He was very nice, willing to talk about insurance and talked me though different options. A nice visit,Excellent! Thoroughly knowledgable, exceptionally competent - a young surgeon at the top of his game. We feel very fortunate that Dr. Blechman was on call at Lennox Hill Emergency(downtown) that night to repair our daughter's badly damaged lip. At 2am on Sunday morning, I feared there was little chance we'd have access to a surgeon of Dr. Blechman's caliber. We got lucky; he was on-call, and today's follow-up 5 days later confirms our gratitude. She may well have had a huge, ugly scar, but it looks like his repair will allow her realize the very best outcome we could have hoped for with minimal scaring.,I am so happy I found Dr. Blechman on ZocDoc. I was looking around for a plastic surgeon for about a week and none of them worked out for me. I arrived early for my appointment and didn't have to wait long. The doctor was very nice and warm as well as the rest of the office staff. This place is clean and welcoming. If I ever need to consult with a plastic surgeon again I will surely go back to Dr. Blechman. ,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

name: Dr. Shereen Russell
og:description: Dr. Russell is a board certified Obstetrician and Gynecologist, practicing on the Upper East Side of New York City. After receiving her undergraduate degree from the University of Southern California in Los Angeles, Dr. Russell earned her medical degree at the University of Connecticut School of Medicine. She completed her residency at Lenox Hill Hospital in New York City and maintains full attending privileges. Dr. Russell is a member of several societies such as the New York Gynecological Society, American College of Obstetrical and Gynecology Fellow, and the American Medical Association. In the course of her practicing medicine, Dr. Russell has earned many accolades such as being designated to New York's Top Obstetricians and Gynecologists and to Castle Connolly Best Doctors in New York.  Dr. Russell has a thriving practice in Manhattan, and her loyal patients value her unique blend of clinical expertise, surgical acumen and caring demeanor. Dr. Russell has built her practice around her personal relationships with patients, and her office is centered around privacy and patient service. While Dr. Russell continues to enjoy practicing Obstetrician and Gynecological healthcare, she devotes at least one day per week to surgery and is an expert in the full suite of major and laparoscopic surgical techniques. As an expert consultant for a medical liability insurance company, Dr. Russell often reviews patient treatment decisions to ensure the highest standards of care in her field. Dr. Russell has a long-term commitment to her practice and to New York City, where she lives with her husband and two daughters, just a few blocks walk to both her practice and Lenox Hill Hospital.

name: Dr. Babajide Faditan
og:description: Dr. Babajide Faditan is a trusted pediatrician and primary care doctor serving families in Largo, MD. He is certified by the American Board of Pediatrics. Dr. Faditan studied medicine at the Obafemi Awolowo University College of Health Sciences in Ife, Nigeria. He continued his education in pediatrics at Bronx-Lebanon Hospital Center in Bronx, NY, and the Brookdale University Hospital and Medical Center in Brooklyn. He has also received continued medical education. Patients and their parents come to Dr. Faditan to receive a number of services, such as routine physical examinations and well-baby checkups, sick children evaluations, prenatal fetal consultations, pediatric vaccinations, urinary tract infection treatments, and many others. His practice uses advanced software to deliver responsible, proactive care. Dr. Faditan enjoys music, watching documentaries, and playing chess.

og:description: Dr Akatue attended Medical University Sofia in Bulgaria Europe and completed Internal Medicine residency training at Meharry Medical College Nashville TN. She comes with a wealth of experience.  She has worked in outpatient services, hospital medicine, long term care and emergency medicine. She is a recipient of The Gateway Health System Physician Excellence Award 2007.  Her Special interest is in the area of advancing the general well-being of her patients; emphasizing on women’s health, improving physical endurance through careful healthy diet and exercise programs. Dr. Akatue’s work is not limited to the office. She is also involved in public speaking on health related issues, medical volunteering such as country music marathons, faith based projects such as mission trips and retreats.

name: Dr. Glenn Malat
og:description: Dr. Malat graduated in 1994 from the State University of New York, College of Optometry. Dr. Malat spent 12 years at East Side Eye Associates in Manhattan, building a loyal patient base and driving what is now the second largest contact lens practice in New York City.He moved his focus to NJ, where he opened three successful practices, each allowing him the freedom to develop deep relationships with his patients and the communities he served. Today, Dr. Malat’s vision is focused on a single, brand new, state of the art eye care practice, supported by his staff of 26 years. (formerly Gurian Hearing and Vision) Caldwell Eyecare offers an in-house lab for digital free form eyeglass prescriptions, with quick service. He is certified in the diagnosis and treatment of eye diseases, including kerataconus and low vision and the co-management of LASIK. He is also a referral source for difficult and hard to fit contact lens patients. Today, his expanded evening and weekend hours maximizes service and convenience for his patients. Dr. Malat is a resident and active member of the West Caldwell community. He has been happily married for 30 years to his elementary school sweetheart, and is father to two daughters, that you will often and proudly hear him describe as “super, amazing, strong and independent young women”. His passion is his patients, especially first time contact lens fittings with his young patients. Over the years, he has been fortunate in seeing many of them grow into adults and then, in turn, bring their own children to see him–and to Dr. Malat, there is no greater satisfaction than to keep growing the Caldwell Eyecare family. When he’s not in the office, he loves spending time with his family, friends and playing baseball.
