He's always so friendly and is a wealth of information. ,Very thorough and professional!,All doctors should learn from him how to treat patients. Dr. Malat is always on time with appointments, respects all questions you have and is very personable. , Dr. Malat has a wonderful combination of being very knowledgeable, very personable, and thorough in his explanations of all the procedures he performs.  I had a thorough eye exam today, my first with Dr Malat after decades of wearing glasses.  It was by far the most comprehensive I've received.  He has my highest recommendation.  ,Nice, friendly, polite and the most important he is PROFESSIONAL. Highly recommended.,He is am amazing eye doctor who thoroughly explains all aspects of the eye exam, and provides various options for treatments (for me, various types of contacts). Whole family has been seeing him for a number of years, and can't say enough good things about him and his practice. Highly recommend!,Very educational, Dr. Malat is your local neighborhood doctor.  He lives in town and cares about his community.  I enjoyed the imaging and scanning of my eyes; seeing my eye in so many different dimensions and angles was "eye opening!",Upon arriving to my appointment I was warmly greeted by two women at the front and given paperwork to complete. Upon completion of the paperwork.  I was greeted by Dr, Malat.
Dr. Malat explained everything step by step that he was going to do and why.  He carried on a light conversation and was always reassuring during every test.
Some on the eye testing equipment I had never seen before.  The information and results of the testing were immediate.  One of the state of the art eye examine was explained to me to similar to an MRI for eye.  I was able to see my the heath of my eye for myself on a large screen.  This device helps diagnose a multiple list of diseases.
After the testing was complete I was assisted by a wonderful woman who was very knowledgeable and assisted me with the best alternatives for eyeglasses and my insurance coverage.
The office has a positive, pleasant atmosphere with a large selection of eyewear.
If you are a dog lover you will be surrounded by immediate friends.  Everyone has at least one dog and loves to share stories.
Now I wish I had found Dr. Malat years ago.

name: Dr. Elisabeth Klor Gross
og:description: Dr. Elisabeth Klor Gross is a caring and diligent internist serving the community of Chicago, IL. Dr. Klor Gross earned her medical degree from the Semmelweis University Faculty of Medicine in Hungary. She completed her residency training at Ravenswood Hospital Medical Center in Chicago. Dr. Klor Gross is a part of Presence Medical Group - Internal and Addiction Medicine. She is board certified in internal medicine and on the medical staff at Presence Saint Joseph Hospital in Chicago. Her clinical interests include cholesterol problems, diabetes, hypertension, lung problems, warts, and weight loss. Because she is bilingual in English and Hungarian, patients from a variety of backgrounds enjoy having her as their physician.  Dr. Klor Gross is dedicated to helping patients receive the treatment they need so they can enjoy a positive and fulfilling lifestyle. From Dr. Klor Gross: "Being a physician is a caring profession of knowledge, experience, compassion and respect. This is what I provide all of my patients with while forming a partnership with them."

name: Dr. Abiola Dele-Michael
og:description: Dr. Abiola Dele-Michael is a board certified cardiovascular disease expert and provides care for patients with valvular heart disease, coronary artery disease, hypertension, lipid disorders, congestive heart failure, heart rhythm disorders (arrhythmias) and peripheral vascular disease. He is a specialist in advanced echocardiography, nuclear cardiology and vascular ultrasound.   Dr. Dele-Michael was born and raised in New York City. He graduated with honors from Cornell University receiving his Bachelor of Science degree. He attended medical school at the University of Rochester in Rochester, NY and graduated with distinction and with a Masters in Public Health. Dr. Dele-Michael completed his Internal Medicine residency at the University of Michigan in Ann Arbor. After completing his residency, Dr. Dele-Michael was a faculty member at the University of Michigan Medical School. He completed his fellowship in Cardiovascular Disease at New York Presbyterian Hospital/Weill Cornell Medical College specializing in noninvasive advanced cardiovascular imaging, including 3D echocardiography, cardiac CT, cardiac MRI and nuclear cardiology.   Prior to starting Dele-Michael Cardiovascular Medicine, Dr. Dele-Michael was an Assistant Professor of Medicine at Weill Cornell Medical College and accrued extensive experience in the diagnosis and management of complex cardiovascular conditions specifically valvular and structural heart disease.

name: Dr. Abiola Dele-Michael
og:description: Dr. Abiola Dele-Michael is a board certified cardiovascular disease expert and provides care for patients with valvular heart disease, coronary artery disease, hypertension, lipid disorders, congestive heart failure, heart rhythm disorders (arrhythmias) and peripheral vascular disease. He is a specialist in advanced echocardiography, nuclear cardiology and vascular ultrasound.   Dr. Dele-Michael was born and raised in New York City. He graduated with honors from Cornell University receiving his Bachelor of Science degree. He attended medical school at the University of Rochester in Rochester, NY and graduated with distinction and with a Masters in Public Health. Dr. Dele-Michael completed his Internal Medicine residency at the University of Michigan in Ann Arbor. After completing his residency, Dr. Dele-Michael was a faculty member at the University of Michigan Medical School. He completed his fellowship in Cardiovascular Disease at New York Presbyterian Hospital/Weill Cornell Medical College specializing in noninvasive advanced cardiovascular imaging, including 3D echocardiography, cardiac CT, cardiac MRI and nuclear cardiology.   Prior to starting Dele-Michael Cardiovascular Medicine, Dr. Dele-Michael was an Assistant Professor of Medicine at Weill Cornell Medical College and accrued extensive experience in the diagnosis and management of complex cardiovascular conditions specifically valvular and structural heart disease.

review_text: Wonderful beside manner and replied to all my concerns. Would definitely recommend!,Dr. Dele-Michael was very personable and professional. He seems thorough and I appreciate that in someone who is dealing with my ticker! ,Dr. Dele-Michael was great!  The office was clean and I had a very short wait time to be seen and that was after I came late.  I found him to be pleasant professional.  What I loved the most was the amount of information I was given.  I went in as part of my preventative health plan.  Dr. Dele-Michael shared a lot of information about how different factors can affect my health, what I can look out for and some steps I could take now that would help me.  It was a good visit and I look forward to returning in order to receive more detailed input.,He's a great doctor - patient, willing to explain anything, and just all around has a great bedside manner. ,Excellent friendly and thorough!,Excellent doctor who is professional and personable with a friendly staff. Worked out all my insurance issues and found a facility that accepted my insurance. Would highly recommend. ,One of the better first visits/consultations I've ever had with a doctor. Dr. Dele-Michael gave very thorough explanations and details during the examination and made me feel comfortable throughout the visit.,This dr's bedside manner was impeccable! He is extremely intelligent and articulate. I am looking forward to continuing my care with him. He takes his time with his patients. ,Thank you so much doctor for taking care of me. I really appreciate all that you have done. I look forward to seeing you at the next visit. ,I've been a patient of the doctor for several months now and I am extremely satisfied. The staff is excellent! ,Dr. Dele-Michael is warm & professional.  Addressed all my health concerns and is into preventative care.  Dr. Dele-Michael is engaging, answered all my questions and has an excellent bedside manner.  ,Excellent costumer service, very satisfied visit I'll recommend to anyone very good Dr. ,Dr. Dele-Michael is excellent. He is very informative and explained my condition which was easy to understand. He also believes in preventive care and counseled me on improving my health. After my first visit, I immediately knew that he was going to be my permanent cardiologist and my dad now sees him as well! Great staff! ,Wonderful experience! I listened to the doctor's advice and I have seen a dramatic improvement in my health. The doctor and his staff are by far the best! I'm looking forward to my next office visit. ,Very caring and friendly doctor. He took care of me and made me very comfortable throughout his consultation. I highly recommend him. Great practice!,Awesome doctor!!! Very professional and compassionate. He addressed all of my concerns. The staff was very pleasant and they made me feel comfortable. The office location is great and convenient. I'm looking forward to my next visit. ,The entire staff were professional & courteous.  I left feeling more knowledgable & hopefully he will address all my concerns at the next visit! ,Great doctor who listens to your concerns ,Outstanding cardiologist! I was very impressed with his knowledge and professionalism. His explanations were clear and easy to understand. I felt very comfortable throughout the visit and I am looking forward to my followup appointment. The office staff are friendly and wonderful!  ,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

professional_memberships: American Board of Podiatric Surgery,Foot Surgery (Podiatric Surgery),Reconstructive Rearfoot / Ankle Surgery (Podiatric Surgery)
professional_statement: Dr. Alavy earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Biology from University of California, Los Angeles. He obtained his Doctor of Podiatric Medicine degree in 1994 at California College of Podiatric Medicine in San Francisco. He successfully completed his residency at the Doctors Hospital of West Covina. He is currently the Director of The 3 year Surgical Podiatric Residency Program at Doctors Hospital of West Covina. Dr. Alavy is double board-certified in Foot Surgery and Reconstructive Rear Foot and Ankle Surgery by the American Board of Podiatric Surgery. Dr. Alavy is a Fellow of the American College of Foot and Ankle Surgeons. In addition, he has assisted in nearly 1,000 orthopedic and spine surgical cases. He has been in private practice since 1996.

review_text: Dr. Babar was warm and friendly, and personality to boot. I will be making him my podiatrist.  2 Thumbs up! :-),It was great. He was terrific answering my question,Awesome doctor, so nice and very caring. ,I've had an ingrown toenail removed by doctors many times before, and this was, by far, the best experience I've ever had.  In fact, this is one of the best doctor's I have ever had, hands down, regardless of specialty.  He clearly knows what he's doing, he minimized the pain as much as possible for the procedure I had to have done, he's extremely competent, and EXTREMELY personable and genuine.  When I've had this done elsewhere, not only did the ingrown return, but other doctors have had to use double the amount of shots to achieve the same numbing effect before beginning the procedure, and those shots are VERY painful because of where they are administered.  He managed to accomplish the same numbing effect with only 4 shots instead of 8, used a cooling spray to minimize that pain as much as possible, and once the actual procedure began (procedure is painless because you are numb), I watched him do it and his work was very neat, efficient, and accurate.  He understands the importance of keeping in mind how the end product will look as well as feel (because I had the procedure done where they permanently remove the side of the nail by killing the root so that it won't grow back as in in-grown again).  This guy knows what he's doing.  He even offered me water while we were waiting for the numbing effect to kick in so that he could begin the procedure.  I'm going to have to have the same thing done on the other foot, and although I wish I didn't have to, since I do, I'm looking forward to returning here.  ,Dr. Alavy has been great so far. I've been going to him several times due to my foot issue and we are taking it step by step. He doesn't just write you a prescription which I hate taking pills. ,Doctor Alavynejad has always been gracious, professional, and keeps his appointment schedule. We would use no one else !,Great doctor,explained the procedure step by step thanks Dr.Bob.,I think he is very good at what he does! !,Made me feel like I was part of his family. Recommend Dr. Bob to all my friends and family  and I will be visiting again soon. ,GREAT DOC AND A GREAT GUY... TRULY CONCERNED WITH HIS PATIENT'S WELFARE AND IMPROVING THEIR CONDITION..,Extremely friendly, patient and thorough. He made my daughter very comfortable and took his time explaining the injury so we could clearly understand the best treatment options. This is the first time ever rating a doctor and we couldn't have started out with a better person. Thank you so much for taking care of my daughter. She can't wait to get back to playing soccer!!!,We were extremely happy with the whole experience at the doctors office. Felt like the way doctor's took care of patience in the old days !! Thanks for restoring our faith..Dorothy Hansen.,The Doctor was very nice and knowledgeable. We will definitely return for more care in the future !!,He was very informative and gave me several options as to what to do about my condition. ,Dr Alvavynejad was very friendly and professional. Right away he put me at ease and explained what my problem was and the procedure he was going to do. He is very passionate about his work and his patients comfort. I would recommend him to anyone with foot aliments. I know I will be going back to him for my foot care. ,Very professional  I soon as I walk in I thought I made the right choice, he's staff is great and  make me feel welcome. ,He is very caring and has the patient's interest at heart.,The doctor is very personable, knowledgeable and very thorough. The office visit was a pleasant experience, and I felt I was in good professional hands. I was nervous about my condition, but he put me at ease right away.  I  highly recommend Dr. Alavy. ,NA,NA,NA

name: Dr. Edward Nejat
og:description: Dr. Nejat is an accomplished reproductive endocrinology and infertility specialist who considers the doctor-patient relationship to be paramount. He believes that spending adequate time with his patients, being accessible to answer their questions, and having empathy, in addition to possessing exceptional clinical ability are crucial to his ability to provide state-of-the-art medical care. His particular areas of scientific interest include repeated implantation failure, unexplained infertility, reproductive surgery, diminished ovarian reserve and oocyte cryopreservation. He has received numerous awards and has published widely in the field of reproductive endocrinology and infertility with contributions to scientific journals including The New England Journal of Medicine, Human Reproduction, Fertility and Sterility and The Journal of Clinical Oncology. He has presented his work at national and international academic conferences and various media outlets have reported on his research including the BBC, The Telegraph, Medscape, Pregnancy.org and IVF.net. Dr. Nejat has spent the vast majority of his academic and professional career in New York City. He received his bachelor’s degree in biology from New York University’s College of Arts and Science, his medical degree from Weill Cornell Medical College and his masters in business administration from The Johnson School of Management of Cornell University. He then completed residency in obstetrics and gynecology at NewYork-Presbyterian Hospital – Weill Cornell and his fellowship in reproductive endocrinology and infertility at the Albert Einstein College of Medicine. He was part of a Manhattan private practice prior to joining Neway.

review_text:
I was unfortunately late to my appt but was seen very quickly. He was very sweet and nice to talk to. I didnt feel weird or uncomfortable, he addressed my issues and talk me through all the steps we where going to go through. And the office is absolutely beautiful, the staff was nice an sweet as well. ,He was extremely informative, professional and listened very well. What an awesome experience! He preformed blood work, ultrasound and genetic testing. The consultation was thorough. Excellent doctor!,Dr. Nejat is the best doctor and his office was the best medical experience we've had in NYC. He has great bedside manner, is knowledgable and thorough, and compassionate. I would highly recommend him to anyone seeking fertility treatment, or in our case, just answers and reassurance around our genetic and reproductive health. Once we got pregnant, he continued to stay with us until our 9th week, and I was so grateful for the continued weekly monitoring and care during those very scare first weeks. ,Dr Nejat is very professional and thorough in his diagnosis. He is one of the best OBGYN I have consulted with and I have seen more than 10 in the last 5 years. You get the sense that he cares about you and genuine in his concern. Highly recommended.,Awesome,Dr. Nejat is a great listener, has an impressive pedigree and seemed genuinely excited to answer our questions. What more could we ask for?,It was a pleasant visit.  The check-in process was discreet and smooth.  Waiting time was less than a few minutes.  
Dr. Nejat greeted me at the waiting room, we went over some medical history, family background, life style, the reason of the visit.  
He was very attentive, great listener, engaging and professional.  
He explained to me about his practice, the procedure of each fertility treatment option, the rough estimates, what might be involved in the process, etc.  It was a very informative consultation. 

After the consultation, he performed an ultra sound and blood tests to determine my wellness state as well as what the next step might be.  

I'm waiting for the lab results.  But I can tell you that my visit to Dr. Nejat was very helpful, informative, and I really appreciate that he treats his patients with such warm, kind but in very honest and realistic manner.    

I highly recommend Dr. Nejat!
 ,Very professional. Thank you.,I found Dr. Nejat here on ZocDoc. I can highly recommend him for fertility consultations and treatments. Very knowledgeable and excellent bedside manners. ,great demeanor.  made me feel at ease!,My visit with Dr. Nejat was phenomenal! He is an excellent listener. He's patient, caring, and very understanding. I knew I was in the best of care the moment I met him. I was very well-informed about my options and was able to ask all of my questions. He's one of a kind and I would recommend him to any and everyone who is interested in learning more about fertility options. In addition, his staff is just as wonderful...very gentle and pleasant!,Dr. Nejat is fantastic. I was nervous before meeting him, but he was incredibly understanding and very informative. I learned a lot and very much look forward to working with him. Phenomenal bedside manner.,This is hands down the best doctor I've ever seen in my life. Period. Loved my experience and the staff it's also great!,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

review_text:
Dr. Dale is always accommodating, friendly, and knowledgeable. He will work with your schedule and base your treatment around your specific needs. He doesn't unnecessarily give X-Rays and tends to plan according to how well you respond to treatment versus having a set criteria for everyone. ,I've been twice so far for horrible sciatic pain. The first time, Dale reached out and offered me an earlier appointment so I wouldn't have to wait three more days, and when I arrived I literally did not have to wait at all. The other patients leaving seemed happy, and I see why. I felt very well taken care of, he explained why I have pain and what he was doing to help, and gave me a very reasonable timeline for what to expect. I've left my two appointments with less pain and honestly, he's so friendly and kind and it's very refreshing.By his interactions with other patients, he seems to show interest in their lives. I realize this all sounds like it is too good to be true, but it isn't! So glad I found him, I would trust him anytime with my chiropractic needs. ,Great experience!  This was my first visit to a Chiripractor. Dr. Zuehlke got me right in, performed a consultation, a treatment to alleviate my back pain, and immediately started a corrective program to get my back in alignment.
My back already feels much better!   ,Dr. Dale Zuehlke is absolutely great! I made the appointment through ZocDoc after injuring my lower back, and he was able to get me in that day and even contacted me saying I could come early. He is very personable and truly cares about his patients, so much so he gave me a follow up call to make sure everything was getting better the next day. Overall, really great and glad I found him! ,Dr. Zuehlke was great! He saw me due super last minute over a weekend after I hurt my lower back exercising. He gave me an adjustment and electric stim which almost immediately made the pain decrease. He also gave me his mobile number to contact him if anything should go wrong between then and my next appointment! He comes highly recommended from me.,Never been to a chiropractor before. Great Experience. Felt great leaving the office. ,Dale is very personable and caring, you will not only enjoy your visit but also walk out of there feeling much improved! ,My previous doctor in SF was the team doctor for Saudi Arabian Olympians and I have been having a hard time to fine a good doctor in Chicago. Needless to say that Dr. Zuelker took care of my serious neck pain right away, he was really listening and attentive. I like his nice, cozy office and that I can see the doctor right away, not through a receptionist. It is very important for me to meet a doctor who enjoys his profession and Dr.Zuehlker is the one.,Awesome very personable and experienced ,I have been going to Chiropractors for over 14 years and was a personal Chiropractic assistant for two and a half years, and can easily say that Dr. Zuehlke is one of the best Chiropractors I have ever been to. It is very important for me to find a Chiropractor who understands my body and its needs, and Dr. Zuehlke clearly has an expansive knowledge, experience and expertise in Chiropractic care that he uses to identify your most troubled areas and find the best solution to treat them. ,Dr. Zuehlke is a total pro. He efficiently made adjustments to my back, telling me the whole time what he was doing and why it would be helpful. He is also very friendly and thoughtful--we had gotten to talking about making bread at our first appointment and the next time I went in, he had brought the recipe we had discussed. I would totally recommend Dr. Zuehlke to a friend. ,Dr. Dale was great! He was able to see me right away. Very professional and knowledgeable. He solved my issues right away. I would definitely recommend him to everyone. ,First appointment was great. He started by asking questions to learn more about my situation, gave me an adjustment, and then finished with electric stim. My back literally feels 10x better today. He has a massage therapist that will stretch you out which I'm also looking forward to. ,Dale is excellent. Very great communicator, and his only goal is to get you the best care out there. Very accommodating schedules, and will work with your insurance to make sure that you are getting exactly what you ask for. I had never worked with a chiropractor before, but it is making all the difference. ,No wait time for treatment, walked in and went through process. Very informative on what he was doing and why, filled me in on what his opinion was and made me feel comfortable. Overall good experience and timely on the process. Definitely would recommend if looking for a chiropractor.,Very friendly and personable. Provided thorough explanations of his methodology and practices. All-around a great experience. ,FANTASTIC! CANNOT WAIT TO WORK WITH HIM!,He is so positive, gentle and fun to be with.,Super friendly and helpful,He greeted me as soon as I walked in. He is great! Very professional.,I arrived to my appt a few minutes as early, as I was a new patient, & was greeted by the doctor immediately. He even knew my name before I could tell him! Instantly, the comfort level was there. He asked all of the right questions, and was attentive to me the entire time. A great first experience, and I look forward to having Dale as my new chiropractor. ,Dr. Dale has been great to me! The office is beautiful and the front office staff and nurse were very kind and professional. Everything is done electronically and efficiently . I had a great first experience. ,Very thorough and knowledge about my health issue.   He and office staff very professional. ,Dr. Chrzan was extremely thorough for my first visit. I would highly recommend this medical group!,Dr. Chrzan was very patient, thorough and caring and he seems knowledgeable. His office is very nice and tech-savvy. name: Dr. Syed Iman Husain
og:description: Dr. Syed Iman Husain is a mindful and compassionate cardiologist serving the communities of Middle Village and Jamaica, NY. Dr. Husain obtained his medical degree from the Ross University School of Medicine. He completed his residency in Internal Medicine at Maimonides Medical Center, where he was awarded as resident of the month. He also completed a fellowship in Interventional Cardiology and in General Cardiovascular disease at the same institute. He also spent a year at The Texas Heart Institute which is a world renowned institute where he finished a post doctoral fellowship in Advanced Heart Failure and Cardiac Transplant. Dr. Husain is a part of Hope Medical Services PC. He is board certified in Internal Medicine, Cardiovascular disease, Advanced Heart Failure and Transplant Cardiology and Interventional Cardiology by the American Board of Internal Medicine. He is a member of the American College of Cardiology, the American College of Physicians, and the International Society for Heart and Lung Transplantation. Dr. Husain is fluent in English, Hindi, Urdu and Farsi. His awareness of these different languages makes him accessible to patients from a variety of cultural backgrounds. Outside of his practice he loves reading, traveling, teaching, cricket and soccer. Dr. Husain is dedicated to helping patients receive the treatment they need so they can enjoy a positive and fulfilling lifestyle.

He completed his residency in Internal Medicine at Maimonides Medical Center, where he was awarded as resident of the month. He also completed a fellowship in Interventional Cardiology and in General Cardiovascular disease at the same institute. He also spent a year at The Texas Heart Institute which is a world renowned institute where he finished a post doctoral fellowship in Advanced Heart Failure and Cardiac Transplant. Dr. Husain is a part of Hope Medical Services PC. He is board certified in Internal Medicine, Cardiovascular disease, Advanced Heart Failure and Transplant Cardiology and Interventional Cardiology by the American Board of Internal Medicine. He is a member of the American College of Cardiology, the American College of Physicians, and the International Society for Heart and Lung Transplantation. Dr. Husain is fluent in English, Hindi, Urdu and Farsi. His awareness of these different languages makes him accessible to patients from a variety of cultural backgrounds. Outside of his practice he loves reading, traveling, teaching, cricket and soccer. Dr. Husain is dedicated to helping patients receive the treatment they need so they can enjoy a positive and fulfilling lifestyle.

board_cert: Aetna,Blue Cross Blue Shield of Michigan,Davis Vision,,
name: Dr. Cindy Wang
og:description: Dr. Cindy Wang received her Doctor of Optometry from the University of California, Berkeley. Her training includes rotations at American Lake VA Hospital in Washington and Cedars Sinai in Los Angeles. Dr. Cindy Wand has spent the majority of her career working alongside ophthalmologists practicing medical optometry. Dr. Cindy Wang is a Michigan native and graduate of University of Michigan, Ann Arbor. Dr. Wang was happy to return to her home state and joined the staff at Eye Surgery Institute in Dearborn, Michigan in 2002. She enjoys family eye care, treating patients of all ages. Dr. Cindy Wang provides well vision exams, glasses examinations, contact lens examinations, low vision examinations and treats medical eye problems. Dr. Cindy Wang truly takes the time to get to know her patients and ensures that each patient receives the quality attention they deserve.   Dr. Wang also has special interests in innovative treatments such as Corneal Refractive Therapy (CRT) for non-surgical, overnight myopia correction and Synergeyes hybrid contact lenses. She is very experienced in specialty contact lens fits for keratoconus, post-RK, post-LASIK, and corneal ectasia. For those struggling with vision loss from conditions such as macular degeneration, glaucoma, and diabetes, Dr. Wang provides low vision services. As her patients already know, Dr. Wang dedicates her time away from the office to her husband and two young children. She is also an active supporter of Food Allergy and Anaphylaxis Network (FAAN) in hopes that someday there will be a cure for life threatening food allergies. She is a top fundraiser for FAAN’s annual Food Walk.

name: Courtney McMillian
og:description: Courtney McMillian is a Certified Nurse Midwife and Advanced Registered Nurse Practitioner.  She received her Master’s degree from the University of Florida after ten years of labor and delivery nursing. Courtney completed her undergraduate studies at Duke University where she graduated with high honors. She is a member of the American College of Nurse Midwives. Courtney enjoys caring for women of all ages, from adolescence through menopause. Her special interests include pregnancy counseling, birth support, and breastfeeding promotion and assistance. She believes each woman should be supported and empowered to safely achieve the type of birth experience that is right for her. She is proud to provide VBAC deliveries to those women who desire vaginal childbirth after having had a prior cesarean section delivery.

The office is very clean and the staff is very friendly.,The visit was very professional.  I felt very comfortable with her.  She  did several adjustments and I felt so much better after.  I will see her again.,I loved her style and professionalism.,Dr. Edwards is so unbelievably personable. I had worked for a Chiropractor some years ago and it was a bad experience, so I avoided going to a chiropractor for years. After my husband saw her and raved about her, I thought I would take the plunge. I'm so glad I did. She isn't like other chiropractors. She doesn't order unnecessary x-rays. She doesn't create expensive treatment plans. She works with your insurance company and what it covers to determine the best treatment plan that is also wallet friendly. The service is dynamic in that it includes massage therapy and treatment with the tens unit and rolling table (my absolute favorite). I went it about my posture and she suggested a really low cost and highly effective way of keeping my posture in check that didn't require an uncomfortable back brace. I'm really happy my husband found her and I look forward to my visits with her each week. ,Very friendly and great bedside manner.  Looking forward to my neck and back not hurting anymore.,Very kind and patient. Sometimes wasn't clear about exactly what I was supposed to be doing next in treatments but definitely helped with my pain and discomfort.,She is fantastic! Very smart and very friendly. ,Nicole was super nice and easy to talk to, I'd definitely see her again!,Very satisfied service. My neck pain was improved already after first visit.,My experience was amazing. I have had dull low back pain for over a month now, and it came to a breaking point. So I scheduled a consultation here based on the ratings they had. My wait was not that long at all. I was taken for an evaluation, and she immediately had a plan to get me relief. She put me on Stem and the Rolly table that day, and then adjusted me and worked on some tight muscles. I was treated so well. I can't wait to continue my treatment here. ,She was perfect. The best chiropractor Ive ever been to.

name: Dr. Susan Hunter
og:description: My philosophy for patient care is to treat every patient as if they were a member of my family. I listen to your concerns and address them. I will give you all your options, including ones that I may not be able to offer. I will address all of your questions and help you take the best care of yourself possible. I was born and raised in Phoenix, Arizona. My dad was an electrician and my mom stayed at home to raise me and my two sisters. We are one-quarter Hispanic on my mom's side, with lots of Padillas and Reynosos in the family, mostly now in California, but previously from Aguas Calientes and Tijuana, Mexico. I do speak medical Spanish. I graduated summa cum laude and phi beta kappa from Arizona State University and attended Northwestern University Medical School, followed by OB/Gyn residency at UTMB-Galveston. Upon graduation in 1997, I moved to Harlingen to practice with Dr. Ruben Martinez who was one of my surgical instructors in residency. I am fully board certified in OB/Gyn, am currently an Assistant Professor of OB/Gyn for UT San Antonio Health Sciences Center and previously also at UTMB Galveston. As a physician, I enjoy helping women throughout their lives, participating in the incredible miracle of childbirth, and doing cutting edge surgery to help women recover as rapidly and painlessly as possible. The daVinci surgical system offers another choice to avoid a large incision on the abdomen for many women who otherwise would have no other alternative. I feel it is important to give back to the profession and community. Helping care for lower income women through South Texas Hospital and teaching medical students, residents, and pa/nurse practitioner students is my way of doing this.

og:description: Dr. Shire became a chiropractor in 1999 after graduating cum laude from Life University in Georgia. He is also a fellow with the International Chiropractic Pediatric Association (ICPA). Dr. Shire was drawn to the profession due to his fascination with and respect for the body and its ability to heal and perform without having to use drugs or surgery. Dr. Shire's practice is located in the prestigious Midtown Integrative Health and Wellness Center. A progressive Health office offering numerous specialties all designed to improve your health. The office is designed to provide a "Concierge Style" of health care where all your needs are anticipated and exceeded. Dr. Shire is also a Certified Health coach and offers the Take Shape for Life optimal health and weight loss program. A medically supervised system to achieve, not only weight loss but a full integration of the Habits of health. Our office happily accepts many insurance plans on an out of network basis. Simply call or email the office with your insurance Id# and date of birth and we will be happy to verify your insurance beneifts with you.

name: Dr. Anita Carleo
og:description: Dr. Anita Carleo, therapeutic optometrist and glaucoma specialist, was born and raised in Dallas where she attended the Hockaday School for 14 years. She completed her undergraduate studies at Austin College in Sherman, TX and received her doctorate of optometry degree at the University of Houston College of Optometry (UHCO). During her career, Dr. Anita Carleo has continued to gain invaluable knowledge and experience in the management of many ocular diseases, including dry eye, glaucoma, macular degeneration, and diabetic retinopathy. She believes that prevention is key and has developed relationships with surgeons and physicians to help co-manage her patients. She, of course, continues to love the “bread and butter” of optometry; that is, comprehensive eye examinations for both glasses and contact lenses to help all ages see better in their daily lives. She works with her patients to find the best options to suit their lifestyle and recreational activities needs, whether it be that perfect pair of glasses or a specialty multifocal contact lens for freedom and flexibility. Dr. Anita is ready to embark on the new practice she is opening with her sister, Dr. Olivia Carleo. As a family practice, she is excited about being able to provide her patients with the care and attention she would want afforded to any of her own family members. She feels strongly that patients deserve a doctor who will listen to their problems, address and treat their issues, and spend the time needed to answer any and all questions. Dr. Anita Carleo was awarded the Ocular Instruments Award of Excellence for Outstanding Performance in the Study of Ocular Disease. She is a proud member of the Beta Sigma Kappa optometric honor society, the American Optometric Association (AOA), Texas Optometry Association (TOA), Dallas County Optometric Society (DCOS), and Vision Source. In her free time, Dr. Anita enjoys spending time with her husband, family, and friends. She loves to travel and enjoys reading and outdoor activities such as skiing and summer water sports.

name: Dr. Omar Awar
og:description: Dr. Awar is a Southeast Texas native who spent most of his childhood in Beaumont, Texas. He received a Bachelor of Arts with High Honors from Washington University in St. Louis, Missouri. Dr. Awar earned his medical degree from Baylor College of Medicine and went on to complete his Internship and Residency at UCLA Medical Center in Los Angeles, California. He returned to the Texas Medical Center to complete his General Cardiology and Interventional Cardiology training at Baylor College of Medicine, where he served as both Chief General Cardiology Fellow and Chief Interventional Cardiology Fellow. Dr. Awar received numerous awards, including "Most Outstanding Clinical Cardiology Fellow" for three consecutive years. He was the recipient of the prestigious Richard Van Reet Award for his dedication, skill and excellence as a clinician and teacher. Dr. Awar is board certified in Internal Medicine, General Cardiology and Interventional Cardiology. He additionally holds board certification in Echocardiography and Nuclear Cardiology. Dr. Awar’s clinical cardiology practice is dedicated to advancing cardiac patient care with special interests in the management of coronary artery disease, peripheral artery disease and valvular heart disease. He is able to offer state-of-the-art care in the treatment of complex coronary disease and specializes in performing heart catheterizations through the wrist (radial approach). His research interests include platelet reactivity and anti-platelet therapy after coronary stenting. Dr. Awar has strong interest in academic medicine and regularly participates in fellow education and has presented at national cardiology conferences.

name: Dr. Omar Awar
og:description: Dr. Awar is a Southeast Texas native who spent most of his childhood in Beaumont, Texas. He received a Bachelor of Arts with High Honors from Washington University in St. Louis, Missouri. Dr. Awar earned his medical degree from Baylor College of Medicine and went on to complete his Internship and Residency at UCLA Medical Center in Los Angeles, California. He returned to the Texas Medical Center to complete his General Cardiology and Interventional Cardiology training at Baylor College of Medicine, where he served as both Chief General Cardiology Fellow and Chief Interventional Cardiology Fellow. Dr. Awar received numerous awards, including "Most Outstanding Clinical Cardiology Fellow" for three consecutive years. He was the recipient of the prestigious Richard Van Reet Award for his dedication, skill and excellence as a clinician and teacher. Dr. Awar is board certified in Internal Medicine, General Cardiology and Interventional Cardiology. He additionally holds board certification in Echocardiography and Nuclear Cardiology. Dr. Awar’s clinical cardiology practice is dedicated to advancing cardiac patient care with special interests in the management of coronary artery disease, peripheral artery disease and valvular heart disease. He is able to offer state-of-the-art care in the treatment of complex coronary disease and specializes in performing heart catheterizations through the wrist (radial approach). His research interests include platelet reactivity and anti-platelet therapy after coronary stenting. Dr. Awar has strong interest in academic medicine and regularly participates in fellow education and has presented at national cardiology conferences.

og:description: Dr. Vojislav Lazarevic is a smart and mindful internist serving the community of Chicago, IL. Dr. Lazarevic attended the University of Belgrade Faculty of Medicine, where he received his medical degree, and completed his residency in internal medicine at Saint Joseph Hospital in Chicago. Dr. Lazarevic is a part of Presence Medical Group - Internal Medicine. Patients see Dr. Lazarevic for a variety of reasons, including illness. He speaks English, Serbian, Bosnian, Croatian, and Serbo-Croatian fluently, which makes him widely accessible to patients from a variety of cultural backgrounds. He is board certified by the American Board of Internal Medicine. His areas of special interest include cholesterol problems, diabetes, hypertension, preventive care, and care of geriatric patients. Dr. Lazarevic is dedicated to helping patients receive the treatment they need so they can enjoy a positive and fulfilling lifestyle.

name: Dr. Feryal Hajee
og:description: After completing Medical school at Ross University, Dr Feryal Hajee went on to perform her internship at the State University of New York Health Science Center at Brooklyn, where she was awarded “Intern of the Year”. She then completed her residency training in Internal Medicine and then fellowship training in adult and pediatric Allergy and clinical Immunology also at SUNY Downstate Medical Center. She is board certified in both Internal Medicine and Allergy and Immunology. She was clinical assistant professor at SUNY Downstate Medical School where she taught and trained medical students and residents. She has been recognized as one of “America’s Top Physicians”, 2009 and continues to reach out to patients by lecturing at schools and community centers to educate and screen people for chronic illnesses such as asthma. Dr Hajee has researched in several areas with publications in prestigious journals such as the Journal of Allergy and Clinical Immunology as well as the Annals of Clinical & Laboratory Science. She is also a member of the American Academy of Allergy, Asthma and Immunology. Dr Hajee has had several expert guest appearances in the media including Channel 12 news, PRN Desi and Dhoom FM, discussing various issues on Asthma and Allergies. Dr. Hajee has over 8 years in this profession and has treated many patients with asthma, allergies and immunology disorders.

og:description: Dr. Karen Salazar Valdes was born in Peru and was raised in Miami. She completed her undergraduate education at the University of Miami, obtaining a bachelorÃ¢??s degree in Religious Studies, Biology and Chemistry in 2004.  She pursued her dream and earned her medical degree from Ross University School of Medicine in 2008. In 2013 she completed her OBGYN residency at Jackson Memorial Hospital, University of Miami and joined our practice. She is happy to be working in the area she grew up in and is currently taking new patients.  Her interests include adolescent GYN, obstetrics and preventive women's health care.  She enjoys family time, traveling, boating and running. She is fluent in English and Spanish. She has a special interest in kids and adults with intellectual disabilities and is a supporter for Best Buddies International.

name: Dr. Alexander Brun
og:description: Dr. Alexander Brun is a patient-oriented and dedicated doctor who specializes in colon cancer screening, irritable bowel syndrome, chronic abdominal pain, inflammatory bowel disease, gastroesophageal reflux disease and diseases of the liver and pancreas. He obtained his medical degree from SUNY Downstate Medical School and completed his internal medicine residency training in Rutgers Robert Wood Johnson University Hospital where he was elected as outstanding resident of the year. Dr. Brun served as chief gastroenterology fellow at North Shore Long Island Jewish Health System, which is where he completed his gastroenterology training. Dr. Brun is now an attending at Mount Sinai Beth Israel.  He has published in numerous medical journals and gastroenterology textbooks on topics ranging from gastrointestinal bleeding to geriatric gastroenterology. He and his staff speak English, Spanish and Russian.

I would highly recommend.,He is very sweet and gears your concerns thoroughly,  and answers them. ,He is great!  ,My appointment for Dr Brun was for a colonoscopy / endoscopy.
I waited for about 30 minutes then was prepared for the two procedures. I was done in about 30 minutes, then waited for the anesthesia to wear off.  Meanwhile Dr. Brun discussed the results with me, then I was on my way. HIs professional staff also made the visit pleasant.
 ,Dr. Brun seems very knowledgeable and easily approachable. However, two hours is way too long of a wait for an 8:30 am appointment. 
Also, the restroom in the waiting/reception  area was ATROCIOUS!  It was unclean and there was no paper. Unacceptable for a doctor's office. ,Doctor is very good and I would definitely recommend him,Dr Brun is excellent doctor! Very pleasant, polite and professional. He responded to all my questions. It feels like he really love his job and his patients. Highly recommend him to everyone! 
The wait time was indecently long, but I guess it can happen everywhere and even that didnt spoil my visit to Dr Brun, because he was great. ,Dr. Brun is an excellent doctor who alleviated two problems I had effortlessly. He has an excellent bed side manner, explains everything coherently and takes the time out to answer any and all questions. ,Great Doctor. Explained well and takes the timeout to make you feel welcomed.,My first visit to Dr Alex Brun was a pleasurable one. Dr. Brun  was very attentive when I was talking about my issue. Responded to any and all concerns I had with care and detailed explanations.  Made me feel very comfortable to talk about things that normally are uncomfortable to talk about. He was very professional and well mannered. 
The staff at the reception area were very pleasant and professional as well.  The wait was about 15 minutes or so. 
Over all a five star experience.  I highly recommend Dr. Alexander Brun. ,The wait time was basically none and the was out fairly quickly  can't rush when it comes to your health. ,I had an endoscopy procedure. Dr. Brun Is definitely very knowledgable and professional! He is also  polite, conscientious and thorough in his work! The office is very clean and neat, the staff is very attentive and responsive. The  wait was only about 5-7 minutes. I am very happy with this experience, and would definitely recommend Dr Brun to all my friends. ,The whole staff was pretty nice. The wait time sucks a little, because you end up waiting about 30 mins or more. But Dr.  Brun was great. I would def recommend seeing him. ,Dr.Brun is excellent,He is really a good doctor. Wait time was to much however I understand things happen. ,The staff were great but the wait time needs improvement. I would def recommend them to my friends. ,Dr Brun and staff are very friendly and nice! Everything is quick, no waiting and atmosphere is good. ,A very pleasant and caring doctor. name: Dr. Alexander Brun
og:description: Dr. Alexander Brun is a patient-oriented and dedicated doctor who specializes in colon cancer screening, irritable bowel syndrome, chronic abdominal pain, inflammatory bowel disease, gastroesophageal reflux disease and diseases of the liver and pancreas. He obtained his medical degree from SUNY Downstate Medical School and completed his internal medicine residency training in Rutgers Robert Wood Johnson University Hospital where he was elected as outstanding resident of the year. Dr. Brun served as chief gastroenterology fellow at North Shore Long Island Jewish Health System, which is where he completed his gastroenterology training. Dr. Brun is now an attending at Mount Sinai Beth Israel.  He has published in numerous medical journals and gastroenterology textbooks on topics ranging from gastrointestinal bleeding to geriatric gastroenterology. He and his staff speak English, Spanish and Russian.

name: Dr. David Boguslavsky
og:description: David  Boguslavsky, MD is an experienced and dedicated family physician and medical acupuncturist who has been practicing medicine for more than a decade.  Dr. Boguslavsky is originally from Russia and at  young age moved to New Jersey where he not only attended medical school but established his medical practice.  Dr. Boguslavsky received his medical degree from Robert Wood Johnson Medical School and completed his residency training at Somerset Family Practice, where he was presented with multiple Resident Teacher of The Year awards.  He underwent extensive additional training in Medical Acupuncture at the prestigious UCLA Helms Medical Acupuncture Institute in Berkley, California.  Dr. Boguslavsky is Board Certified in Family Medicine and in Medical Acupuncture, a unique achievement. At the root of Dr. Boguslavsky’ s holistic approach to medicine lies a belief that there is much more to being healthy than just preventing being sick. The doctor's function is to support the patient during his or her life journey, and to make sure that the patient is in the best physical, emotional and spiritual health they can be.  Dr. Boguslavsky practices the full spectrum of Family medicine and sees his patients for acute illness (such as headaches, sinus infections) as well for chronic conditions management (thyroid, hypertension, diabetes, cholesterol). Every patient of the practice benefits from his unique dual perspective, offered by Western and Eastern Medicine. Some patients walk away with a medication, whereas others leave reassured, and improved with some Chinese Herbal  Medicines or a few well-chosen acupuncture needles. Additionally, Dr. Boguslavsky specializes in treating patients with pain and functional disorders.   There is a great emphasis in the practice on preventative care and on early control of risk factors, vitamin and mineral deficiencies diet-related imbalances. Finally, it is important to stress how much PremierMD and Dr. Boguslavsky embrace the latest in medical technology. From using the state-of-the-art Electronic Medical Record (EMR), to digital prescriptions, to a user-friendly Patient Portal the patients reap the benefits of the technological advances in medical care. Despite adopting the modern approach to medical information, Dr. Boguslavsky continues the time-tested tenets of doctor-patient relationship: “Give every patient all the time that they need.” For example, new patients are allotted an hour to get to know the doctor and to share their medical history. Established patient visits are allotted 30 minutes. The office runs smoothly and there is rarely more than a few minutes that a patient spends in the waiting or an exam room.

name: Dr. Carol Reid
og:description: Dr. Carol Reid is a skilled and detail-oriented ear, nose & throat doctor serving the community of Denver, CO. Dr. Reid attended the University of Wisconsin where she received her medical degree, and completed her residencies in otolaryngology and general surgery at Oregon Health & Science University. She is board certified by the American Board of Otolaryngology and is a member of the American Academy of Otolaryngology – Head and Neck Surgery, the Denver Medical Society, and the Colorado Medical Society. Patients see Dr. Reid for a variety of reasons, including allergy consultations, filler treatments, ENT consultations, vertigo, and allergic cough. Patients trust Dr. Reid's expertise because she consistently provides high quality care that leads to positive and lasting health outcomes.

name: Dr. Peter Stone
og:description: Peter L. Stone, MD, board certified since 1986, has practiced all aspects of urology for over 25 years with specific emphasis on management of kidney stones, urinary incontinence, erectile dysfunction, and prostate and bladder cancer. For the past ten years, Dr. Stone has been consistently listed in Castle Connolly’s Best Doctors in the New York Metro Area. He has also been listed several times in New York Magazine’s list of Best Doctors, as recently as the 2009 edition. Dr. Stone received his AB degree from Hamilton College, MD degree from New York Medical College. He completed his residency in urology at Montefiore Medical Center that included training at Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Center. He is presently Chief of Urology at Westchester Square Medical Center in the Bronx, and operates, as well, at all divisions of Montefiore Medical Center. As an Assistant Clinical Professor of Urology at the Albert Einstein College of Medicine, Dr. Stone is privileged to teach urology residents and medical students. Dr. Stone is a member of the American Urological Association (AUA), the New York Section of the AUA, the New York State Medical Society, and the Bronx County Medical Society.

name: Dr. Katherine (Katie) Babaliaros
og:description: *Please note: Please arrive 20 minutes prior to your appointment time and bring your insurance ID card. A native of Louisville, Kentucky, Dr. Katie Babaliaros is a Phi Beta Kappa graduate of Emory College where she received a B.S. in neuroscience and behavioral biology. She simultaneously earned a medical degree from the Emory University School of Medicine  and a master’s degree in public health from the Rollins School of Public Health before completing a residency in obstetrics and gynecology at Emory. During her residency, she  was named Outstanding Resident in Maternal Fetal Medicine, Gynecologic Oncology and Continuity Clinic. She is a member of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology and the Georgia Obstetrical Gynecologic Society.  She began her career in private practice in 2014 and joined Peachtree Women’s Specialists in March, 2015.   Dr. Babaliaros has a special interest in adolescent gynecology, contraceptive management, minimally invasive gynecologic surgery and high-risk pregnancy. She is certified to place Mirena and Paragard IUDs and the contraceptive insert Nexplanon.

name: Dr. Katherine (Katie) Babaliaros
og:description: *Please note: Please arrive 20 minutes prior to your appointment time and bring your insurance ID card. A native of Louisville, Kentucky, Dr. Katie Babaliaros is a Phi Beta Kappa graduate of Emory College where she received a B.S. in neuroscience and behavioral biology. She simultaneously earned a medical degree from the Emory University School of Medicine  and a master’s degree in public health from the Rollins School of Public Health before completing a residency in obstetrics and gynecology at Emory. During her residency, she  was named Outstanding Resident in Maternal Fetal Medicine, Gynecologic Oncology and Continuity Clinic. She is a member of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology and the Georgia Obstetrical Gynecologic Society.  She began her career in private practice in 2014 and joined Peachtree Women’s Specialists in March, 2015.   Dr. Babaliaros has a special interest in adolescent gynecology, contraceptive management, minimally invasive gynecologic surgery and high-risk pregnancy. She is certified to place Mirena and Paragard IUDs and the contraceptive insert Nexplanon.

name: Dr. Luis Lu
og:description: Dr. Lu graduated from Columbia University in New York and founded the renowned Elk County Eye Clinic / Pennsylvania Eye Consultants in Pennsylvania. He relocated to Chandler, AZ where he founded Eye Consultants of Arizona, and still provides patients with compassionate, quality care. Dr. Lu formerly served as an instructor at the University of Pittsburgh and is an Honorary Professor of Ophthalmology at the CH Peruvian University School of Medicine. Dr. Lu is proudly certified by the American Board of Ophthalmology and the American Board of Eye Surgery. He has written 3 books, and contributed to 25 chapters for other texts on ophthalmic medicine.   Dr. Lu is also a native Peruvian and a member of the Arizona Latin-American Medical Association. He is the only fluent Spanish-speaking ophthalmologist in the Phoenix area. Certified Ophthalmologist Quality eye care services “We loved having Dr. Lu take care of our eye problem.”   – Marty & Mary I., via Vitals.com  Universidad Peruana Cayetano Heredia College Luis Washington Lu, M.D. is a double board-certified ophthalmologist by the American Academy of Ophthalmology and American Board of Eye Surgery,  founder of the Elk County Eye Clinic / Pennsylvania Eye Consultants, and the new Eye Consultants of Arizona, a state-of-the-art eye disease consultation facility. A vision correction expert, Dr. Lu specializes in complex eye surgeries. He has been listed in as one of the "Top Eye Surgeons" in the entire country. Dr. Luis Lu is widely regarded as a "Doctor's Doctor."   Over the course of his career he has been honored with awards from the American Academy of Ophthalmology, American Society of Cataract and Refractive Surgery, The Keratomileusis Study Group, The Nikon Award, the Peruvian College of Surgeons, the Argentinian Society of Ophthalmology, the Colombian Society, Mexican Society, and many other organizations. He is regularly invited to teach eye surgeons at major conferences and specialized forums. Dr. Lu's prominent standing in the field of eye surgery is well balanced by his impeccable bedside manner and gentle touch, which continue to attract patients from around the Phoenix area. Dr. Lu has dedicated his career to the latest advancements, education and research in the field of eye surgery. He has designed award-winning ophthalmic surgical instruments, written three textbooks in eye surgery, over 25 chapters for ophthalmic books, about 500 articles in continuing medical education for ophthalmologists, and his work has been published in some of the most prestigious medical journals nationwide.   Married to Laura E. Lu, RN, CRNO, have two children, Architect L. Michael Lu and future Doctor Andrew N. Lu.

name: Dr. Sarah Chewerda
og:description: Dr. Sarah Chewerda is a qualified and diligent optometrist based in Portland, OR. Dr. Chewerda attended Pacific University, where she received her degree in optometry. She received her bachelor’s degree from the University of Saskatchewan.  Dr. Chewerda is a part of Alberta Eye Care. She is a member of the American Optometric Association, the Oregon Optometric Physician’s Association, and the Portland Metro Optometric Association. Because Dr. Chewerda is bilingual in English and French, patients from a variety of backgrounds enjoy having her as their physician. Dr. Chewerda believes in listening to each patient and creating a partnership to maintain and improve lifelong health.

name: Samantha Alburn
og:description: Samantha Alburn is a Family Nurse Practitioner and is nationally certified by the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners.  She enjoys seeing all different types of patients.  Samantha is a big believer of individual treatment plans and personalized care.   For her undergraduate degree, Samantha attended Cal Poly, San Luis Obispo, where she graduated cum laude and earned her Bachelor of Science degree in Biological Sciences. Following graduation, she began her nursing career by becoming a certified nursing assistant.  Samantha then attended CSU Los Angeles, where she graduated with honors and earned her Master of Science degree in Nursing.  At CSU Los Angeles, Samantha was an active member of the Sigma Theta Tau honor society of nursing.  She is currently an active member of the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners and the California Association of Nurse Practitioners. Samantha has completed clinical rotations at various medical offices and clinics in Southern California. She has trained for over one year with Dr. Michael Marsh at PMCB. She also has extensive clinical experience working closely with a host of specialists, including ENT and dermatology. Samantha was born and raised in Visalia, CA. Her hobbies include reading novels, traveling, and spending time with family.  She loves Southern California and is honored to make a positive contribution to the community we all call our home.

name: Dr. Douglas Min
og:description: He was born and raised in Fort Wayne, Indiana.  He attended the University of Virginia in Charlottesville, Virginia where he graduated with a Bachelor of Arts in Spanish.  He then earned his medical degree from Emory University in Atlanta, Georgia in 1999.  He went on to complete his internship and residency in pediatrics at the University of Texas Southwestern, here in Dallas.  At the conclusion of his residency in 2002, Dr. Min received the inaugural White Hat Award when he was elected by his fellow graduating residents as the colleague they would most want as their own child’s pediatrician.  He then served four years in the United States Air Force at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base in Tucson, Arizona.  He received the Air Force Commendation Medal for meritorious service as a staff physician.  He also was awarded the Air Force Achievement Medal for serving as chief of medical services for a humanitarian mission to Honduras in 2004. Dr. Min completed a fellowship in allergy and immunology at UT Southwestern in 2009.  He then moved to Tucson, AZ where he worked for four years in private practice, seeing adults and children with allergies, asthma and other immunologic disorders including eczema and anaphylaxis. Dr. Min is Board Certified by the American Board of Allergy and Immunology, a conjoint Board of the American Board of Internal Medicine and the American Board of Pediatrics. Dr. Min was happy to return to Dallas is 2013.  He enjoys, sports, walking and running with his dog, Echo, and rooting for his favorite team, the Dallas Cowboys.

name: Dr. Daniel Murauski
og:description: *The practice requests at least 24 hours notice for appointment cancellations Dr. Murauski received his undergraduate degree in biomechanical engineering from the University of Illinois at Chicago.  From there, inspired by the osteopathic philosophy, he went on to medical school at Midwestern University School of Osteopathic Medicine.  Following medical school he completed a residency program in family medicine at Lutheran General Hospital in Park Ridge, IL and is now a board-certified family physician. Through his journey he developed a fondness for yoga and became intrigued by philosophies that promote wellness. Fueled by this passion, Dr. Murauski has successfully earned his certification from the American Board of Integrative and Holistic Medicine. Dr. Murauski tailors his treatment of patients around a diverse array of evidence-based therapies and integrates them safely into current Western medicine.

og:description: Dr. Robert James is a friendly pediatrician treating young patients in the greater Phoenix area. He is a member of the Arizona Chapter of the American Academy of Pediatrics. Dr. James was a member of the Residency Admissions Committee and the Medical School Admissions Committee during the nineteen-nineties. Later, he also became a PALS instructor.

name: Dr. Stephanie Lechlitner
og:description: Dr. Stephanie Lechlitner grew up in a small town in northern Indiana. She received her bachelor of science in Biology at Purdue University while playing for the women’s club soccer team. Dr. Lechlitner graduated Magna Cum Laude from the University of Houston College of Optometry. She was elected as a member of both the Beta Sigma Kappa and Gold Key International Optometric Honor Societies.  She also served as trustee for her college to the American Optometric Student Association.  Before officially moving to Austin to begin her career, she completed a year of internships in Austin, Houston, and Dallas. Dr. Lechlitner is a licensed Therapeutic Optometrist and an Optometric Glaucoma Specialist and an active member in the Texas Optometric Association, the American Optometric Association, and the Central Texas Optometric Society, where she serves as a Vice President for the Central Texas Optometric Society. When she has free time, she enjoys staying active by going to the gym, playing sports, and being on the lake. She likes watching football, hockey, and soccer. Dr. Lechlitner also likes discovering new local spots with her friends.

Before officially moving to Austin to begin her career, she completed a year of internships in Austin, Houston, and Dallas. Dr. Lechlitner is a licensed Therapeutic Optometrist and an Optometric Glaucoma Specialist and an active member in the Texas Optometric Association, the American Optometric Association, and the Central Texas Optometric Society, where she serves as a Vice President for the Central Texas Optometric Society. When she has free time, she enjoys staying active by going to the gym, playing sports, and being on the lake. She likes watching football, hockey, and soccer. Dr. Lechlitner also likes discovering new local spots with her friends.

name: Dr. Nicole Dabul
og:description: Dr. Nicole Dabul is a caring and considerate podiatrist serving the communities of Margate and Boca Raton, FL. Dr. Dabul attended Barry University, where she received her doctorate degree, and completed her residency in surgery at Westside Regional Medical Center.   Dr. Dabul is a part of Associated Foot and Ankle where she sees patients for foot problems, ankle injuries, toenail problems, and orthotics as well as other common and specialized reasons. Dr. Dabul is a member of the American Podiatric Medical Association, the American Association for Women Podiatrists, and the Florida Podiatric Medical Association. Because Dr. Dabul is bilingual in English and Spanish, patients from a variety of backgrounds enjoy having her as their physician. Dr. Dabul enjoys giving back to her community and has participated in many volunteer activities, including health fairs, the Yucatan Crippled Children’s Project, and conducted a shoe drive called Soles for Souls.   Dr. Dabul believes in listening to each patient and creating a partnership to maintain and improve lifelong health.

name: Stefanie Osterloh
og:description: If you are experiencing shortness of breath, chest pain or any other emergency, please call 911. Stefanie Osterloh is a certified nurse practitioner at the GW Family Practice of Crofton. Stefanie earned both her Master of Science in Nursing and Bachelor of Science in Nursing degrees from the University of Maryland in Baltimore.  Prior to earning her Master’s degree, she worked at Good Samaritan Hospital in the emergency department where she was nominated ‘Nurse of the Year’.  She is certified as a Family Nurse Practitioner and works with both adult and pediatric patients.  Areas of clinical interest and expertise include comprehensive physicals, women’s health, and management of chronic medical conditions including (but not limited to) diabetes, hypertension and hyperlipidemia.

name: Dr. Anna Jamrozik
og:description: Effective February 1, 2016, Stamford Health Integrated Practices Norwalk Family Practice will be changing its name to Stamford Health Medical Group. Our new name better reflects our service as a multispecialty group of more than 120 primary and specialty care providers throughout lower Fairfield County. Rest assured that although Norwalk Family Practice will discontinue its individual practice name and be known as part of Stamford Health Medical Group, the providers and staff you know and trust will remain in the same office you currently visit. Our address, phone number, and insurance will also continue as before. Dr. Anna Jamrozik has over twenty years of experience in a broad spectrum of medicine. After receiving her medical degree from Jagiellonian University School of Medicine in Krakow, Poland, she completed a Pediatric and Otolaryngological residency at the Children's Hospital in Krakow. She completed her Family Medicine residency at St. Joseph Medical Center in Reading, PA and is board certified by the American Board of Family Medicine. She is also the Assistant Clinical Professor in the Department of Family Medicine at the University of Connecticut School of Medicine. Before joining Stamford Health Integrated Practices, Dr. Jamrozik practiced at Saint Francis Care Medical Group in Ellington, CT, and prior to that she was a partner for thirteen years at Mansfield Family Practice in Storrs, CT. Dr. Jamrozik is passionate about the treatment of the whole person and practices the most up to date evidence based medicine. She is an advocate of integrative medicine including lifestyle modification, exercise, and dietary choices. Her clinical interests include women's health, pediatrics, adolescent medicine, preventive medicine, lifestyle/wellness and nutrition.

name: Dr. Adhuna Mathuria
og:description: Dr. Mathuria completed her fellowship in adult and pediatric Allergy, Asthma and Immunology at the Johns Hopkins University School of Medicine, where she earned the Allergy/Immunology Clinical Fellowship Award given by the American Academy of Allergy, Asthma and Immunology.  She completed her residency at Georgetown University Medical Center, internship at Eastern Virginia Medical School, and medical training through the combined BS/MD program at the Medical College of Virginia.  Dr. Mathuria has published several basic science articles and performed research at various institutions including Johns Hopkins University, the National Institutes of Health, and the Yale School of Medicine. She has been practicing in Northern Virginia for the past six years and is part time faculty at Johns Hopkins University. She sees all pediatric and adult allergy and immunology patients, including those with chronic rhinosinusitis, drug and insect allergy, urticaria, eczema, immunodeficiency and asthma. Her special interests include food allergy and eosinophilic esophagitis. Dr. Mathuria was born in Washington DC, lives in Fairfax with her husband and twin boys, and enjoys dancing and swimming.

Dr. Barmore is committed to helping her patients enjoy a healthier lifestyle. She works with each one to discuss ways they can make better choices for their health.

name: Dr. Keith West
og:description: Dr. Keith West grew up in upstate New York where he enjoyed a lifetime of competitive sports; focusing primarily on soccer, tennis, and cycling.  Athletics taught him the virtues of hard work and perseverance, attributes which he carries over into his professional career.   Dr. West graduated as valedictorian from Owego Free Academy, and went on to further his education at Cornell University where he received his Bachelors degree in biological sciences.  Following a year of travelling and teaching in Spain and Colombia, Dr. West continued his educational journey at New York Chiropractic College where he earned his Doctor of Chiropractic degree with honors and completed a yearlong internship at the Miami VA Medical Center. Dr. West follows an evidence-based approach to health care in order to provide his patients with proven treatment protocols.  Techniques employed include, hands on adjustments, Cox Flexion and Distraction, decompression therapy, and Active Release.  Dr. West also recognizes the importance of proper muscular balance and incorporates functional rehabilitation exercises into his treatment plans when appropriate.   Dr. West works within a multidisciplinary group that includes orthopedists, physical therapists, acupuncturists, physiatrists, podiatrists and massage therapists to provide the most effective treatment and the relief you need.

review_text: Keith is a great chiropractor.  Not only are his treatments effective, but he does a great job of talking you through everything he's doing, the reasons, etc.  It's sadly far too easy to find a bad chiropractor - the ones who try to push you with treatments you don't need and manipulations that don't work.  If you're looking for a good one, book Keith.  Seriously, you won't regret it. ,I have been seeing the team at Manhattan Sports Medicine for about 4 weeks and I feel tremendously better. I have some shoulder and neck issues and even though I'm still continuing treatment, my posture has improved as well as my stiffness!,I came early and they were busy. didn't wait more than 5 minutes from my scheduled appointment time.  love love love dr. west!!!,It was great! The staff was extreamly freandly and helpful. ,He was really great and super informative. Very knowledgeable about my scoliosis and forms of back and hip pain I was experiencing. He didn't withheld any thoughts and is very helpful. Also is a great conversationalist.,Explains everything, uses good hands-on techniques, and care is effective.  Big fan of Dr West - glad to have a good chiropractor in NYC. ,First visit was awesome.  I am not new to Chiropractic and have been looking for a doctor in NYC who reminds me of the holistic care I got from my therapist in NJ and Chicago.  Dr. West explained everything thoroughly and used techniques that really got to the root of the issue.  The staff is really friendly, as well.  I'm feeling really positive about my care in this office!,Doctor West was wonderful! He was mindful, explained to me all the procedures and was very patient with any question I may have. I absolutely recommend him!,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

name: Dr. Valerie Phillips
og:description: Doctor Valerie Phillips ND (Dr. Val) is a native Angelino who started studying the medical arts as a teenager in magnet school. She studied Biochemistry at U.C. Davis, and subsequently pursued research in neuropathology at U.C. San Francisco.  She also volunteered at the Berkeley Free Clinic and at the Native American Health Center in San Francisco, and became a “lay healthcare worker,” delivering limited primary care services to the underserved populations of the San Francisco Bay area.  Based on this experience, Dr. Val decided to pursue her long term interest in eastern and alternative forms of medine by pursuing a Naturopathic Medical degree at Bastyr University in Kenmore, WA. The education was the perfect blend of western scientific medical thought combined with herbal traditions from across the globe, nutrition, physical medicine and many more disciplines designed to train physicians to see all the aspects of the human body as a holistic unit. As eclectic as the Bastyr education was, Dr. Val added extra study in the areas of Yoga, raw foods nutrition and detoxification medicine. She is currently practicing as an alternative primary care physician offering many services, including the following: Bio-identical hormone replacement for men and women Women's health Natural therapeutics for Autoimmune disease Prolotherapy and prolozone injections for musculoskeletal and joint pain Digestive System healing Therapeutic diets Cognitive enhancement therapy Cardiovascular disease management Respiratory disease management Adjunctive cancer therapeutics IV nutrition /chelation Dr. Val's treatments are designed to enhance the overall health of her patients, to optimize vitality, and thereby prevent and reverse illness.

name: Shelley Tomlin
og:description: Shelley Tomlin is a board certified Family Nurse Practitioner at Hillcrest Medical. Ms. Tomlin received both her bachelor’s and master’s degrees in nursing from Texas Woman’s University. She began her nursing career at Parkland Hospital as a Nurse Resident in the Neonatal ICU. Afterwards, she worked as a school nurse in DISD, where she was responsible for the health and safety of students, faculty, and staff.  As a family nurse practitioner, Ms. Tomlin is licensed by the state of Texas to treat and to diagnose various illnesses and to perform annual exams for patients of all ages. Ms. Tomlin is dedicated to providing quality care and wellness to patients and their families. She will take the time to listen to all of your health concerns and to address your needs. When not working, Ms. Tomlin enjoys spending time with her husband and three children.

name: Dr. Anne Schroeder
og:description: Dr. Anne E. Schroeder is a graduate of the University of Chicago where she was awarded the honor of placement on the Dean's List. After graduating from medical school, she went on to complete a medical internship at Rush University Medical Center in Chicago. Dr. Schroeder then successfully completed her ophthalmology residency at Havener Eye Institute at the Ohio State University Medical Center in Columbus, Ohio.  Dr. Schroeder is a fellow of the American Academy of Ophthalmology and is a diplomate of the American Board of Ophthalmology. She enjoys treating adult patients, having experience in the diagnosis and treatment of a variety of conditions including glaucoma, diabetic retinopathy, macular degeneration, and with a special emphasis on dry eye and ocular surface disorders.  Dr. Schroeder was born and raised in Chicago, and has crisscrossed the globe with her husband before settling in Arizona. When not attending to patients, Dr. Schroeder is an avid antiquer who enjoys the arts, watching English period dramas, and spoiling the newest member of their family – Jean-Luc, their precociously charming Coton de Tulear puppy.
