name: Dr. Zachary Kordik
og:description: Zachary Kordik is a considerate and experienced psychiatrist as well as addiction specialist serving the community of Chicago, IL. He attended the University of Illinois, Chicago, where he received his medical degree, and completed his residency in psychiatry at Rush University Medical Center. He also holds a bachelor’s degree from the University of Notre Dame. Dr. Kordik is certified by the American Board of Psychiatry and Neurology and the American Board of Addiction Medicine. He is affiliated with Rush University Medical Center and Presence Saint Joseph Hospital in Chicago, IL. He gives each patient his focused attention, and he prides himself on delivering the best treatment available. Dr. Kordik is an assistant professor at Rush University Medical Center where he works with and supervises Psychiatry resident physicians and anesthesiologists pursuing a fellowship in Pain Management. He also volunteers and serves on the Associates Board at the Judd Goldman Adaptive Sailing Foundation, which enables physically disabled persons the opportunity to learn to sail on Lake Michigan.   Dr. Kordik is devoted to ensuring the longevity of his patients’ health and developing long-lasting relationships with them. He takes his time to understand symptoms and give correct diagnoses to ensure the continued health of all his patients.

name: Dr. Margaret Dupree Hobson
og:description: Dr. Hobson Dupree received her undergraduate degree from the University of Texas at Austin in 1988 and joined the US Navy the following year.  After completing a tour of duty at the National Naval Medical Center and a deployment to the Persian Gulf,  she attended and received her medical degree from the Uniformed Services University of the Health Sciences at Bethesda, Maryland where she graduated with honors  and was awarded the Navy Surgeon General Award.    She completed internship at the National Naval Medical Center before serving  as a Naval Flight Surgeon for 3 years at Marine Corps Air Station (MCAS) Miramar then completing Dermatology residency at Naval Medical Center San Diego.  Board certified by the American Board of Dermatology since 2002, she served as Head of the Dermatology Division at Naval Hospital Camp Pendleton and MCAS Miramar.  After leaving active duty in 2006, she was a Dermatologist at Scripps Clinic Medical Group, Nova Medical Group and Mid-Atlantic Permanente Medical Group before moving back to North San Diego County  to start North County Dermatology Center with her partner and colleague Dr. David Thomas.  Dr. Hobson Dupree is a fellow of the American Academy of Dermatology,  a member of the Alpha Omega Alpha Honor Medical Society and San Diego Society for Dermatological Surgery.  She has a been a speaker at several national meetings, given many dermatology lectures and has been published in a number of professional journals.  She was selected as a Top Doctor in Dermatology  (Northern Virginia)  and Consumers Checkbook Top Doctor (Washington DC) in 2015.  Her scope of practice includes medical, surgical and cosmetic dermatology.  She speaks Japanese fluently.

name: Dr. Randy Charrier
og:description: Aside from his career in the United States Navy, Dr. Charrier has lived in southeast Texas his whole life.  He holds two bachelors degrees in Music and Biology and earned a Doctor of Optometry degree from the University of Houston. As a naval officer, Dr. Charrier served as Director of the Specialty Contact Lens Clinic at the Naval Hospital in San Diego, California.  While there, he served military members and their families in comprehensive and medical eye care as well as fit medically necessary contact lenses on patients with eye disease or trauma from the battle field. In his time at the Naval hospital, Dr. Charrier routinely treated patients suffering from eye disease, war injuries, traumatic brain injuries and corneal diseases.  Furthermore, he served as optometrist to our nation’s elite war fighters and pilots including SEALS and the famous Blue Angels. In his career, Dr. Charrier has treated thousands of healthy as well as complicated patients and continues to have one of the largest specialty contact lens practices in the country. Dr. Charrier is active in lecturing and research.  He has held Associate Professor positions at Marshall B. Ketchum University, Pacific University, and currently at the University of Houston.  It is common to see interns and residents training at the practice. Dr. Charrier is passionate about helping patients find the best solution to meet their visual needs.

Dr. Charrier was pleasant, patient, and willing to explain in lay terms, the medical concerns of my eyes and examination process. It was a true pleasure meeting him and his entire team.  Office was quiet and calm, offered coffee and pastries while you wait. I didn't wait five minutes before I was called. Greeted as soon as I entered. Spot on hospitality, professionalism, and welcoming. ,Dr. Charrier and his staff were very professional, thorough, and considerate.  It had been a long time since I had an eye exam, but as far as I could tell the latest equipment and techniques were used.  Dr. Charrier spent about 20 minutes explaining the results of the eye exam and possible options in terms eyeglasses with me, which was more time than I expected.  I highly recommend his office to anyone.,The ladies working at the front desk were very friendly, professional and courteous. The gentleman who goes through the introduction information ("what brings you in today") was very personable and interactive. name: Dr. Mychailo Fulmes
og:description: Mychailo Fulmes is a surgeon specializing in colorectal surgery caring for the Metropolitan New York area. Dr. Fulmes earned his medical degree from Lviv, Ukraine. He then moved to the United States and completed his residency in general surgery at one of the Cleveland Clinic Hospitals. During fellowships, he trained at Memorial Sloan Kettering, New York Presbyterian Weill Cornell hospital and Lehigh Valley Hospital in Pennsylvania. Dr. Fulmes runs his own practice and is board certified by the American Board of Colon and Rectal Surgery and the American Board of Surgery. He is a member of the International Society of University Colon and Rectal Surgeons and the American Society Colon and Rectal Surgery. His medical career is colored by many outstanding contributions to medicine, including several publications, research, and scientific presentations. Patients trust Dr. Fulmes’s expertise because he consistently provides high quality care that leads to positive and lasting health outcomes. Dr. Fulmes developed unique technique for treatment of severe anal pain and anal fissure in the office even on initial visit. No surgery, no sphincterotomy (partial  sphincter division). Excellent results close to 100%. Pain relieve on day one after procedure. He is a patent developer for postoperative wound infection prevention. He believes alternative medicine can be used in many colorectal/health conditions in addition to medications and surgical procedures. Dr. Fulmes is devoted to ensuring the longevity of his patients’ health and developing long-lasting relationships with them. He takes his time to understand symptoms and give correct diagnoses to ensure the continued health.

Her office was easy to find and the staff was friendly and efficient.

I very rarely like doctors, let alone love them, but: I LOVED Dr. McGugins Hill. She was friendly and had an excellent bedside manor. My appointment didn't feel rushed, and she took the time to answer questions and address my concerns. She was incredibly thorough and extremely patient.

She ordered blood work and explained that their office doesn't make appointments for blood work, and that I could just come during certain hours to get my blood drawn. I was a bit nervous about this--I didn't want to sit there for an hour just to get blood drawn--so I called ahead before going in about a week later. It turned out to be no problem, and I was in and out of the office within 45 minutes or so. Dr. McGugins Hill called me the very next day with my results.

name: Dr. Jaclyn Hutchins
og:description: Dr. Renee Dunlap is an optometrist treating patients in San Antonio, Texas, and the surrounding communities. She is dedicated to providing high-quality, individualized, and compassionate care to each of her patients.  For her undergraduate degree, Dr. Dunlap attended Texas A&M University - Corpus Christi. She pursued her doctoral degree in optometry at the University of Houston College of Optometry. Patients visiting Dr. Hutchins can receive a full range of optometric services. She provides fittings for eyeglasses and treatment for issues including glaucoma, dry eyes, allergies, infections, injuries, and macular degeneration. Her specialties include Diabetic eye care, Glaucoma, Pediatrics, Dry Eye, Allergies, Infections, Injuries, Pre and Post op LASIK and Cataract surgery

name: Dr. Andrew Gilmartin
og:description: r. Gilmartin has completed internal medicine training, with honors, at St. Francis Medical Center in Trenton. He is a native of Massachusetts (and a secret Boston Red Sox fan, we suspect!) Dr. Gilmartin completed his education at Wheaton College, Boston University and St. Georges Medical School. He has done research at Becton Dickinson and is a member of the Mashpee Wampanoag Nation. He comes to us with top-notch recommendations from his teachers and will be a great addition to our expanding group of medical providers.  Dr. Gilmartin is married and has two young sons. He will see patients at our medical office and also at Morristown Medical Center and St. Clares Hospital, as well as at the neighboring long-term facilities. In his spare time, Andrew enjoys golf, sailing, fishing, and Alpine skiing.

name: Dr. Andrew Gilmartin
og:description: r. Gilmartin has completed internal medicine training, with honors, at St. Francis Medical Center in Trenton. He is a native of Massachusetts (and a secret Boston Red Sox fan, we suspect!) Dr. Gilmartin completed his education at Wheaton College, Boston University and St. Georges Medical School. He has done research at Becton Dickinson and is a member of the Mashpee Wampanoag Nation. He comes to us with top-notch recommendations from his teachers and will be a great addition to our expanding group of medical providers.  Dr. Gilmartin is married and has two young sons. He will see patients at our medical office and also at Morristown Medical Center and St. Clares Hospital, as well as at the neighboring long-term facilities. In his spare time, Andrew enjoys golf, sailing, fishing, and Alpine skiing.

name: Dr. James Nodler
og:description: Dr. Jamie Nodler was born and raised in Houston, Texas. He is board certified in Obstetrics and Gynecology by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology. He was named a "Texas Rising Star" by Super Docs in Texas Monthly Magazine in 2016. Dr. Nodler was an Instructor at Harvard Medical School and a Visiting Scientist at Boston Children’s Hospital while completing his fellowship in Reproductive Endocrinology and Infertility at Harvard Medical School’s Brigham and Women’s Hospital in Boston, Massachusetts. He received his Baccalaureate degree in Biology from the University of Texas at Austin. Following medical school at the Texas Tech University School of Medicine, Dr. Nodler completed residency training in Obstetrics and Gynecology at the University of Alabama at Birmingham. Dr. Nodler is a Fellow of the American Congress of Obstetricians and Gynecologists, member of the American Society of Reproductive Medicine, and member of the American Association of Gynecologic Laparoscopists. He has received multiple honors and awards including research grants from Harvard Medical School, the Brigham and Women’s Hospital Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology, and the New England Fertility Society. He has extensive experience in robotic surgery with a focus on uterine fibroids and endometriosis, and has completed the Intuitive Surgical da Vinci Robotic Skills training program. Dr. Nodler’s research at Harvard focused on the areas of nutrition and endometriosis. He has also published in peer-reviewed journals and presented research at national meetings on recurrent pregnancy loss, reproductive surgery, and polycystic ovarian syndrome, and published data on uterine fibroids while working at the National Institutes of Health in Washington D.C.  *Will verify all insurances.

name: Chris Turner
og:description: Christine Turner, WHNP-BC, graduated from Brenau Women’s College, Gainesville, Georgia, in 1984 with a Bachelor’s Degree in Nursing. In 2001, Chris attended the Nell Hodgson School of Nursing (Emory University) to pursue a Master’s Degree in Nursing in the Women’s Health Nurse Practitioner program. She is certified by the National Certification Corporation for the Obstetric, Gynecologic, and Neonatal Nursing Specialties Center. She is a member of the National Association of Nurse Practitioners in Women’s Health and North American Menopause Society. Chris began her career as a staff nurse at Emory University Hospital in Atlanta; she specialized in Hematology/Oncology. Since then, she has worked in a wide range of settings including community and university-based HIV/AIDS clinical research sites, hospice, a progressive independent women’s clinic, an Atlanta area women’s prison and a private Gynecology/ Urogynecology practice. Chris has worked in the Metro-Atlanta area in various settings in Gynecology/Women's Health, HIV/AIDS and Oncology/Hematology. Much of her clinical research knowledge was derived from working with clinical trials at the AIDS Research Consortium of Atlanta (ARCA) and at the Emory University ACTG program. Other important insight and experience was gained through providing hospice care at Atlanta’s Haven House and administering public health education programs for incarcerated women and men in Georgia through Emory’s Rollins School of Public Health. She also practiced at Metro State Women’s Prison (GA Department of Corrections/Office of Health Services), which afforded her opportunities to both develop and implement women’s health policy. Chris most recently worked for a private Gynecology/ Urogynecology practice focusing on health education and prevention/treatment of disease for women of all ages and socioeconomic status.

name: Dr. Glenn Waldman
og:description: Dr. Glenn Waldman is a highly experienced board-certified otolaryngologist and facial plastic surgeon who has been practicing in the Thousand Oaks and Simi Valley areas since 2000. Dr. Waldman graduated magna cum laude from the University of California, San Diego, and went on to complete medical school at the University of Southern California School of Medicine. After an internship in general surgery and his residency in otolaryngology-head and neck surgery-facial plastic and reconstructive surgery, Dr. Waldman opened his own practice in Thousand Oaks, California. As an otolaryngologist, he treats all disorders relating to the ear, nose, and throat and has a special interest in sinus disorders. In addition, Dr. Waldman specializes in facial plastic and reconstructive surgery, using the most current and advanced methods available to perform procedures, such as facial rejuvenation surgery, eyelid surgery, and his well-known rhinoplasty. He employs his cosmetic surgical expertise and state-of-the-art techniques to achieve results that are natural, rejuvenating, and aesthetically pleasing, and always with the patient’s utmost satisfaction in mind. With patients flying from all over the world to see him, Dr. Waldman has made a reputation for himself as one of the most trusted names in his field.

name: Dr. Catalina Grija
og:description: As a third-generation doctor, Dr. Catalina Grija's concern for the health of her patients runs in her blood. Her grandfather was a pulmonologist (lung doctor) and radiologist, and her mother was a dentist. Dr. Grija is part of a family that has made people their life.   Dr. Grija’s philosophy of medicine emphasizes a focus on people. It brings her great satisfaction to make a person feel better or to save a life. With a passion for internal medicine, Dr. Grija enjoys her work and has made her patients the foundation of her practice. A firm believer in the benefits of alternative medicine, Dr. Grija will only recommend medications that have proven to be safe and effective. If there’s one thing you can expect from Dr. Grija, it’s a genuine love for what she does and who she treats.   Dr. Grija received her medical degree from Carol Davila Institute of Medicine and Pharmacy in Bucharest, Romania, and completed her residency at West Suburban Hospital in Chicago, Illinois. Dr. Grija is board-certified by the American Board of Internal Medicine and is a USCIS designated civil surgeon. She has published a number of medical articles and stays up-to-date on the latest in medicine with continuing education, conferences, and medical journals.   Married with two children, Dr. Grija enjoys music, opera, traveling, reading, and swimming. She speaks English and Romanian, as well as some German and French.

name: Dr. Beaula Koduri
og:description: Dr. Koduri received her medical degree from Osmania Medical College in Hyderabad, India. She completed Internal Medicine Residencies at Pennsylvania Hospital in Philadelphia and Morristown Memorial Hospital in New Jersey, and did her Fellowship in Hematology/Oncology at Lankenau Hospital in Wynnewood, Pennsylvania. Dr. Koduri also has research experience in Breast Cancer Biopsies. She is a member of the American Medical Association, the American Society of Hematology, and the American Society of Clinical Oncology. It was her undying passion for Medical Oncology and Hematology backed up with over decade of extensive clinical experience that led Dr. Koduri to establish her own private practice   “Hematology-Oncology Consultants, LLC” at New Jersey. She accepts several major insurances and is currently accepting new patients as well.

name: Dr. Patrick Jean-Pierre
og:description: Dr Jean-Pierre completed his undergraduate studies at Cornell University with a focus on human biology and nutritional sciences then completed his medical school at SUNY Upstate Medical University.  He did his Internship and Residency in Internal Medicine at North Shore University Hospital in Manhasset. He completed his fellowship in Primary Care Sports Medicine at Henry Ford Hospital. Dr Jean-Pierre is Board Certified in both Internal Medicine and Sports Medicine.  He is a Diplomate in Integrative/Regenerative Medicine by the American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine.   Dr Jean-Pierre's experience working as a Hospitalist helped him realize the true importance of prevention for the improved treatment of chronic diseases.  He believes in using a combination of conventional medicine with integrative and holistic concepts to provide a highly specialized care to his patients. Dr Jean-Pierre is uniquely trained in both Internal Medicine and Anti-Aging/Integrative Medicine. By reviewing a patient’s health history, medications and activity level he will formulate a customized program of medications/supplements, nutrition and exercise. Dr Jean-Pierre is also fellowship trained in the evaluation, diagnosis and treatment of musculoskeletal injuries. He treats patients of all activity levels; he is a former assistant team physician for high school and Division I college athletes.   He worked closely in his fellowship under the physicians responsible for the medical care of the NFL’s Detroit Lions and MLB’s Detroit Tigers. Using a multidisciplinary approach, he will provide a comprehensive non-operative plan for the treatment of musculoskeletal injuries. Dr Jean-Pierre has a special interest in the prevention of chronic injuries, exercise programs and concussion management.

name: Dr. Lisa Jackson
og:description: Dr. Jackson is a board certified Obstetrician-Gynecologist. She received her bachelors degree in Economics from New York University, and her medical degree from Vanderbilt University in Nashville, TN. She completed her residency training in Chicago at Rush University Medical Center. Upon her return to NYC in 2007, Dr. Jackson worked as a staff physician at Jamaica Hospital and Mount Sinai Hospital, where she supervised residents, taught medical students, and worked in clinics in underserved areas in Queens, and East Harlem. She has also worked in the world of private practice on the upper west side for several years. Currently she is an Assistant Clinical Professor of OBGYN at Mount Sinai, and has worked primarily as a laborist for the last 2 1/2 years. Dr. Jackson’s areas of interest include adolescent health, contraceptive education, obstetrical health, and labor/postpartum support. Her goal is to provide support and guidance to her patients wherever they are in their reproductive or post-reproductive journey. Outside of work, she enjoys the outdoors, pilates, and spending time with her husband and two young children.

name: Dr. Francisco Gelpi-Hammerschmidt
og:description: Dr. Gelpi joins Houston Metro Urology from Harvard University, where he completed a fellowship in Urologic Oncology.  He specializes in minimally invasive surgical procedures concerning the treatment of malignant genitourinary diseases such as cancer of the prostate, bladder, and other urologic tissue. Minimally invasive surgery refers to the approach of treatment that requires small to no incision relative to what is traditionally used in open surgery, while yielding comparable results.  Using these minimally invasive techniques along with the latest in medical technology, Dr. Gelpi is able to greatly reduce patient discomfort post surgery and insure a more rapid recovery time.  He has published in multiple peer-reviewed medical journals, presented at multiple regional/national meetings, and received many awards for his works. His passion for medical advances is only surpassed by the well being and care for his patients.

name: Dr. Christopher Fincke
og:description: Dr. Fincke obtained his undergraduate and medical degree from The George Washington University in Washington DC. He completed a Gastroenterology fellowship at BAMC (SAMMC) and later served as a faculty gastroenterologist for the San Antonio Uniformed Health Services Gastroenterology Fellowship program, where he was responsible for the education and training of numerous GI physicians. Upon the completion of his 11 years of military service in the United States Army, Dr. Fincke began private practice in San Antonio in 2007.  Dr. Fincke’s interests include general gastroenterology and hepatology, as well as therapeutic endoscopy, including ERCP and Endoscopic Ultrasound (EUS). In addition, he has expertise in celiac plexus block, endoluminal stenting, complex biliary and pancreatic endoscopy and HALO™ radiofrequency ablation of Barrett’s Esophagus. Dr. Fincke is active in several charitable organizations in the San Antonio community and when not practicing medicine, he enjoys attending and coaching his children’s various sporting events.

name: Dr. Oana Galicki
og:description: Dr. Galicki completed her general psychiatry residency followed by a fellowship in Psychosomatic Medicine, at St. Luke’s-Roosevelt Medical Center, a training hospital of Columbia University College of Physicians and Surgeons in New York City. After graduation, Dr. Galicki continued on as a staff psychiatrist responsible for running the Consult Liaison service as well as providing teaching and supervision for psychiatry residents and fellows. She has also conducted research and published papers on subjects including treatment for depression in patients with Parkinson’s disease and Alzheimer’s disease prevention. Since moving to San Francisco in 2011, she has been providing outpatient psychiatric care to a diverse population in both community clinic and private practice settings.

My only issue was how much paperwork TMS put me through the first time, even though I had seen Dr. Galicki through another office before.  I would've rather done the paperwork in the waiting room instead of via email before confirming an appointment.,she was very easy to talk to and trustworthy. she seemed like she genuinely cares.,Competent professional with a wide range of experience and expertise. ,Quick and easy appointment right in the middle of town!,Dr. Galicki is wonderful! Her office is very relaxing and her staff is efficient and caring. She is extremely professional, non-judgemental, and calm. She understands what you're dealing with, is empathetic, and is a greater listener.,Her bedside manner was perfect. She made me feel comfortable and that I wasn't just another patient. She made me feel important.,My current doctor recently retired and I had to find someone quickly as it was a sudden retirement. So was not certain what to expect. Dr. Galicki was terrific: very knowledgeable letting me know latest research on some medication I was taking and side effects plus recommending a tweak to my current medication as I have been experiencing symptoms for months that me and my prior doctor had attributed to peri menopause. Haven't tried the new medicine but felt relief that possibly there's an option to treat some of the side effects I have been struggling with. She is warm, sympathetic and nice!

og:description: SAME DAY APPOINTMENTS ARE ALWAYS AVAILABLE.  Yes, we provide primary care for your family Please call our office if you don't find the appointment you need here and we will be happy to accommodate. Full Service Primary Care Tara Cavazos grew up in Norman, OK. After graduating from Baylor University with her nursing degree she worked in the Pediatric Intensive Care Unit at Medical City Children's Hospital. Tara earned her Master's Degree in Nursing at the University of Texas at Arlington, where she was an MSN Academic Scholar and was awarded with the Excellence in Clinical Nursing two consecutive years. In her free time, she enjoys spending time outdoors with her family, running, watching sports, and traveling. Tara volunteers her time at a local urgent care clinic for the underserved population of Dallas.

name: Dr. David Vieweger
og:description: Dr. Vieweger completed his foot and ankle surgical residency at MedStar Washington Hospital Center. During residency, he performed more procedures than any previous graduate of the program before him. Dr. Vieweger specializes in helping patients achieve optimal foot health through both surgical and conservative methods. A D.C. area native, Dr. Vieweger grew up in Stafford, Virginia. He is an avid runner and enjoys competing in local races. He has a special interest in helping both professional and amateur athletes compete at their highest ability. During his leisure time, he enjoys biking, watersports, and traveling. EDUCATION Doctorate in Podiatric Medicine, Scholl College of Podiatric Medicine at Rosalind Franklin University of Medicine and Science, North Chicago, Illinois, 2013. Dr. Vieweger completed three-year post-graduate Foot and Ankle Reconstruction training program at MedStar Washington Hospital Center and MedStar Georgetown University Hospital. Extensive training in diabetic limb salvage, trauma, sports medicine and elective foot and ankle reconstruction. Board Qualified by the American Board of Foot and Ankle Surgery (ABFAS) in foot and ankle surgery.

name: Dr. Kim Ip
og:description: Dr. Kim Ip was born in Hong Kong and moved to Texas to attend O’Conner High School here in San Antonio. She graduated from The University of Texas at Austin with a Bachelor of Science in Biology. She then received her Doctorate of Optometry from the University of Houston College of Optometry. For her clinical rotation, she was trained at the Naval Medical Center at San Diego, California and the South Texas Veterans Eye Clinic in San Antonio, Texas. As a board certified therapeutic optometrist and an optometric glaucoma specialist in Texas, she treats and manages glaucoma, diabetes, dry eye, cataract, macular degeneration, and other eye diseases. She is also a member of the American Optometric Association and Texas Optometric Association. Dr. Ip returned to San Antonio after completing optometry school and is looking forward to becoming a part of the growing community here.

review_text:
This was my first appointment with Dr. Kelly and if the treatment I received today is indicative of what is to come, I eagerly look forward to becoming an established patient!  First, I would be remiss if I did not mention Nicole, her medical assistant.  Nicole is such a joy -- she examined me before I met with Dr. Kelly and I was impressed by Nicole's level of knowledge!  It quickly became apparent that Nicole "knows her stuff" because Dr. Kelly was briefed by Nicole before entering the exam room and was not only comfortable with Nicole's assessment of my condition, but also in total agreement!  That says a lot about her trust in Nicole’s abilities!  When Dr. Kelly entered the room, her warm smile made me feel like an old friend.  She not only examined me once again but also took a keen interest in listening to me -- an important quality that some physicians seem to lack.  Afterwards, Dr. Kelly gave me her recommendations, which I readily accepted.  Her diagnoses were right on point and I left her office feeling as if I was her only patient – the quality of care I received was nothing short of phenomenal!  Lastly, I cannot leave out how professional and welcoming her front office personnel were.  They greeted me with a smile and both were very accommodating. name: Dr. George Roepke
og:description: George Roepke is a mindful and skilled family physician based in Chicago, IL. Dr. Roepke earned his medical degree from Thomas Jefferson University in Philadelphia, PA. He then completed his residency in family medicine at the University of Illinois, Chicago, Saint Joseph Hospital. Dr. Roepke is part of Presence Medical Group Primary Care, Chicago and is affiliated with Presence Saint Joseph Hospital in Chicago. He is board certified by the American Board of Family Medicine and is a member of the American Academy of Family Physicians. Dr. Roepke enjoys giving back to his community and has participated in many volunteer activities, including serving as an Ambulatory Resident Physician at Community Health Clinic through June 2012 to June 2015 and also volunteered at Physician Seton Family Health Medical Tent in August 2015.  Dr. Roepke is committed to helping his patients enjoy a healthier lifestyle. He works with each one to discuss ways they can make better choices for their health.

name: Dr. Jennifer McGugins Hill
og:description: Jennifer McGugins Hill is a skilled and trusted primary care doctor and internist caring for the Park Ridge, NJ community. Dr. McGugins Hill attended the University of Maryland, where she earned her degree in medicine. She completed her residency in internal medicine at New York Medical College. Dr. McGugins Hill is part of VMG Park Ridge Medical and is affiliated with the Valley Hospital, NJ. Dr. McGugins Hill is board certified by the American Board of Internal Medicine. Because Dr. Demirci is bilingual in English and Spanish, patients from a variety of backgrounds enjoy having her as their physician. Dr. McGugins Hill is devoted to ensuring the longevity of her patients’ health and developing long-lasting relationships with them. She takes her time to understand symptoms and give correct diagnoses to ensure the continued health of all her patients.

name: Dr. Annalise James Hussain
og:description: Dr. James is originally from Seattle, Washington where she completed her undergraduate education.  She then went on to attend medical school at Creighton University in Omaha, Nebraska followed by residency training in obstetrics and gynecology at the University of Missouri in Kansas City.  Dr. James's special interests include but are not limited to:  Contraceptive counseling, colposcopy and management of abnormal pap smears, abnormal uterine bleeding, and hysteroscopy.  She also serves as a clinical instructor at Northwestern University’s Feinberg School of Medicine.

,She's always great and has excellent bedside manner! 
There was an issue at the lab, so I had to go back in and provide more "samples". It wasn't an error on my part, so Joann said that I did not have to pay for the repeat appointment. I appreciate that, because I am disabled and can only afford so many copays each month. Other drs offices would have charged for the repeat visit!
Also very open and easy to speak with Joann about women's health issues! ,I absolutely love JoAnn, only issue with the office is the wait time. They always take so long to get to calling patience back and enter the room. , She is by far one of the best professional healthcare providers that I have encountered since moving here from New York.,Love love love Dr. Joann!!! She has a great bedside manner and really thinks outside of the box for dxes, like a physician should. 
Usually am seen right away. This one appointment was about a 30 mins wait, due to some construction in the office. Only felt uncomfortable because I was waiting undressed for a pap smear while hearing men outside the exam room door. 
I have an autoimmune disorder and have been searching for someone to do IV Vitamin Infusions therapy when I lived in CA to no avail. I want to schedule these ASAP and am so happy that I not only found a dr who does them, but also don't have to travel far out of my small town to get them! ,She has always been great and very caring. I recently moved, and the office is further away from my home. I left with a clear understanding and a plan for future goals. I was given a written recap of our visit with detailed information pertaining to my health. I did not feel rushed and she encouraged any questions I had. ,Very informative and educational. Joanne was pleasant with a very up beat personality. Enjoyable!,Awesome!!,Joann always asks relevant questions to the situation, and listens to your answers.  Very professional but also a good person who is easy to talk to.

name: Dr. Jose Echenique
og:description: Dr. Jose Echenique is a board certified orthopaedic surgeon who is fellowship trained in sports medicine and arthroscopic surgery of the shoulder and knee. Dr. Echenique obtained his doctor of medicine degree with honors from Dartmouth Medical School, Hanover, NH. While at Dartmouth he was the recipient of the Dartmouth-Mosenthal Anatomy Fellowship, a recognition given for his work conducting anatomic dissections, simulated surgical dissections, and his work as an anatomy lab instructor to other medical students. Dr. Echenique then went to complete an orthopedic surgery residency at George Washington University in Washington, DC where he was chief resident from 2008-2009. While in Washington, DC, he assisted in the care of the George Washington University athletes and served as onsite team physician for the District of Columbia Public Schools. Dr. Echenique then received specialized training in sports medicine and arthroscopy during his fellowship at the world renowned American Sports Medicine Institute (ASMI) in Birmingham, AL. While in Birmingham, Dr. Echenique gained vast experience in the nonsurgical and surgical treatment of athletes at all levels from High School to professional. He was team physician for Concordia College, Hueytown High School, Gardendale High School and Fultondale High School, and assisted in the care of athletes from Samford University, Alabama State University, Miles College, University of Montevallo and the United Football League. review_text:
Dr. Echenique was quick, candid, and precise in his treatment recommendation around a fracture I suffered. The office in general was superb as well: intake with the PA was done almost as soon as I arrived, x-rays were ordered and executed quickly, and those images were ready for review in minutes. Highly recommended all around!,Excellent professional.,Dr Echenique was very professional and very pleasant.I.He listened to my concerns, examined me thoroughly and explained what was the problem and what the treatment would be.He is a very good doctor and I would recommend him  friends and colleagues.,He is very nice, kind and professional.  I would love to recommend you. ,So wonderful!  Definitely made me feel comfortable and answered all my questions. ,I can't possibly say enough great things about Dr. Echenique! I went into see him for chronic neck and back pain that I have been having, and I was very apprehensive about the visit because I was in a lot of pain and even more so because some doctors don't have the best bed side manner or are very quick and/or dismissive- however he couldn't have been more wonderful! Dr. Echenique put me at ease right away. He let me express all of my symptoms, concerns and questions. He was very patient, informative and excellent at explaining everything so I could understand it. He was also very comforting and thorough. I had a great experience with everyone being very kind and professional - from the front desk, to the x-ray technician, to his nurse/PA, to the doctor himself. Excellent experience all around. I know that I am in great hands there. ,Dr. Echenique had a great bedside manner, but more than that, he took the time to explain the parts of the knee and point out specifically in the X-Ray and sonogram photos what we were looking at and what we were looking for.

He was very thorough and patient with my questions as well.,I've been dealing with an ongoing knee issue for >10 years; orthopedic surgeons had referred me to rheumatologists, and vice versa. I even had a prior knee surgery that made matters much worse. Dr. Echenique was humble, intelligent, patient, and thorough, and most importantly (in my particular case) provided me with insight no other physician had. ,He was professional and made me feel comfortable ,I haven't seen a doctor since before college and Dr Echenique seemed more like a friend than the doctors of my childhood.,I was able to get a same day appointment, which for an orthopedist was a pleasant and unexpected surprise. There was a delay in being seen because the receptionist forgot to check me in. Other than that, everyone one was professional and courteous.  Dr. Echenique answered all of my questions and took the time to educate me about my options.  I highly recommend him and his practice., Dr. Echenique  is truly unique in the world of doctors, and I've been to plenty in my lifetime, in that he always conveys and authenticity  that for me as his patient is crucial to my trust in him as a diagnostician  as well as his very personable and rarely have I seen a more instantly likeable  physician that I knew I was in good hands. He was thorough regarding all aspects of my diagnose ,  treatment, and most importantly for me, because I ask a lot of questions as I am very curious being a teacher myself of biology and chemistry ,  he took the time to answer all of my questions without making me feel like I was taking up too much of his time, which is truly  rare in the majority of the medical profession. I would recommend him to anybody for anything regarding  any issues  with your body that require the specification  of an orthopedist and or surgeon. Everyone on staff is genuinely pleasant and  gives you the feeling that they are only there to serve you, and treat you like the most important person during the time they are with you. Awesome!,He was a very nice and answered all of my questions.  His PA was fantastic.  She gave me an injection into my joint and I didn't feel a thing.,Saw him for rotator cuff.  Very pleased with the visit.  Explained all the options and the treatment.  Very down to earth, and knowledgeable -   with no condescending attitude.,Professional, courteous & efficient but thorough.,He was the consumate professional, pleasant respectful and knowledgeable,Everything about my appointment was handled expertly.  I've been to many Doctors throughout my life and he and his staff made me feel welcomed, calm, confident in my Doctor, and every question and concern I had was answered.  I am healing rapidly and know that I received the best treatment.  Highly-qualified, highly-rated, and highly recommended! Thank you. ,Dr . Echenique was empathetic. He explained my diagnosis clearly and concise. ,Very professional, with explanations clear and simple... He was sure that I leave the office with un understanding of my problem and its solution....,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA

name: JoEllen Embry
og:description: A Proven and Compassionate Expert in Women’s Health with a focus on PCOS, Endometriosis and Urinary Urgency.  JoEllen Embry has worked in women’s health for 31 years. Over the course of her career she had the privilege of working with excellent providers in women’s health. In 2014 she decided that it was time for a change. She wanted to provide women with the care they deserve. Allowing them time to receive treatment and understand their care plan.  Additionally, as someone who has been diagnosed with PCOS, she had first hand experience of providers ignoring the symptoms. She wanted to do things differently which inspired her to found Embry Women’s Health. She obtained her nurse practitioner degree from the University of Phoenix. She obtained her bachelors and nursing degree from Arizona State University. She is a Sun Devil by degree, but will always consider herself an Alabama girl at heart. Roll Tide! Doctors that she has had the privilege of working with previously include Dr Joseph Lindstrom, Dr Shelly Messer and Dr DeAnna Bullero-Anderer. Her industry experience is extensive and includes being a national speaker for GlaxoSmithKline, Warner Chilcott, Xanodyne, and TAPP Pharmaceuticals. She has been a member of East Valley OB/GYN Society, Arizona Family Planning Council, Arizona Nurses Association, National Association of Nurse Practitioners in Women’s Health, and The Arizona Postpartum Wellness Coalition. Specialities: PCOS, Endometriosis, Chronic Pelvic Pain, Abnormal Uterine Bleeding, Abnormal Periods, Abnormal Pap, Pregnancy, Infertility, Uterine Fibroids, HPV, Urinary Urgency, Sexual Dysfunction, Depression and Hormone Imbalance.

review_text:
JoEllen is the most wonderful ob/gyn doctor I have ever met. She is very down to earth and so easy to talk to. She is also very compassionate. I would definitely recommend her to anyone. She helped me with my PCOS and actually listened to me when no one else would. ,Great visit! Dr. Embry has a great bedside manner, and she made me feel very comfortable. ,Best ,Embry was very thorough and made me feel comfortable, she is so knowledgeable! Definitely a key player in your personal long term health care!  Took her time and was real with me; her staff and Embry made me feel very comfortable! I love the up to date email reminders and patient portal system she has. Very professional and clean. ,It was a great experience and Dr. Embry answered every question I had. ,Jo Ellen is AMAZING! She is kind, caring and very attentive. As a matter of fact, the entire office was top notch! I can not say enough good things about them. Best experience ever; from getting an appointment, to reminders, to personalized service. Thank you! :-) ,I have been her patient for many years.  Jo Ellen has had some tough conversations with me about my health.  She is always thorough, gives great referrals to other HCP's and has a solid work ethic.  She always follows through, follows up and truly cares! ,Highly recommended! Really took the time to explain things.,Everyone was professional, knowledgeable and personable. And even though I didn't see Jo Ellen until my appt time was over, I will go back and I would recommend her to friends and family.,Professional and clearly understood my health issues! My first visit and look forward to working with Jo Ellen to get even healthier in 2016!
,Professional and very pleasant to speak with and she listens to all of my concerns. Definitely recommend her to other women!,She was easy to talk to and quite personable. I felt very comfortable which can be difficult for these kind of appointments. She didn't seem to pass any judgment and genuinely seemed to care about me as an individual and not just another code to bill. ,From her expertise to her bedside manner, I have never felt so heard or so sure a doctor understands the way my issues intertwine. Dr. Embry is incredibly knowledgable, attentive, thorough, and she treats the whole person. She is non-judgmental, and she actively listens to her patients. I'm recommending her to both of my sisters, and I have already scheduled a follow up. The wait might be a little longer than some offices, but there is a reason that no one in the waiting room is upset by it. Honestly, I'd wait much longer to see her if I had to. Highly recommend.,She took the time to listen to me and was very open and helpful. I'm so thankful to have found her!!!,We spent lots of time talk about my health and plans for the future. I didn't feel hurried out the door or anything and felt like she had a good handle on what's going on with me and what to do next. ,I am on Cloud 9 about what an incredible experience I had meeting Jo Ellen Embry. I've had my fair share of doctors for all types of issues, and she is by far the best I've ever had, hands down. She was so knowledgable, understanding, she listened and gave invaluable feedback; I've never felt so cared about by a doctor as I did with her. I'd recommend her to anyone and everyone. She is nothing short of amazing. ,I felt very comfortable and learned a lot I was not aware of. I have never felt comfortable seeing doctors and I felt as though Dr. Embry actually cared about my well being. She definitely made my visit feel personalized. I highly recommend her to anyone, even if you are not located in the Mesa area- it is definitely worth the drive!,My visit was awesome! She really took the time to listen to my concerns and get to know me beforehand. I have actually already recommended her to my sister and mom. ,Never have I ever enjoyed a doctor visit like I did today. I left in tears, but they were happy tears! Jo Ellen Embry was able to accomplish in one visit, what a handful of doctors could not in over 10 years! She was super informative and broke it down for me so that I would understand exactly what was going on and what she was going to do. She is a blessing and a true breath of fresh air! Thank you! Thank you so much for doing what you do! Above all, thank you for truly listening and for caring for my situation as much as I do. :) ,JoEllen is very easy to talk to.  She is very thorough.  The office is very nice with a real nice view.  I am glad to have finally found a 'physician' I can feel comfortable with.,Awsome!!!,Jo Ellen was amazing! So knowledgable & patient! I have always been intimidated by going to doctors and such, but she made the appointment so comfortable & I highly recommend her! ,She is great. Very professional and very informative and very easy to talk to. So glad I used Zocdoc and found her. ,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA
